66static void
67sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
68{
69 struct sctp_nets *net;
70
71 /* This now not only stops all cookie timers
72 * it also stops any INIT timers as well. This
73 * will make sure that the timers are stopped in
74 * all collision cases.
75 */
76 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
77 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
78 if (net->rxt_timer.type == SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE) {
79 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE,
80 stcb->sctp_ep,
81 stcb,
82 net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_1);
83 } else if (net->rxt_timer.type == SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT) {
84 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT,
85 stcb->sctp_ep,
86 stcb,
87 net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_2);
88 }
89 }
90}

92/* INIT handler */
93static void
94sctp_handle_init(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
95 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst, struct sctphdr *sh,
96 struct sctp_init_chunk *cp, struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
97 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, int *abort_no_unlock,
98#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
99 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
100#endif
101 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
102{
103 struct sctp_init *init;
104 struct mbuf *op_err;
105
106 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "sctp_handle_init: handling INIT tcb:%p\n",
107 (void *)stcb);
108 if (stcb == NULL) {
109 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
110 }
111 /* Validate parameters */
112 init = &cp->init;
113 if ((ntohl(init->initiate_tag) == 0) ||
114 (ntohl(init->a_rwnd) < SCTP_MIN_RWND) ||
115 (ntohs(init->num_inbound_streams) == 0) ||
116 (ntohs(init->num_outbound_streams) == 0)) {
117 /* protocol error... send abort */
118 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_INVALID_PARAM, "");
119 sctp_abort_association(inp, stcb, m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, op_err,
120#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
121 mflowtype, mflowid,
122#endif
123 vrf_id, port);
124 if (stcb)
125 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
126 goto outnow;
127 }
128 if (sctp_validate_init_auth_params(m, offset + sizeof(*cp),
129 offset + ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length))) {
130 /* auth parameter(s) error... send abort */
131 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
132 "Problem with AUTH parameters");
133 sctp_abort_association(inp, stcb, m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, op_err,
134#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
135 mflowtype, mflowid,
136#endif
137 vrf_id, port);
138 if (stcb)
139 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
140 goto outnow;
141 }
142 /* We are only accepting if we have a listening socket.*/
143 if ((stcb == NULL) &&
144 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
145 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
146 (!SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp)))) {
147 /*
148 * FIX ME ?? What about TCP model and we have a
149 * match/restart case? Actually no fix is needed.
150 * the lookup will always find the existing assoc so stcb
151 * would not be NULL. It may be questionable to do this
152 * since we COULD just send back the INIT-ACK and hope that
153 * the app did accept()'s by the time the COOKIE was sent. But
154 * there is a price to pay for COOKIE generation and I don't
155 * want to pay it on the chance that the app will actually do
156 * some accepts(). The App just looses and should NOT be in
157 * this state :-)
158 */
159 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_blackhole) == 0) {
160 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
161 "No listener");
162 sctp_send_abort(m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, 0, op_err,
163#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
164 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
165#endif
166 vrf_id, port);
167 }
168 goto outnow;
169 }
170 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
171 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
172 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "sctp_handle_init: sending SHUTDOWN-ACK\n");
173 sctp_send_shutdown_ack(stcb, NULL);
174 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_CONTROL_PROC, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
175 } else {
176 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "sctp_handle_init: sending INIT-ACK\n");
177 sctp_send_initiate_ack(inp, stcb, net, m, iphlen, offset,
178 src, dst, sh, cp,
179#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
180 mflowtype, mflowid,
181#endif
182 vrf_id, port);
183 }
184 outnow:
185 if (stcb == NULL) {
186 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
187 }
188}

190/*
191 * process peer "INIT/INIT-ACK" chunk returns value < 0 on error
192 */
193
194int
195sctp_is_there_unsent_data(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int so_locked)
196{
197 int unsent_data;
198 unsigned int i;
199 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
200 struct sctp_association *asoc;
201
202 /* This function returns if any stream has true unsent data on it.
203 * Note that as it looks through it will clean up any places that
204 * have old data that has been sent but left at top of stream queue.
205 */
206 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
207 unsent_data = 0;
208 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
209 if (!stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_is_empty(stcb, asoc)) {
210 /* Check to see if some data queued */
211 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
212 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
213 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue);
214 if (sp == NULL) {
215 continue;
216 }
217 if ((sp->msg_is_complete) &&
218 (sp->length == 0) &&
219 (sp->sender_all_done)) {
220 /* We are doing differed cleanup. Last
221 * time through when we took all the data
222 * the sender_all_done was not set.
223 */
224 if (sp->put_last_out == 0) {
225 SCTP_PRINTF("Gak, put out entire msg with NO end!-1\n");
226 SCTP_PRINTF("sender_done:%d len:%d msg_comp:%d put_last_out:%d\n",
227 sp->sender_all_done,
228 sp->length,
229 sp->msg_is_complete,
230 sp->put_last_out);
231 }
232 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt, 1);
233 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue, sp, next);
234 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, &asoc->strmout[i], sp, 1);
235 if (sp->net) {
236 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
237 sp->net = NULL;
238 }
239 if (sp->data) {
240 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
241 sp->data = NULL;
242 }
243 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, so_locked);
244 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue)) {
245 unsent_data++;
246 }
247 } else {
248 unsent_data++;
249 }
250 if (unsent_data > 0) {
251 break;
252 }
253 }
254 }
255 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
256 return (unsent_data);
257}
258
259static int
260sctp_process_init(struct sctp_init_chunk *cp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
261{
262 struct sctp_init *init;
263 struct sctp_association *asoc;
264 struct sctp_nets *lnet;
265 unsigned int i;
266
267 init = &cp->init;
268 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
269 /* save off parameters */
270 asoc->peer_vtag = ntohl(init->initiate_tag);
271 asoc->peers_rwnd = ntohl(init->a_rwnd);
272 /* init tsn's */
273 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map = asoc->asconf_seq_in = ntohl(init->initial_tsn) - 1;
274
275 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->nets)) {
276 /* update any ssthresh's that may have a default */
277 TAILQ_FOREACH(lnet, &asoc->nets, sctp_next) {
278 lnet->ssthresh = asoc->peers_rwnd;
279 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & (SCTP_CWND_MONITOR_ENABLE|SCTP_CWND_LOGGING_ENABLE)) {
280 sctp_log_cwnd(stcb, lnet, 0, SCTP_CWND_INITIALIZATION);
281 }
282 }
283 }
284 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
285 if (asoc->pre_open_streams > ntohs(init->num_inbound_streams)) {
286 unsigned int newcnt;
287 struct sctp_stream_out *outs;
288 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, *nsp;
289 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
290
291 /* abandon the upper streams */
292 newcnt = ntohs(init->num_inbound_streams);
293 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
294 if (chk->rec.data.sid >= newcnt) {
295 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
296 asoc->send_queue_cnt--;
297 if (asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
298 asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues--;
299#ifdef INVARIANTS
300 } else {
301 panic("No chunks on the queues for sid %u.", chk->rec.data.sid);
302#endif
303 }
304 if (chk->data != NULL) {
305 sctp_free_bufspace(stcb, asoc, chk, 1);
306 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL, stcb,
307 0, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
308 if (chk->data) {
309 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
310 chk->data = NULL;
311 }
312 }
313 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
314 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
315 }
316 }
317 if (asoc->strmout) {
318 for (i = newcnt; i < asoc->pre_open_streams; i++) {
319 outs = &asoc->strmout[i];
320 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sp, &outs->outqueue, next, nsp) {
321 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt, 1);
322 TAILQ_REMOVE(&outs->outqueue, sp, next);
323 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, outs, sp, 1);
324 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SPECIAL_SP_FAIL,
325 stcb, 0, sp, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
326 if (sp->data) {
327 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
328 sp->data = NULL;
329 }
330 if (sp->net) {
331 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
332 sp->net = NULL;
333 }
334 /* Free the chunk */
335 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
336 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
337 }
338 outs->state = SCTP_STREAM_CLOSED;
339 }
340 }
341 /* cut back the count */
342 asoc->pre_open_streams = newcnt;
343 }
344 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
345 asoc->streamoutcnt = asoc->pre_open_streams;
346 if (asoc->strmout) {
347 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamoutcnt; i++) {
348 asoc->strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_OPEN;
349 }
350 }
351 /* EY - nr_sack: initialize highest tsn in nr_mapping_array */
352 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map;
353 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MAP_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
354 sctp_log_map(0, 5, asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map, SCTP_MAP_SLIDE_RESULT);
355 }
356 /* This is the next one we expect */
357 asoc->str_reset_seq_in = asoc->asconf_seq_in + 1;
358
359 asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn = ntohl(init->initial_tsn);
360 asoc->tsn_last_delivered = asoc->cumulative_tsn = asoc->asconf_seq_in;
361
362 asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point = asoc->last_acked_seq;
363 /* open the requested streams */
364
365 if (asoc->strmin != NULL) {
366 /* Free the old ones */
367 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamincnt; i++) {
368 sctp_clean_up_stream(stcb, &asoc->strmin[i].inqueue);
369 sctp_clean_up_stream(stcb, &asoc->strmin[i].uno_inqueue);
370 }
371 SCTP_FREE(asoc->strmin, SCTP_M_STRMI);
372 }
373 if (asoc->max_inbound_streams > ntohs(init->num_outbound_streams)) {
374 asoc->streamincnt = ntohs(init->num_outbound_streams);
375 } else {
376 asoc->streamincnt = asoc->max_inbound_streams;
377 }
378 SCTP_MALLOC(asoc->strmin, struct sctp_stream_in *, asoc->streamincnt *
379 sizeof(struct sctp_stream_in), SCTP_M_STRMI);
380 if (asoc->strmin == NULL) {
381 /* we didn't get memory for the streams! */
382 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "process_init: couldn't get memory for the streams!\n");
383 return (-1);
384 }
385 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamincnt; i++) {
386 asoc->strmin[i].sid = i;
387 asoc->strmin[i].last_mid_delivered = 0xffffffff;
388 TAILQ_INIT(&asoc->strmin[i].inqueue);
389 TAILQ_INIT(&asoc->strmin[i].uno_inqueue);
390 asoc->strmin[i].pd_api_started = 0;
391 asoc->strmin[i].delivery_started = 0;
392 }
393 /*
394 * load_address_from_init will put the addresses into the
395 * association when the COOKIE is processed or the INIT-ACK is
396 * processed. Both types of COOKIE's existing and new call this
397 * routine. It will remove addresses that are no longer in the
398 * association (for the restarting case where addresses are
399 * removed). Up front when the INIT arrives we will discard it if it
400 * is a restart and new addresses have been added.
401 */
402 /* sa_ignore MEMLEAK */
403 return (0);
404}

406/*
407 * INIT-ACK message processing/consumption returns value < 0 on error
408 */
409static int
410sctp_process_init_ack(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
411 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst, struct sctphdr *sh,
412 struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *cp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
413 struct sctp_nets *net, int *abort_no_unlock,
414#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
415 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
416#endif
417 uint32_t vrf_id)
418{
419 struct sctp_association *asoc;
420 struct mbuf *op_err;
421 int retval, abort_flag, cookie_found;
422 int initack_limit;
423 int nat_friendly = 0;
424
425 /* First verify that we have no illegal param's */
426 abort_flag = 0;
427 cookie_found = 0;
428
429 op_err = sctp_arethere_unrecognized_parameters(m,
430 (offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk)),
431 &abort_flag, (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)cp,
432 &nat_friendly, &cookie_found);
433 if (abort_flag) {
434 /* Send an abort and notify peer */
435 sctp_abort_an_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, op_err, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
436 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
437 return (-1);
438 }
439 if (!cookie_found) {
440 uint16_t len;
441
442 /* Only report the missing cookie parameter */
443 if (op_err != NULL) {
444 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
445 }
446 len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_error_missing_param) + sizeof(uint16_t));
447 /* We abort with an error of missing mandatory param */
448 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
449 if (op_err != NULL) {
450 struct sctp_error_missing_param *cause;
451
452 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = len;
453 cause = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_error_missing_param *);
454 /* Subtract the reserved param */
455 cause->cause.code = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_MISSING_PARAM);
456 cause->cause.length = htons(len);
457 cause->num_missing_params = htonl(1);
458 cause->type[0] = htons(SCTP_STATE_COOKIE);
459 }
460 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
461 src, dst, sh, op_err,
462#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
463 mflowtype, mflowid,
464#endif
465 vrf_id, net->port);
466 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
467 return (-3);
468 }
469 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
470 asoc->peer_supports_nat = (uint8_t)nat_friendly;
471 /* process the peer's parameters in the INIT-ACK */
472 if (sctp_process_init((struct sctp_init_chunk *)cp, stcb) < 0) {
473 if (op_err != NULL) {
474 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
475 }
476 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
477 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_process_init() failed\n");
478 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
479 src, dst, sh, op_err,
480#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
481 mflowtype, mflowid,
482#endif
483 vrf_id, net->port);
484 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
485 return (-1);
486 }
487 initack_limit = offset + ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length);
488 /* load all addresses */
489 if ((retval = sctp_load_addresses_from_init(stcb, m,
490 offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
491 initack_limit, src, dst, NULL, stcb->asoc.port)) < 0) {
492 if (op_err != NULL) {
493 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
494 }
495 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
496 "Problem with address parameters");
497 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
498 "Load addresses from INIT causes an abort %d\n",
499 retval);
500 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
501 src, dst, sh, op_err,
502#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
503 mflowtype, mflowid,
504#endif
505 vrf_id, net->port);
506 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
507 return (-1);
508 }
509 /* if the peer doesn't support asconf, flush the asconf queue */
510 if (asoc->asconf_supported == 0) {
511 struct sctp_asconf_addr *param, *nparam;
512
513 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(param, &asoc->asconf_queue, next, nparam) {
514 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_queue, param, next);
515 SCTP_FREE(param, SCTP_M_ASC_ADDR);
516 }
517 }
518
519 stcb->asoc.peer_hmac_id = sctp_negotiate_hmacid(stcb->asoc.peer_hmacs,
520 stcb->asoc.local_hmacs);
521 if (op_err) {
522 sctp_queue_op_err(stcb, op_err);
523 /* queuing will steal away the mbuf chain to the out queue */
524 op_err = NULL;
525 }
526 /* extract the cookie and queue it to "echo" it back... */
527 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_THRESHOLD_LOGGING) {
528 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_THRESHOLD_CLEAR,
529 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count,
530 0,
531 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT,
532 __LINE__);
533 }
534 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count = 0;
535 net->error_count = 0;
536
537 /*
538 * Cancel the INIT timer, We do this first before queueing the
539 * cookie. We always cancel at the primary to assue that we are
540 * canceling the timer started by the INIT which always goes to the
541 * primary.
542 */
543 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
544 asoc->primary_destination, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_3);
545
546 /* calculate the RTO */
547 sctp_calculate_rto(stcb, asoc, net, &asoc->time_entered,
548 SCTP_RTT_FROM_NON_DATA);
549#if defined(__Userspace__)
550 if (stcb->sctp_ep->recv_callback) {
551 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
552 uint32_t inqueue_bytes, sb_free_now;
553 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
554
555 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
556 inqueue_bytes = stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue * sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk));
557 sb_free_now = SCTP_SB_LIMIT_SND(stcb->sctp_socket) - (inqueue_bytes + stcb->asoc.sb_send_resv);
558
559 /* check if the amount free in the send socket buffer crossed the threshold */
560 if (inp->send_callback &&
561 (((inp->send_sb_threshold > 0) &&
562 (sb_free_now >= inp->send_sb_threshold) &&
563 (stcb->asoc.chunks_on_out_queue <= SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_max_chunks_on_queue))) ||
564 (inp->send_sb_threshold == 0))) {
565 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
566 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
567 inp->send_callback(stcb->sctp_socket, sb_free_now, inp->ulp_info);
568 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
569 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
570 }
571 }
572 }
573#endif
574 retval = sctp_send_cookie_echo(m, offset, initack_limit, stcb, net);
575 return (retval);
576}
577
578static void
579sctp_handle_heartbeat_ack(struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk *cp,
580 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
581{
582 union sctp_sockstore store;
583 struct sctp_nets *r_net, *f_net;
584 struct timeval tv;
585 int req_prim = 0;
586 uint16_t old_error_counter;
587
588 if (ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length) != sizeof(struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk)) {
589 /* Invalid length */
590 return;
591 }
592
593 memset(&store, 0, sizeof(store));
594 switch (cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_family) {
595#ifdef INET
596 case AF_INET:
597 if (cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len == sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
598 store.sin.sin_family = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_family;
599#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
600 store.sin.sin_len = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len;
601#endif
602 store.sin.sin_port = stcb->rport;
603 memcpy(&store.sin.sin_addr, cp->heartbeat.hb_info.address,
604 sizeof(store.sin.sin_addr));
605 } else {
606 return;
607 }
608 break;
609#endif
610#ifdef INET6
611 case AF_INET6:
612 if (cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len == sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
613 store.sin6.sin6_family = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_family;
614#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
615 store.sin6.sin6_len = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len;
616#endif
617 store.sin6.sin6_port = stcb->rport;
618 memcpy(&store.sin6.sin6_addr, cp->heartbeat.hb_info.address, sizeof(struct in6_addr));
619 } else {
620 return;
621 }
622 break;
623#endif
624#if defined(__Userspace__)
625 case AF_CONN:
626 if (cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len == sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn)) {
627 store.sconn.sconn_family = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_family;
628#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
629 store.sconn.sconn_len = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.addr_len;
630#endif
631 store.sconn.sconn_port = stcb->rport;
632 memcpy(&store.sconn.sconn_addr, cp->heartbeat.hb_info.address, sizeof(void *));
633 } else {
634 return;
635 }
636 break;
637#endif
638 default:
639 return;
640 }
641 r_net = sctp_findnet(stcb, &store.sa);
642 if (r_net == NULL) {
643 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Huh? I can't find the address I sent it to, discard\n");
644 return;
645 }
646 if ((r_net && (r_net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED)) &&
647 (r_net->heartbeat_random1 == cp->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value1) &&
648 (r_net->heartbeat_random2 == cp->heartbeat.hb_info.random_value2)) {
649 /*
650 * If the its a HB and it's random value is correct when can
651 * confirm the destination.
652 */
653 r_net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
654 if (r_net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REQ_PRIMARY) {
655 stcb->asoc.primary_destination = r_net;
656 r_net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_REQ_PRIMARY;
657 f_net = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
658 if (f_net != r_net) {
659 /* first one on the list is NOT the primary
660 * sctp_cmpaddr() is much more efficient if
661 * the primary is the first on the list, make it
662 * so.
663 */
664 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.nets, r_net, sctp_next);
665 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&stcb->asoc.nets, r_net, sctp_next);
666 }
667 req_prim = 1;
668 }
669 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED,
670 stcb, 0, (void *)r_net, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
671 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
672 r_net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_4);
673 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, r_net);
674 }
675 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_THRESHOLD_LOGGING) {
676 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_THRESHOLD_CLEAR,
677 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count,
678 0,
679 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT,
680 __LINE__);
681 }
682 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count = 0;
683 old_error_counter = r_net->error_count;
684 r_net->error_count = 0;
685 r_net->hb_responded = 1;
686 tv.tv_sec = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.time_value_1;
687 tv.tv_usec = cp->heartbeat.hb_info.time_value_2;
688 /* Now lets do a RTO with this */
689 sctp_calculate_rto(stcb, &stcb->asoc, r_net, &tv,
690 SCTP_RTT_FROM_NON_DATA);
691 if (!(r_net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE)) {
692 r_net->dest_state |= SCTP_ADDR_REACHABLE;
693 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP, stcb,
694 0, (void *)r_net, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
695 }
696 if (r_net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_PF) {
697 r_net->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_PF;
698 stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_exit_pf(stcb, net);
699 }
700 if (old_error_counter > 0) {
701 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep,
702 stcb, r_net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_5);
703 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, r_net);
704 }
705 if (r_net == stcb->asoc.primary_destination) {
706 if (stcb->asoc.alternate) {
707 /* release the alternate, primary is good */
708 sctp_free_remote_addr(stcb->asoc.alternate);
709 stcb->asoc.alternate = NULL;
710 }
711 }
712 /* Mobility adaptation */
713 if (req_prim) {
714 if ((sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
715 SCTP_MOBILITY_BASE) ||
716 sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
717 SCTP_MOBILITY_FASTHANDOFF)) &&
718 sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
719 SCTP_MOBILITY_PRIM_DELETED)) {
720 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PRIM_DELETED,
721 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
722 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_6);
723 if (sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
724 SCTP_MOBILITY_FASTHANDOFF)) {
725 sctp_assoc_immediate_retrans(stcb,
726 stcb->asoc.primary_destination);
727 }
728 if (sctp_is_mobility_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep,
729 SCTP_MOBILITY_BASE)) {
730 sctp_move_chunks_from_net(stcb,
731 stcb->asoc.deleted_primary);
732 }
733 sctp_delete_prim_timer(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb);
734 }
735 }
736}
737
738static int
739sctp_handle_nat_colliding_state(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
740{
741 /*
742 * Return 0 means we want you to proceed with the abort
743 * non-zero means no abort processing.
744 */
745 uint32_t new_vtag;
746 struct sctpasochead *head;
747
748 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
749 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
750 new_vtag = sctp_select_a_tag(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_lport, stcb->rport, 1);
751 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
752 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
753 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
754 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
755 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
756 } else {
757 return (0);
758 }
759 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) {
760 /* generate a new vtag and send init */
761 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_asocs);
762 stcb->asoc.my_vtag = new_vtag;
763 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(stcb->asoc.my_vtag, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
764 /* put it in the bucket in the vtag hash of assoc's for the system */
765 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_asocs);
766 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
767 sctp_send_initiate(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
768 return (1);
769 } else {
770 /* treat like a case where the cookie expired i.e.:
771 * - dump current cookie.
772 * - generate a new vtag.
773 * - resend init.
774 */
775 /* generate a new vtag and send init */
776 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_asocs);
777 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
778 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
779 sctp_toss_old_cookies(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
780 stcb->asoc.my_vtag = new_vtag;
781 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(stcb->asoc.my_vtag, SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
782 /* put it in the bucket in the vtag hash of assoc's for the system */
783 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_asocs);
784 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
785 sctp_send_initiate(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
786 return (1);
787 }
788 return (0);
789}

791static int
792sctp_handle_nat_missing_state(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
793 struct sctp_nets *net)
794{
795 /* return 0 means we want you to proceed with the abort
796 * non-zero means no abort processing
797 */
798 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) {
799 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "sctp_handle_nat_missing_state: Peer does not support AUTH, cannot send an asconf\n");
800 return (0);
801 }
802 sctp_asconf_send_nat_state_update(stcb, net);
803 return (1);
804}
805
806/* Returns 1 if the stcb was aborted, 0 otherwise */
807static int
808sctp_handle_abort(struct sctp_abort_chunk *abort,
809 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
810{
811#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
812 struct socket *so;
813#endif
814 uint16_t len;
815 uint16_t error;
816
817 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "sctp_handle_abort: handling ABORT\n");
818 if (stcb == NULL)
819 return (0);
820
821 len = ntohs(abort->ch.chunk_length);
822 if (len >= sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) + sizeof(struct sctp_error_cause)) {
823 /* Need to check the cause codes for our
824 * two magic nat aborts which don't kill the assoc
825 * necessarily.
826 */
827 struct sctp_error_cause *cause;
828
829 cause = (struct sctp_error_cause *)(abort + 1);
830 error = ntohs(cause->code);
831 if (error == SCTP_CAUSE_NAT_COLLIDING_STATE) {
832 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Received Colliding state, ABORT flags:%x\n",
833 abort->ch.chunk_flags);
834 if (sctp_handle_nat_colliding_state(stcb)) {
835 return (0);
836 }
837 } else if (error == SCTP_CAUSE_NAT_MISSING_STATE) {
838 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Received missing state, ABORT flags:%x\n",
839 abort->ch.chunk_flags);
840 if (sctp_handle_nat_missing_state(stcb, net)) {
841 return (0);
842 }
843 }
844 } else {
845 error = 0;
846 }
847 /* stop any receive timers */
848 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
849 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_7);
850 /* notify user of the abort and clean up... */
851 sctp_abort_notification(stcb, 1, error, abort, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
852 /* free the tcb */
853 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
854 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
855 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
856 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
857 }
858#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
859 sctp_print_out_track_log(stcb);
860#endif
861#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
862 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
863 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
864 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
865 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
866 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
867 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
868#endif
869 (void)sctp_free_assoc(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
870 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_8);
871#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
872 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
873#endif
874 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "sctp_handle_abort: finished\n");
875 return (1);
876}
877
878static void
879sctp_start_net_timers(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
880{
881 uint32_t cnt_hb_sent;
882 struct sctp_nets *net;
883
884 cnt_hb_sent = 0;
885 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
886 /* For each network start:
887 * 1) A pmtu timer.
888 * 2) A HB timer
889 * 3) If the dest in unconfirmed send
890 * a hb as well if under max_hb_burst have
891 * been sent.
892 */
893 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
894 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
895 if ((net->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) &&
896 (cnt_hb_sent < SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_hb_maxburst))) {
897 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
898 cnt_hb_sent++;
899 }
900 }
901 if (cnt_hb_sent) {
902 sctp_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
903 SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_COOKIE_ACK,
904 SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
905 }
906}
907
908static void
909sctp_handle_shutdown(struct sctp_shutdown_chunk *cp,
910 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, int *abort_flag)
911{
912 struct sctp_association *asoc;
913 int some_on_streamwheel;
914 int old_state;
915#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
916 struct socket *so;
917#endif
918
919 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
920 "sctp_handle_shutdown: handling SHUTDOWN\n");
921 if (stcb == NULL)
922 return;
923 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
924 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
925 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
926 return;
927 }
928 if (ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length) != sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_chunk)) {
929 /* Shutdown NOT the expected size */
930 return;
931 }
932 old_state = SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb);
933 sctp_update_acked(stcb, cp, abort_flag);
934 if (*abort_flag) {
935 return;
936 }
937 if (asoc->control_pdapi) {
938 /* With a normal shutdown
939 * we assume the end of last record.
940 */
941 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
942 if (asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q) {
943 struct sctp_stream_in *strm;
944
945 strm = &asoc->strmin[asoc->control_pdapi->sinfo_stream];
946 if (asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q == SCTP_ON_UNORDERED) {
947 /* Unordered */
948 TAILQ_REMOVE(&strm->uno_inqueue, asoc->control_pdapi, next_instrm);
949 asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q = 0;
950 } else if (asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q == SCTP_ON_ORDERED) {
951 /* Ordered */
952 TAILQ_REMOVE(&strm->inqueue, asoc->control_pdapi, next_instrm);
953 asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q = 0;
954#ifdef INVARIANTS
955 } else {
956 panic("Unknown state on ctrl:%p on_strm_q:%d",
957 asoc->control_pdapi,
958 asoc->control_pdapi->on_strm_q);
959#endif
960 }
961 }
962 asoc->control_pdapi->end_added = 1;
963 asoc->control_pdapi->pdapi_aborted = 1;
964 asoc->control_pdapi = NULL;
965 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
966#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
967 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
968 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
969 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
970 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
971 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
972 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
973 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
974 /* assoc was freed while we were unlocked */
975 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
976 return;
977 }
978#endif
979 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
980 sctp_sorwakeup(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb->sctp_socket);
981 }
982#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
983 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
984#endif
985 }
986 /* goto SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED state to block new requests */
987 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
988 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
989 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) &&
990 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT)) {
991 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED);
992 /* notify upper layer that peer has initiated a shutdown */
993 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_PEER_SHUTDOWN, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
994
995 /* reset time */
996 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&asoc->time_entered);
997 }
998 }
999 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) {
1000 /*
1001 * stop the shutdown timer, since we WILL move to
1002 * SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT.
1003 */
1004 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
1005 net, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_9);
1006 }
1007 /* Now is there unsent data on a stream somewhere? */
1008 some_on_streamwheel = sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1009
1010 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) ||
1011 !TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) ||
1012 some_on_streamwheel) {
1013 /* By returning we will push more data out */
1014 return;
1015 } else {
1016 /* no outstanding data to send, so move on... */
1017 /* send SHUTDOWN-ACK */
1018 /* move to SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT state */
1019 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
1020 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
1021 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
1022 }
1023 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) {
1024 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT);
1025 sctp_stop_timers_for_shutdown(stcb);
1026 sctp_send_shutdown_ack(stcb, net);
1027 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNACK,
1028 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net);
1029 } else if (old_state == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) {
1030 sctp_send_shutdown_ack(stcb, net);
1031 }
1032 }
1033}
1034
1035static void
1036sctp_handle_shutdown_ack(struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk *cp SCTP_UNUSED,
1037 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
1038 struct sctp_nets *net)
1039{
1040 struct sctp_association *asoc;
1041#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1042 struct socket *so;
1043
1044 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
1045#endif
1046 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1047 "sctp_handle_shutdown_ack: handling SHUTDOWN ACK\n");
1048 if (stcb == NULL)
1049 return;
1050
1051 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
1052 /* process according to association state */
1053 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
1054 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
1055 /* unexpected SHUTDOWN-ACK... do OOTB handling... */
1056 sctp_send_shutdown_complete(stcb, net, 1);
1057 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1058 return;
1059 }
1060 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) &&
1061 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
1062 /* unexpected SHUTDOWN-ACK... so ignore... */
1063 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1064 return;
1065 }
1066 if (asoc->control_pdapi) {
1067 /* With a normal shutdown
1068 * we assume the end of last record.
1069 */
1070 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
1071 asoc->control_pdapi->end_added = 1;
1072 asoc->control_pdapi->pdapi_aborted = 1;
1073 asoc->control_pdapi = NULL;
1074 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
1075#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1076 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1077 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1078 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
1079 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1080 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1081 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
1082 /* assoc was freed while we were unlocked */
1083 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1084 return;
1085 }
1086#endif
1087 sctp_sorwakeup(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb->sctp_socket);
1088#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1089 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1090#endif
1091 }
1092#ifdef INVARIANTS
1093 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->send_queue) ||
1094 !TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->sent_queue) ||
1095 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED)) {
1096 panic("Queues are not empty when handling SHUTDOWN-ACK");
1097 }
1098#endif
1099 /* stop the timer */
1100 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
1101 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_10);
1102 /* send SHUTDOWN-COMPLETE */
1103 sctp_send_shutdown_complete(stcb, net, 0);
1104 /* notify upper layer protocol */
1105 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
1106 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
1107 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
1108 stcb->sctp_socket->so_snd.sb_cc = 0;
1109 }
1110 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_DOWN, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1111 }
1112 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_shutdown);
1113 /* free the TCB but first save off the ep */
1114#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1115 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1116 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1117 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
1118 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1119 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1120#endif
1121 (void)sctp_free_assoc(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
1122 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_11);
1123#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1124 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1125#endif
1126}
1127
1128static void
1129sctp_process_unrecog_chunk(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint8_t chunk_type)
1130{
1131 switch (chunk_type) {
1132 case SCTP_ASCONF_ACK:
1133 case SCTP_ASCONF:
1134 sctp_asconf_cleanup(stcb);
1135 break;
1136 case SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN:
1137 case SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN:
1138 stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported = 0;
1139 break;
1140 default:
1141 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1142 "Peer does not support chunk type %d (0x%x).\n",
1143 chunk_type, chunk_type);
1144 break;
1145 }
1146}
1147
1148/*
1149 * Skip past the param header and then we will find the param that caused the
1150 * problem. There are a number of param's in a ASCONF OR the prsctp param
1151 * these will turn of specific features.
1152 * XXX: Is this the right thing to do?
1153 */
1154static void
1155sctp_process_unrecog_param(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint16_t parameter_type)
1156{
1157 switch (parameter_type) {
1158 /* pr-sctp draft */
1159 case SCTP_PRSCTP_SUPPORTED:
1160 stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported = 0;
1161 break;
1162 case SCTP_SUPPORTED_CHUNK_EXT:
1163 break;
1164 /* draft-ietf-tsvwg-addip-sctp */
1165 case SCTP_HAS_NAT_SUPPORT:
1166 stcb->asoc.peer_supports_nat = 0;
1167 break;
1168 case SCTP_ADD_IP_ADDRESS:
1169 case SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS:
1170 case SCTP_SET_PRIM_ADDR:
1171 stcb->asoc.asconf_supported = 0;
1172 break;
1173 case SCTP_SUCCESS_REPORT:
1174 case SCTP_ERROR_CAUSE_IND:
1175 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Huh, the peer does not support success? or error cause?\n");
1176 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1177 "Turning off ASCONF to this strange peer\n");
1178 stcb->asoc.asconf_supported = 0;
1179 break;
1180 default:
1181 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1182 "Peer does not support param type %d (0x%x)??\n",
1183 parameter_type, parameter_type);
1184 break;
1185 }
1186}
1187
1188static int
1189sctp_handle_error(struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch,
1190 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, uint32_t limit)
1191{
1192 struct sctp_error_cause *cause;
1193 struct sctp_association *asoc;
1194 uint32_t remaining_length, adjust;
1195 uint16_t code, cause_code, cause_length;
1196#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1197 struct socket *so;
1198#endif
1199
1200 /* parse through all of the errors and process */
1201 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
1202 cause = (struct sctp_error_cause *)((caddr_t)ch +
1203 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr));
1204 remaining_length = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
1205 if (remaining_length > limit) {
1206 remaining_length = limit;
1207 }
1208 if (remaining_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr)) {
1209 remaining_length -= sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
1210 } else {
1211 remaining_length = 0;
1212 }
1213 code = 0;
1214 while (remaining_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_error_cause)) {
1215 /* Process an Error Cause */
1216 cause_code = ntohs(cause->code);
1217 cause_length = ntohs(cause->length);
1218 if ((cause_length > remaining_length) || (cause_length == 0)) {
1219 /* Invalid cause length, possibly due to truncation. */
1220 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Bogus length in cause - bytes left: %u cause length: %u\n",
1221 remaining_length, cause_length);
1222 return (0);
1223 }
1224 if (code == 0) {
1225 /* report the first error cause */
1226 code = cause_code;
1227 }
1228 switch (cause_code) {
1229 case SCTP_CAUSE_INVALID_STREAM:
1230 case SCTP_CAUSE_MISSING_PARAM:
1231 case SCTP_CAUSE_INVALID_PARAM:
1232 case SCTP_CAUSE_NO_USER_DATA:
1233 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Software error we got a %u back? We have a bug :/ (or do they?)\n",
1234 cause_code);
1235 break;
1236 case SCTP_CAUSE_NAT_COLLIDING_STATE:
1237 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Received Colliding state, ERROR flags: %x\n",
1238 ch->chunk_flags);
1239 if (sctp_handle_nat_colliding_state(stcb)) {
1240 return (0);
1241 }
1242 break;
1243 case SCTP_CAUSE_NAT_MISSING_STATE:
1244 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Received missing state, ERROR flags: %x\n",
1245 ch->chunk_flags);
1246 if (sctp_handle_nat_missing_state(stcb, net)) {
1247 return (0);
1248 }
1249 break;
1250 case SCTP_CAUSE_STALE_COOKIE:
1251 /*
1252 * We only act if we have echoed a cookie and are
1253 * waiting.
1254 */
1255 if ((cause_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_error_stale_cookie)) &&
1256 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
1257 struct sctp_error_stale_cookie *stale_cookie;
1258
1259 stale_cookie = (struct sctp_error_stale_cookie *)cause;
1260 /* stable_time is in usec, convert to msec. */
1261 asoc->cookie_preserve_req = ntohl(stale_cookie->stale_time) / 1000;
1262 /* Double it to be more robust on RTX. */
1263 asoc->cookie_preserve_req *= 2;
1264 asoc->stale_cookie_count++;
1265 if (asoc->stale_cookie_count >
1266 asoc->max_init_times) {
1267 sctp_abort_notification(stcb, 0, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1268 /* now free the asoc */
1269#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1270 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
1271 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1272 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1273 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
1274 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1275 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1276#endif
1277 (void)sctp_free_assoc(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
1278 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_12);
1279#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1280 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1281#endif
1282 return (-1);
1283 }
1284 /* blast back to INIT state */
1285 sctp_toss_old_cookies(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
1286 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT);
1287 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
1288 sctp_send_initiate(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1289 }
1290 break;
1291 case SCTP_CAUSE_UNRESOLVABLE_ADDR:
1292 /*
1293 * Nothing we can do here, we don't do hostname
1294 * addresses so if the peer does not like my IPv6
1295 * (or IPv4 for that matter) it does not matter. If
1296 * they don't support that type of address, they can
1297 * NOT possibly get that packet type... i.e. with no
1298 * IPv6 you can't receive a IPv6 packet. so we can
1299 * safely ignore this one. If we ever added support
1300 * for HOSTNAME Addresses, then we would need to do
1301 * something here.
1302 */
1303 break;
1304 case SCTP_CAUSE_UNRECOG_CHUNK:
1305 if (cause_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_error_unrecognized_chunk)) {
1306 struct sctp_error_unrecognized_chunk *unrec_chunk;
1307
1308 unrec_chunk = (struct sctp_error_unrecognized_chunk *)cause;
1309 sctp_process_unrecog_chunk(stcb, unrec_chunk->ch.chunk_type);
1310 }
1311 break;
1312 case SCTP_CAUSE_UNRECOG_PARAM:
1313 /* XXX: We only consider the first parameter */
1314 if (cause_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_error_cause) + sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
1315 struct sctp_paramhdr *unrec_parameter;
1316
1317 unrec_parameter = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)(cause + 1);
1318 sctp_process_unrecog_param(stcb, ntohs(unrec_parameter->param_type));
1319 }
1320 break;
1321 case SCTP_CAUSE_COOKIE_IN_SHUTDOWN:
1322 /*
1323 * We ignore this since the timer will drive out a
1324 * new cookie anyway and there timer will drive us
1325 * to send a SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE. We can't send one
1326 * here since we don't have their tag.
1327 */
1328 break;
1329 case SCTP_CAUSE_DELETING_LAST_ADDR:
1330 case SCTP_CAUSE_RESOURCE_SHORTAGE:
1331 case SCTP_CAUSE_DELETING_SRC_ADDR:
1332 /*
1333 * We should NOT get these here, but in a
1334 * ASCONF-ACK.
1335 */
1336 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "Peer sends ASCONF errors in a error cause with code %u.\n",
1337 cause_code);
1338 break;
1339 case SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC:
1340 /*
1341 * And what, pray tell do we do with the fact that
1342 * the peer is out of resources? Not really sure we
1343 * could do anything but abort. I suspect this
1344 * should have came WITH an abort instead of in a
1345 * OP-ERROR.
1346 */
1347 break;
1348 default:
1349 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_handle_error: unknown code 0x%x\n",
1350 cause_code);
1351 break;
1352 }
1353 adjust = SCTP_SIZE32(cause_length);
1354 if (remaining_length >= adjust) {
1355 remaining_length -= adjust;
1356 } else {
1357 remaining_length = 0;
1358 }
1359 cause = (struct sctp_error_cause *)((caddr_t)cause + adjust);
1360 }
1361 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_REMOTE_ERROR, stcb, code, ch, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1362 return (0);
1363}
1364
1365static int
1366sctp_handle_init_ack(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
1367 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst, struct sctphdr *sh,
1368 struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *cp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
1369 struct sctp_nets *net, int *abort_no_unlock,
1370#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1371 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
1372#endif
1373 uint32_t vrf_id)
1374{
1375 struct sctp_init_ack *init_ack;
1376 struct mbuf *op_err;
1377
1378 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1379 "sctp_handle_init_ack: handling INIT-ACK\n");
1380
1381 if (stcb == NULL) {
1382 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
1383 "sctp_handle_init_ack: TCB is null\n");
1384 return (-1);
1385 }
1386 init_ack = &cp->init;
1387 /* Validate parameters. */
1388 if ((ntohl(init_ack->initiate_tag) == 0) ||
1389 (ntohl(init_ack->a_rwnd) < SCTP_MIN_RWND) ||
1390 (ntohs(init_ack->num_inbound_streams) == 0) ||
1391 (ntohs(init_ack->num_outbound_streams) == 0)) {
1392 /* protocol error... send an abort */
1393 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_INVALID_PARAM, "");
1394 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
1395 src, dst, sh, op_err,
1396#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1397 mflowtype, mflowid,
1398#endif
1399 vrf_id, net->port);
1400 *abort_no_unlock = 1;
1401 return (-1);
1402 }
1403 /* process according to association state... */
1404 switch (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb)) {
1405 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT:
1406 /* this is the expected state for this chunk */
1407 /* process the INIT-ACK parameters */
1408 if (stcb->asoc.primary_destination->dest_state &
1409 SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
1410 /*
1411 * The primary is where we sent the INIT, we can
1412 * always consider it confirmed when the INIT-ACK is
1413 * returned. Do this before we load addresses
1414 * though.
1415 */
1416 stcb->asoc.primary_destination->dest_state &=
1417 ~SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
1418 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED,
1419 stcb, 0, (void *)stcb->asoc.primary_destination, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1420 }
1421 if (sctp_process_init_ack(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst, sh, cp, stcb,
1422 net, abort_no_unlock,
1423#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1424 mflowtype, mflowid,
1425#endif
1426 vrf_id) < 0) {
1427 /* error in parsing parameters */
1428 return (-1);
1429 }
1430 /* update our state */
1431 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "moving to COOKIE-ECHOED state\n");
1432 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED);
1433
1434 /* reset the RTO calc */
1435 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_THRESHOLD_LOGGING) {
1436 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_THRESHOLD_CLEAR,
1437 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count,
1438 0,
1439 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT,
1440 __LINE__);
1441 }
1442 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count = 0;
1443 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&stcb->asoc.time_entered);
1444 /*
1445 * collapse the init timer back in case of a exponential
1446 * backoff
1447 */
1448 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE, stcb->sctp_ep,
1449 stcb, net);
1450 /*
1451 * the send at the end of the inbound data processing will
1452 * cause the cookie to be sent
1453 */
1454 break;
1455 case SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT:
1456 /* incorrect state... discard */
1457 break;
1458 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED:
1459 /* incorrect state... discard */
1460 break;
1461 case SCTP_STATE_OPEN:
1462 /* incorrect state... discard */
1463 break;
1464 case SCTP_STATE_EMPTY:
1465 case SCTP_STATE_INUSE:
1466 default:
1467 /* incorrect state... discard */
1468 return (-1);
1469 break;
1470 }
1471 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Leaving handle-init-ack end\n");
1472 return (0);
1473}
1474
1475static struct sctp_tcb *
1476sctp_process_cookie_new(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
1477 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
1478 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_state_cookie *cookie, int cookie_len,
1479 struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_nets **netp,
1480 struct sockaddr *init_src, int *notification,
1481 int auth_skipped, uint32_t auth_offset, uint32_t auth_len,
1482#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1483 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
1484#endif
1485 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port);
1486
1487/*
1488 * handle a state cookie for an existing association m: input packet mbuf
1489 * chain-- assumes a pullup on IP/SCTP/COOKIE-ECHO chunk note: this is a
1490 * "split" mbuf and the cookie signature does not exist offset: offset into
1491 * mbuf to the cookie-echo chunk
1492 */
1493static struct sctp_tcb *
1494sctp_process_cookie_existing(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
1495 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
1496 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_state_cookie *cookie, int cookie_len,
1497 struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets **netp,
1498 struct sockaddr *init_src, int *notification,
1499 int auth_skipped, uint32_t auth_offset, uint32_t auth_len,
1500#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1501 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
1502#endif
1503 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
1504{
1505 struct sctp_association *asoc;
1506 struct sctp_init_chunk *init_cp, init_buf;
1507 struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *initack_cp, initack_buf;
1508 struct sctp_asconf_addr *aparam, *naparam;
1509 struct sctp_asconf_ack *aack, *naack;
1510 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
1511 struct sctp_stream_reset_list *strrst, *nstrrst;
1512 struct sctp_queued_to_read *sq, *nsq;
1513 struct sctp_nets *net;
1514 struct mbuf *op_err;
1515 struct timeval old;
1516 int init_offset, initack_offset, i;
1517 int retval;
1518 int spec_flag = 0;
1519 uint32_t how_indx;
1520#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
1521 int j;
1522#endif
1523
1524 net = *netp;
1525 /* I know that the TCB is non-NULL from the caller */
1526 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
1527 for (how_indx = 0; how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how); how_indx++) {
1528 if (asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] == 0)
1529 break;
1530 }
1531 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how)) {
1532 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 1;
1533 }
1534 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) {
1535 /* SHUTDOWN came in after sending INIT-ACK */
1536 sctp_send_shutdown_ack(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination);
1537 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_COOKIE_IN_SHUTDOWN, "");
1538 sctp_send_operr_to(src, dst, sh, cookie->peers_vtag, op_err,
1539#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1540 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
1541#endif
1542 vrf_id, net->port);
1543 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1544 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 2;
1545 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1546 return (NULL);
1547 }
1548 /*
1549 * find and validate the INIT chunk in the cookie (peer's info) the
1550 * INIT should start after the cookie-echo header struct (chunk
1551 * header, state cookie header struct)
1552 */
1553 init_offset = offset += sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_echo_chunk);
1554
1555 init_cp = (struct sctp_init_chunk *)
1556 sctp_m_getptr(m, init_offset, sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
1557 (uint8_t *) & init_buf);
1558 if (init_cp == NULL) {
1559 /* could not pull a INIT chunk in cookie */
1560 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1561 return (NULL);
1562 }
1563 if (init_cp->ch.chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) {
1564 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1565 return (NULL);
1566 }
1567 /*
1568 * find and validate the INIT-ACK chunk in the cookie (my info) the
1569 * INIT-ACK follows the INIT chunk
1570 */
1571 initack_offset = init_offset + SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(init_cp->ch.chunk_length));
1572 initack_cp = (struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *)
1573 sctp_m_getptr(m, initack_offset, sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk),
1574 (uint8_t *) & initack_buf);
1575 if (initack_cp == NULL) {
1576 /* could not pull INIT-ACK chunk in cookie */
1577 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1578 return (NULL);
1579 }
1580 if (initack_cp->ch.chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION_ACK) {
1581 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1582 return (NULL);
1583 }
1584 if ((ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag) == asoc->my_vtag) &&
1585 (ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) == asoc->peer_vtag)) {
1586 /*
1587 * case D in Section 5.2.4 Table 2: MMAA process accordingly
1588 * to get into the OPEN state
1589 */
1590 if (ntohl(initack_cp->init.initial_tsn) != asoc->init_seq_number) {
1591 /*-
1592 * Opps, this means that we somehow generated two vtag's
1593 * the same. I.e. we did:
1594 * Us Peer
1595 * <---INIT(tag=a)------
1596 * ----INIT-ACK(tag=t)-->
1597 * ----INIT(tag=t)------> *1
1598 * <---INIT-ACK(tag=a)---
1599 * <----CE(tag=t)------------- *2
1600 *
1601 * At point *1 we should be generating a different
1602 * tag t'. Which means we would throw away the CE and send
1603 * ours instead. Basically this is case C (throw away side).
1604 */
1605 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1606 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 17;
1607 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1608 return (NULL);
1609 }
1610 switch (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb)) {
1611 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT:
1612 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED:
1613 /*
1614 * INIT was sent but got a COOKIE_ECHO with the
1615 * correct tags... just accept it...but we must
1616 * process the init so that we can make sure we
1617 * have the right seq no's.
1618 */
1619 /* First we must process the INIT !! */
1620 if (sctp_process_init(init_cp, stcb) < 0) {
1621 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1622 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 3;
1623 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
1624 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_process_init() failed\n");
1625 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
1626 src, dst, sh, op_err,
1627#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1628 mflowtype, mflowid,
1629#endif
1630 vrf_id, net->port);
1631 return (NULL);
1632 }
1633 /* we have already processed the INIT so no problem */
1634 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, inp,
1635 stcb, net,
1636 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_13);
1637 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT, inp,
1638 stcb, net,
1639 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_14);
1640 /* update current state */
1641 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)
1642 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_activeestab);
1643 else
1644 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_collisionestab);
1645
1646 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
1647 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) {
1648 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD,
1649 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
1650 }
1651 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
1652 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
1653 if (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
1654 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) &&
1655 (!SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp))) {
1656#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1657 struct socket *so;
1658#endif
1659 /*
1660 * Here is where collision would go if we
1661 * did a connect() and instead got a
1662 * init/init-ack/cookie done before the
1663 * init-ack came back..
1664 */
1665 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |=
1666 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
1667#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1668 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
1669 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1670 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1671 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
1672 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1673 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
1674 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
1675 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1676 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1677 return (NULL);
1678 }
1679#endif
1680 soisconnected(stcb->sctp_socket);
1681#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1682 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1683#endif
1684 }
1685 /* notify upper layer */
1686 *notification = SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_UP;
1687 /*
1688 * since we did not send a HB make sure we
1689 * don't double things
1690 */
1691 old.tv_sec = cookie->time_entered.tv_sec;
1692 old.tv_usec = cookie->time_entered.tv_usec;
1693 net->hb_responded = 1;
1694 sctp_calculate_rto(stcb, asoc, net, &old,
1695 SCTP_RTT_FROM_NON_DATA);
1696
1697 if (stcb->asoc.sctp_autoclose_ticks &&
1698 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTOCLOSE))) {
1699 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE,
1700 inp, stcb, NULL);
1701 }
1702 break;
1703 default:
1704 /*
1705 * we're in the OPEN state (or beyond), so
1706 * peer must have simply lost the COOKIE-ACK
1707 */
1708 break;
1709 } /* end switch */
1710 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
1711 if ((retval = sctp_load_addresses_from_init(stcb, m,
1712 init_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
1713 initack_offset, src, dst, init_src, stcb->asoc.port)) < 0) {
1714 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1715 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 4;
1716 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
1717 "Problem with address parameters");
1718 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
1719 "Load addresses from INIT causes an abort %d\n",
1720 retval);
1721 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
1722 src, dst, sh, op_err,
1723#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1724 mflowtype, mflowid,
1725#endif
1726 vrf_id, net->port);
1727 return (NULL);
1728 }
1729 /* respond with a COOKIE-ACK */
1730 sctp_toss_old_cookies(stcb, asoc);
1731 sctp_send_cookie_ack(stcb);
1732 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1733 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 5;
1734 return (stcb);
1735 }
1736
1737 if (ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->my_vtag &&
1738 ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) == asoc->peer_vtag &&
1739 cookie->tie_tag_my_vtag == 0 &&
1740 cookie->tie_tag_peer_vtag == 0) {
1741 /*
1742 * case C in Section 5.2.4 Table 2: XMOO silently discard
1743 */
1744 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1745 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 6;
1746 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1747 return (NULL);
1748 }
1749 /* If nat support, and the below and stcb is established,
1750 * send back a ABORT(colliding state) if we are established.
1751 */
1752 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) &&
1753 (asoc->peer_supports_nat) &&
1754 ((ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag) == asoc->my_vtag) &&
1755 ((ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->peer_vtag) ||
1756 (asoc->peer_vtag == 0)))) {
1757 /* Special case - Peer's support nat. We may have
1758 * two init's that we gave out the same tag on since
1759 * one was not established.. i.e. we get INIT from host-1
1760 * behind the nat and we respond tag-a, we get a INIT from
1761 * host-2 behind the nat and we get tag-a again. Then we
1762 * bring up host-1 (or 2's) assoc, Then comes the cookie
1763 * from hsot-2 (or 1). Now we have colliding state. We must
1764 * send an abort here with colliding state indication.
1765 */
1766 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_NAT_COLLIDING_STATE, "");
1767 sctp_send_abort(m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, 0, op_err,
1768#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1769 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
1770#endif
1771 vrf_id, port);
1772 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1773 return (NULL);
1774 }
1775 if ((ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag) == asoc->my_vtag) &&
1776 ((ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->peer_vtag) ||
1777 (asoc->peer_vtag == 0))) {
1778 /*
1779 * case B in Section 5.2.4 Table 2: MXAA or MOAA my info
1780 * should be ok, re-accept peer info
1781 */
1782 if (ntohl(initack_cp->init.initial_tsn) != asoc->init_seq_number) {
1783 /* Extension of case C.
1784 * If we hit this, then the random number
1785 * generator returned the same vtag when we
1786 * first sent our INIT-ACK and when we later sent
1787 * our INIT. The side with the seq numbers that are
1788 * different will be the one that normnally would
1789 * have hit case C. This in effect "extends" our vtags
1790 * in this collision case to be 64 bits. The same collision
1791 * could occur aka you get both vtag and seq number the
1792 * same twice in a row.. but is much less likely. If it
1793 * did happen then we would proceed through and bring
1794 * up the assoc.. we may end up with the wrong stream
1795 * setup however.. which would be bad.. but there is
1796 * no way to tell.. until we send on a stream that does
1797 * not exist :-)
1798 */
1799 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1800 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 7;
1801
1802 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1803 return (NULL);
1804 }
1805 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1806 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 8;
1807 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, inp, stcb, net,
1808 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_15);
1809 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
1810 /*
1811 * since we did not send a HB make sure we don't double
1812 * things
1813 */
1814 net->hb_responded = 1;
1815 if (stcb->asoc.sctp_autoclose_ticks &&
1816 sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTOCLOSE)) {
1817 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE, inp, stcb,
1818 NULL);
1819 }
1820 asoc->my_rwnd = ntohl(initack_cp->init.a_rwnd);
1821 if (asoc->pre_open_streams < asoc->streamoutcnt) {
1822 asoc->pre_open_streams = asoc->streamoutcnt;
1823 }
1824
1825 if (ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->peer_vtag) {
1826 /* Ok the peer probably discarded our
1827 * data (if we echoed a cookie+data). So anything
1828 * on the sent_queue should be marked for
1829 * retransmit, we may not get something to
1830 * kick us so it COULD still take a timeout
1831 * to move these.. but it can't hurt to mark them.
1832 */
1833
1834 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
1835 if (chk->sent < SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
1836 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND;
1837 sctp_flight_size_decrease(chk);
1838 sctp_total_flight_decrease(stcb, chk);
1839 sctp_ucount_incr(stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
1840 spec_flag++;
1841 }
1842 }
1843 }
1844 /* process the INIT info (peer's info) */
1845 if (sctp_process_init(init_cp, stcb) < 0) {
1846 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1847 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 9;
1848 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
1849 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_process_init() failed\n");
1850 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
1851 src, dst, sh, op_err,
1852#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1853 mflowtype, mflowid,
1854#endif
1855 vrf_id, net->port);
1856 return (NULL);
1857 }
1858 if ((retval = sctp_load_addresses_from_init(stcb, m,
1859 init_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
1860 initack_offset, src, dst, init_src, stcb->asoc.port)) < 0) {
1861 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1862 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 10;
1863 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
1864 "Problem with address parameters");
1865 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
1866 "Load addresses from INIT causes an abort %d\n",
1867 retval);
1868 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
1869 src, dst, sh, op_err,
1870#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1871 mflowtype, mflowid,
1872#endif
1873 vrf_id, net->port);
1874 return (NULL);
1875 }
1876 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
1877 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
1878 *notification = SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_UP;
1879
1880 if (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
1881 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) &&
1882 (!SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp))) {
1883#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1884 struct socket *so;
1885#endif
1886 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
1887#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1888 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
1889 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1890 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1891 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
1892 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
1893 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
1894 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
1895 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1896 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1897 return (NULL);
1898 }
1899#endif
1900 soisconnected(stcb->sctp_socket);
1901#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1902 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
1903#endif
1904 }
1905 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)
1906 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_activeestab);
1907 else
1908 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_collisionestab);
1909 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
1910 } else if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
1911 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_restartestab);
1912 } else {
1913 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_collisionestab);
1914 }
1915 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
1916 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) {
1917 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD,
1918 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
1919 }
1920 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
1921 sctp_toss_old_cookies(stcb, asoc);
1922 sctp_send_cookie_ack(stcb);
1923 if (spec_flag) {
1924 /* only if we have retrans set do we do this. What
1925 * this call does is get only the COOKIE-ACK out
1926 * and then when we return the normal call to
1927 * sctp_chunk_output will get the retrans out
1928 * behind this.
1929 */
1930 sctp_chunk_output(inp,stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_COOKIE_ACK, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
1931 }
1932 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1933 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 11;
1934
1935 return (stcb);
1936 }
1937 if ((ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->my_vtag &&
1938 ntohl(init_cp->init.initiate_tag) != asoc->peer_vtag) &&
1939 cookie->tie_tag_my_vtag == asoc->my_vtag_nonce &&
1940 cookie->tie_tag_peer_vtag == asoc->peer_vtag_nonce &&
1941 cookie->tie_tag_peer_vtag != 0) {
1942 struct sctpasochead *head;
1943#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1944 struct socket *so;
1945#endif
1946
1947 if (asoc->peer_supports_nat) {
1948 struct sctp_tcb *local_stcb;
1949
1950 /* This is a gross gross hack.
1951 * Just call the cookie_new code since we
1952 * are allowing a duplicate association.
1953 * I hope this works...
1954 */
1955 local_stcb = sctp_process_cookie_new(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst,
1956 sh, cookie, cookie_len,
1957 inp, netp, init_src,notification,
1958 auth_skipped, auth_offset, auth_len,
1959#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
1960 mflowtype, mflowid,
1961#endif
1962 vrf_id, port);
1963 if (local_stcb == NULL) {
1964 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
1965 }
1966 return (local_stcb);
1967 }
1968 /*
1969 * case A in Section 5.2.4 Table 2: XXMM (peer restarted)
1970 */
1971 /* temp code */
1972 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
1973 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 12;
1974 sctp_stop_association_timers(stcb, false);
1975 /* notify upper layer */
1976 *notification = SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_RESTART;
1977 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
1978 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_OPEN) &&
1979 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) &&
1980 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT)) {
1981 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
1982 }
1983 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) {
1984 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_restartestab);
1985 } else if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) {
1986 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_collisionestab);
1987 }
1988 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) {
1989 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
1990 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD,
1991 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
1992
1993 } else if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) {
1994 /* move to OPEN state, if not in SHUTDOWN_SENT */
1995 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
1996 }
1997 if (asoc->pre_open_streams < asoc->streamoutcnt) {
1998 asoc->pre_open_streams = asoc->streamoutcnt;
1999 }
2000 asoc->init_seq_number = ntohl(initack_cp->init.initial_tsn);
2001 asoc->sending_seq = asoc->asconf_seq_out = asoc->str_reset_seq_out = asoc->init_seq_number;
2002 asoc->asconf_seq_out_acked = asoc->asconf_seq_out - 1;
2003 asoc->asconf_seq_in = asoc->last_acked_seq = asoc->init_seq_number - 1;
2004 asoc->str_reset_seq_in = asoc->init_seq_number;
2005 asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point = asoc->last_acked_seq;
2006 asoc->send_sack = 1;
2007 asoc->data_pkts_seen = 0;
2008 asoc->last_data_chunk_from = NULL;
2009 asoc->last_control_chunk_from = NULL;
2010 asoc->last_net_cmt_send_started = NULL;
2011 if (asoc->mapping_array) {
2012 memset(asoc->mapping_array, 0,
2013 asoc->mapping_array_size);
2014 }
2015 if (asoc->nr_mapping_array) {
2016 memset(asoc->nr_mapping_array, 0,
2017 asoc->mapping_array_size);
2018 }
2019 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2020#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2021 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
2022 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2023#endif
2024 SCTP_INP_INFO_WLOCK();
2025 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2026 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2027 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
2028 /* send up all the data */
2029 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
2030
2031 sctp_report_all_outbound(stcb, 0, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
2032 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
2033 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].chunks_on_queues = 0;
2034#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
2035 for (j = 0; j < SCTP_PR_SCTP_MAX + 1; j++) {
2036 asoc->strmout[i].abandoned_sent[j] = 0;
2037 asoc->strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[j] = 0;
2038 }
2039#else
2040 asoc->strmout[i].abandoned_sent[0] = 0;
2041 asoc->strmout[i].abandoned_unsent[0] = 0;
2042#endif
2043 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_ordered = 0;
2044 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_unordered = 0;
2045 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].sid = i;
2046 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].last_msg_incomplete = 0;
2047 }
2048 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(strrst, &asoc->resetHead, next_resp, nstrrst) {
2049 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->resetHead, strrst, next_resp);
2050 SCTP_FREE(strrst, SCTP_M_STRESET);
2051 }
2052 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sq, &asoc->pending_reply_queue, next, nsq) {
2053 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->pending_reply_queue, sq, next);
2054 if (sq->data) {
2055 sctp_m_freem(sq->data);
2056 sq->data = NULL;
2057 }
2058 sctp_free_remote_addr(sq->whoFrom);
2059 sq->whoFrom = NULL;
2060 sq->stcb = NULL;
2061 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, sq);
2062 }
2063 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
2064 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
2065 if (chk->data) {
2066 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
2067 chk->data = NULL;
2068 }
2069 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
2070 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
2071 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
2072 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
2073 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
2074 }
2075 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt = 0;
2076 asoc->str_reset = NULL;
2077 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding = 0;
2078 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->asconf_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
2079 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
2080 if (chk->data) {
2081 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
2082 chk->data = NULL;
2083 }
2084 if (chk->holds_key_ref)
2085 sctp_auth_key_release(stcb, chk->auth_keyid, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
2086 sctp_free_remote_addr(chk->whoTo);
2087 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_chunk), chk);
2088 SCTP_DECR_CHK_COUNT();
2089 }
2090 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(aparam, &asoc->asconf_queue, next, naparam) {
2091 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_queue, aparam, next);
2092 SCTP_FREE(aparam,SCTP_M_ASC_ADDR);
2093 }
2094 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(aack, &asoc->asconf_ack_sent, next, naack) {
2095 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->asconf_ack_sent, aack, next);
2096 if (aack->data != NULL) {
2097 sctp_m_freem(aack->data);
2098 }
2099 SCTP_ZONE_FREE(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_asconf_ack), aack);
2100 }
2101
2102 /* process the INIT-ACK info (my info) */
2103 asoc->my_vtag = ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag);
2104 asoc->my_rwnd = ntohl(initack_cp->init.a_rwnd);
2105
2106 /* pull from vtag hash */
2107 LIST_REMOVE(stcb, sctp_asocs);
2108 /* re-insert to new vtag position */
2109 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(stcb->asoc.my_vtag,
2110 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
2111 /*
2112 * put it in the bucket in the vtag hash of assoc's for the
2113 * system
2114 */
2115 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(head, stcb, sctp_asocs);
2116
2117 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
2118 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
2119 SCTP_INP_INFO_WUNLOCK();
2120#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2121 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2122#endif
2123 asoc->total_flight = 0;
2124 asoc->total_flight_count = 0;
2125 /* process the INIT info (peer's info) */
2126 if (sctp_process_init(init_cp, stcb) < 0) {
2127 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
2128 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 13;
2129 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
2130 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_process_init() failed\n");
2131 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
2132 src, dst, sh, op_err,
2133#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2134 mflowtype, mflowid,
2135#endif
2136 vrf_id, net->port);
2137 return (NULL);
2138 }
2139 /*
2140 * since we did not send a HB make sure we don't double
2141 * things
2142 */
2143 net->hb_responded = 1;
2144
2145 if ((retval = sctp_load_addresses_from_init(stcb, m,
2146 init_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
2147 initack_offset, src, dst, init_src, stcb->asoc.port)) < 0) {
2148 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
2149 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 14;
2150 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
2151 "Problem with address parameters");
2152 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
2153 "Load addresses from INIT causes an abort %d\n",
2154 retval);
2155 sctp_abort_association(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, m, iphlen,
2156 src, dst, sh, op_err,
2157#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2158 mflowtype, mflowid,
2159#endif
2160 vrf_id, net->port);
2161 return (NULL);
2162 }
2163 /* respond with a COOKIE-ACK */
2164 sctp_send_cookie_ack(stcb);
2165 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
2166 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 15;
2167 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTOCLOSE) &&
2168 (asoc->sctp_autoclose_ticks > 0)) {
2169 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE, inp, stcb, NULL);
2170 }
2171 return (stcb);
2172 }
2173 if (how_indx < sizeof(asoc->cookie_how))
2174 asoc->cookie_how[how_indx] = 16;
2175 /* all other cases... */
2176 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2177 return (NULL);
2178}
2179
2180/*
2181 * handle a state cookie for a new association m: input packet mbuf chain--
2182 * assumes a pullup on IP/SCTP/COOKIE-ECHO chunk note: this is a "split" mbuf
2183 * and the cookie signature does not exist offset: offset into mbuf to the
2184 * cookie-echo chunk length: length of the cookie chunk to: where the init
2185 * was from returns a new TCB
2186 */
2187static struct sctp_tcb *
2188sctp_process_cookie_new(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
2189 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
2190 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_state_cookie *cookie, int cookie_len,
2191 struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_nets **netp,
2192 struct sockaddr *init_src, int *notification,
2193 int auth_skipped, uint32_t auth_offset, uint32_t auth_len,
2194#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2195 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
2196#endif
2197 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
2198{
2199 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
2200 struct sctp_init_chunk *init_cp, init_buf;
2201 struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *initack_cp, initack_buf;
2202 union sctp_sockstore store;
2203 struct sctp_association *asoc;
2204 int init_offset, initack_offset, initack_limit;
2205 int retval;
2206 int error = 0;
2207 uint8_t auth_chunk_buf[SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE];
2208#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2209 struct socket *so;
2210
2211 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
2212#endif
2213
2214 /*
2215 * find and validate the INIT chunk in the cookie (peer's info) the
2216 * INIT should start after the cookie-echo header struct (chunk
2217 * header, state cookie header struct)
2218 */
2219 init_offset = offset + sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_echo_chunk);
2220 init_cp = (struct sctp_init_chunk *)
2221 sctp_m_getptr(m, init_offset, sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
2222 (uint8_t *) & init_buf);
2223 if (init_cp == NULL) {
2224 /* could not pull a INIT chunk in cookie */
2225 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
2226 "process_cookie_new: could not pull INIT chunk hdr\n");
2227 return (NULL);
2228 }
2229 if (init_cp->ch.chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) {
2230 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "HUH? process_cookie_new: could not find INIT chunk!\n");
2231 return (NULL);
2232 }
2233 initack_offset = init_offset + SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(init_cp->ch.chunk_length));
2234 /*
2235 * find and validate the INIT-ACK chunk in the cookie (my info) the
2236 * INIT-ACK follows the INIT chunk
2237 */
2238 initack_cp = (struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *)
2239 sctp_m_getptr(m, initack_offset, sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk),
2240 (uint8_t *) & initack_buf);
2241 if (initack_cp == NULL) {
2242 /* could not pull INIT-ACK chunk in cookie */
2243 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "process_cookie_new: could not pull INIT-ACK chunk hdr\n");
2244 return (NULL);
2245 }
2246 if (initack_cp->ch.chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION_ACK) {
2247 return (NULL);
2248 }
2249 /*
2250 * NOTE: We can't use the INIT_ACK's chk_length to determine the
2251 * "initack_limit" value. This is because the chk_length field
2252 * includes the length of the cookie, but the cookie is omitted when
2253 * the INIT and INIT_ACK are tacked onto the cookie...
2254 */
2255 initack_limit = offset + cookie_len;
2256
2257 /*
2258 * now that we know the INIT/INIT-ACK are in place, create a new TCB
2259 * and popluate
2260 */
2261
2262 /*
2263 * Here we do a trick, we set in NULL for the proc/thread argument. We
2264 * do this since in effect we only use the p argument when
2265 * the socket is unbound and we must do an implicit bind.
2266 * Since we are getting a cookie, we cannot be unbound.
2267 */
2268 stcb = sctp_aloc_assoc(inp, init_src, &error,
2269 ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag), vrf_id,
2270 ntohs(initack_cp->init.num_outbound_streams),
2271 port,
2272#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2273 (struct thread *)NULL,
2274#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2275 (PKTHREAD)NULL,
2276#else
2277 (struct proc *)NULL,
2278#endif
2279 SCTP_DONT_INITIALIZE_AUTH_PARAMS);
2280 if (stcb == NULL) {
2281 struct mbuf *op_err;
2282
2283 /* memory problem? */
2284 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
2285 "process_cookie_new: no room for another TCB!\n");
2286 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
2287 sctp_abort_association(inp, (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL, m, iphlen,
2288 src, dst, sh, op_err,
2289#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2290 mflowtype, mflowid,
2291#endif
2292 vrf_id, port);
2293 return (NULL);
2294 }
2295 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
2296 /* get scope variables out of cookie */
2297 asoc->scope.ipv4_local_scope = cookie->ipv4_scope;
2298 asoc->scope.site_scope = cookie->site_scope;
2299 asoc->scope.local_scope = cookie->local_scope;
2300 asoc->scope.loopback_scope = cookie->loopback_scope;
2301
2302#if defined(__Userspace__)
2303 if ((asoc->scope.ipv4_addr_legal != cookie->ipv4_addr_legal) ||
2304 (asoc->scope.ipv6_addr_legal != cookie->ipv6_addr_legal) ||
2305 (asoc->scope.conn_addr_legal != cookie->conn_addr_legal)) {
2306#else
2307 if ((asoc->scope.ipv4_addr_legal != cookie->ipv4_addr_legal) ||
2308 (asoc->scope.ipv6_addr_legal != cookie->ipv6_addr_legal)) {
2309#endif
2310 struct mbuf *op_err;
2311
2312 /*
2313 * Houston we have a problem. The EP changed while the
2314 * cookie was in flight. Only recourse is to abort the
2315 * association.
2316 */
2317 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
2318 sctp_abort_association(inp, (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL, m, iphlen,
2319 src, dst, sh, op_err,
2320#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2321 mflowtype, mflowid,
2322#endif
2323 vrf_id, port);
2324#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2325 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2326 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2327 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2328 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2329 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2330#endif
2331 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
2332 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_18);
2333#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2334 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2335#endif
2336 return (NULL);
2337 }
