2338 /* process the INIT-ACK info (my info) */
2339 asoc->my_vtag = ntohl(initack_cp->init.initiate_tag);
2340 asoc->my_rwnd = ntohl(initack_cp->init.a_rwnd);
2341 asoc->init_seq_number = ntohl(initack_cp->init.initial_tsn);
2342 asoc->sending_seq = asoc->asconf_seq_out = asoc->str_reset_seq_out = asoc->init_seq_number;
2343 asoc->asconf_seq_out_acked = asoc->asconf_seq_out - 1;
2344 asoc->asconf_seq_in = asoc->last_acked_seq = asoc->init_seq_number - 1;
2345 asoc->str_reset_seq_in = asoc->init_seq_number;
2346
2347 asoc->advanced_peer_ack_point = asoc->last_acked_seq;
2348
2349 /* process the INIT info (peer's info) */
2350 if (sctp_process_init(init_cp, stcb) < 0) {
2351#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2352 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2353 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2354 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2355 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2356 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2357#endif
2358 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
2359 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_19);
2360#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2361 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2362#endif
2363 return (NULL);
2364 }
2365 /* load all addresses */
2366 if ((retval = sctp_load_addresses_from_init(stcb, m,
2367 init_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk),
2368 initack_offset, src, dst, init_src, port)) < 0) {
2369#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2370 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2371 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2372 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2373 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2374 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2375#endif
2376 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
2377 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_20);
2378#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2379 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2380#endif
2381 return (NULL);
2382 }
2383 /*
2384 * verify any preceding AUTH chunk that was skipped
2385 */
2386 /* pull the local authentication parameters from the cookie/init-ack */
2387 sctp_auth_get_cookie_params(stcb, m,
2388 initack_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk),
2389 initack_limit - (initack_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk)));
2390 if (auth_skipped) {
2391 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth;
2392
2393 if (auth_len <= SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE) {
2394 auth = (struct sctp_auth_chunk *)sctp_m_getptr(m, auth_offset, auth_len, auth_chunk_buf);
2395 } else {
2396 auth = NULL;
2397 }
2398 if ((auth == NULL) || sctp_handle_auth(stcb, auth, m, auth_offset)) {
2399 /* auth HMAC failed, dump the assoc and packet */
2400 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_AUTH1,
2401 "COOKIE-ECHO: AUTH failed\n");
2402#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2403 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2404 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2405 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2406 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2407 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2408#endif
2409 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
2410 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_21);
2411#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2412 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2413#endif
2414 return (NULL);
2415 } else {
2416 /* remaining chunks checked... good to go */
2417 stcb->asoc.authenticated = 1;
2418 }
2419 }
2420
2421 /*
2422 * if we're doing ASCONFs, check to see if we have any new local
2423 * addresses that need to get added to the peer (eg. addresses
2424 * changed while cookie echo in flight). This needs to be done
2425 * after we go to the OPEN state to do the correct asconf
2426 * processing. else, make sure we have the correct addresses in our
2427 * lists
2428 */
2429
2430 /* warning, we re-use sin, sin6, sa_store here! */
2431 /* pull in local_address (our "from" address) */
2432 switch (cookie->laddr_type) {
2433#ifdef INET
2434 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
2435 /* source addr is IPv4 */
2436 memset(&store.sin, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
2437 store.sin.sin_family = AF_INET;
2438#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
2439 store.sin.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
2440#endif
2441 store.sin.sin_addr.s_addr = cookie->laddress[0];
2442 break;
2443#endif
2444#ifdef INET6
2445 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
2446 /* source addr is IPv6 */
2447 memset(&store.sin6, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
2448 store.sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
2449#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
2450 store.sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
2451#endif
2452 store.sin6.sin6_scope_id = cookie->scope_id;
2453 memcpy(&store.sin6.sin6_addr, cookie->laddress, sizeof(struct in6_addr));
2454 break;
2455#endif
2456#if defined(__Userspace__)
2457 case SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS:
2458 /* source addr is conn */
2459 memset(&store.sconn, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
2460 store.sconn.sconn_family = AF_CONN;
2461#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
2462 store.sconn.sconn_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
2463#endif
2464 memcpy(&store.sconn.sconn_addr, cookie->laddress, sizeof(void *));
2465 break;
2466#endif
2467 default:
2468#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2469 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2470 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2471 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2472 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2473 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2474#endif
2475 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
2476 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_22);
2477#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2478 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2479#endif
2480 return (NULL);
2481 }
2482
2483 /* update current state */
2484 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "moving to OPEN state\n");
2485 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
2486 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) {
2487 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD,
2488 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
2489 }
2490 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
2491 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_passiveestab);
2492 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
2493
2494 /* set up to notify upper layer */
2495 *notification = SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_UP;
2496 if (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
2497 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) &&
2498 (!SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp))) {
2499 /*
2500 * This is an endpoint that called connect() how it got a
2501 * cookie that is NEW is a bit of a mystery. It must be that
2502 * the INIT was sent, but before it got there.. a complete
2503 * INIT/INIT-ACK/COOKIE arrived. But of course then it
2504 * should have went to the other code.. not here.. oh well..
2505 * a bit of protection is worth having..
2506 */
2507 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
2508#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2509 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2510 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
2511 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
2512 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
2513 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
2514 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
2515 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2516 return (NULL);
2517 }
2518#endif
2519 soisconnected(stcb->sctp_socket);
2520#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2521 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
2522#endif
2523 } else if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
2524 (SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp))) {
2525 /*
2526 * We don't want to do anything with this one. Since it is
2527 * the listening guy. The timer will get started for
2528 * accepted connections in the caller.
2529 */
2530 ;
2531 }
2532 if (stcb->asoc.sctp_autoclose_ticks &&
2533 sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTOCLOSE)) {
2534 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE, inp, stcb, NULL);
2535 }
2536 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&stcb->asoc.time_entered);
2537 *netp = sctp_findnet(stcb, init_src);
2538 if (*netp != NULL) {
2539 struct timeval old;
2540
2541 /*
2542 * Since we did not send a HB, make sure we don't double
2543 * things.
2544 */
2545 (*netp)->hb_responded = 1;
2546 /* Calculate the RTT. */
2547 old.tv_sec = cookie->time_entered.tv_sec;
2548 old.tv_usec = cookie->time_entered.tv_usec;
2549 sctp_calculate_rto(stcb, asoc, *netp, &old, SCTP_RTT_FROM_NON_DATA);
2550 }
2551 /* respond with a COOKIE-ACK */
2552 sctp_send_cookie_ack(stcb);
2553
2554 /*
2555 * check the address lists for any ASCONFs that need to be sent
2556 * AFTER the cookie-ack is sent
2557 */
2558 sctp_check_address_list(stcb, m,
2559 initack_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk),
2560 initack_limit - (initack_offset + sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk)),
2561 &store.sa, cookie->local_scope, cookie->site_scope,
2562 cookie->ipv4_scope, cookie->loopback_scope);
2563
2564 return (stcb);
2565}
2566
2567/*
2568 * CODE LIKE THIS NEEDS TO RUN IF the peer supports the NAT extension, i.e
2569 * we NEED to make sure we are not already using the vtag. If so we
2570 * need to send back an ABORT-TRY-AGAIN-WITH-NEW-TAG No middle box bit!
2571 head = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(sctp_asochash)[SCTP_PCBHASH_ASOC(tag,
2572 SCTP_BASE_INFO(hashasocmark))];
2573 LIST_FOREACH(stcb, head, sctp_asocs) {
2574 if ((stcb->asoc.my_vtag == tag) && (stcb->rport == rport) && (inp == stcb->sctp_ep)) {
2575 -- SEND ABORT - TRY AGAIN --
2576 }
2577 }
2578*/
2579
2580/*
2581 * handles a COOKIE-ECHO message stcb: modified to either a new or left as
2582 * existing (non-NULL) TCB
2583 */
2584static struct mbuf *
2585sctp_handle_cookie_echo(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
2586 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
2587 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_cookie_echo_chunk *cp,
2588 struct sctp_inpcb **inp_p, struct sctp_tcb **stcb, struct sctp_nets **netp,
2589 int auth_skipped, uint32_t auth_offset, uint32_t auth_len,
2590 struct sctp_tcb **locked_tcb,
2591#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2592 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
2593#endif
2594 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
2595{
2596 struct sctp_state_cookie *cookie;
2597 struct sctp_tcb *l_stcb = *stcb;
2598 struct sctp_inpcb *l_inp;
2599 struct sockaddr *to;
2600 struct sctp_pcb *ep;
2601 struct mbuf *m_sig;
2602 uint8_t calc_sig[SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE], tmp_sig[SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE];
2603 uint8_t *sig;
2604#if defined(__Userspace__) && defined(FUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION)
2605 uint8_t cookie_ok = 1;
2606#else
2607 uint8_t cookie_ok = 0;
2608#endif
2609 unsigned int sig_offset, cookie_offset;
2610 unsigned int cookie_len;
2611 struct timeval now;
2612 struct timeval time_entered, time_expires;
2613 int notification = 0;
2614 struct sctp_nets *netl;
2615 int had_a_existing_tcb = 0;
2616 int send_int_conf = 0;
2617#ifdef INET
2618 struct sockaddr_in sin;
2619#endif
2620#ifdef INET6
2621 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6;
2622#endif
2623#if defined(__Userspace__)
2624 struct sockaddr_conn sconn;
2625#endif
2626
2627 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
2628 "sctp_handle_cookie: handling COOKIE-ECHO\n");
2629
2630 if (inp_p == NULL) {
2631 return (NULL);
2632 }
2633 cookie = &cp->cookie;
2634 cookie_offset = offset + sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
2635 cookie_len = ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length);
2636
2637 if (cookie_len < sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_echo_chunk) +
2638 sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk) +
2639 sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk) + SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE) {
2640 /* cookie too small */
2641 return (NULL);
2642 }
2643 if ((cookie->peerport != sh->src_port) ||
2644 (cookie->myport != sh->dest_port) ||
2645 (cookie->my_vtag != sh->v_tag)) {
2646 /*
2647 * invalid ports or bad tag. Note that we always leave the
2648 * v_tag in the header in network order and when we stored
2649 * it in the my_vtag slot we also left it in network order.
2650 * This maintains the match even though it may be in the
2651 * opposite byte order of the machine :->
2652 */
2653 return (NULL);
2654 }
2655#if defined(__Userspace__)
2656 /*
2657 * Recover the AF_CONN addresses within the cookie.
2658 * This needs to be done in the buffer provided for later processing
2659 * of the cookie and in the mbuf chain for HMAC validation.
2660 */
2661 if ((cookie->addr_type == SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS) && (src->sa_family == AF_CONN)) {
2662 struct sockaddr_conn *sconnp = (struct sockaddr_conn *)src;
2663
2664 memcpy(cookie->address, &sconnp->sconn_addr , sizeof(void *));
2665 m_copyback(m, cookie_offset + offsetof(struct sctp_state_cookie, address),
2666 (int)sizeof(void *), (caddr_t)&sconnp->sconn_addr);
2667 }
2668 if ((cookie->laddr_type == SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS) && (dst->sa_family == AF_CONN)) {
2669 struct sockaddr_conn *sconnp = (struct sockaddr_conn *)dst;
2670
2671 memcpy(cookie->laddress, &sconnp->sconn_addr , sizeof(void *));
2672 m_copyback(m, cookie_offset + offsetof(struct sctp_state_cookie, laddress),
2673 (int)sizeof(void *), (caddr_t)&sconnp->sconn_addr);
2674 }
2675#endif
2676 /*
2677 * split off the signature into its own mbuf (since it should not be
2678 * calculated in the sctp_hmac_m() call).
2679 */
2680 sig_offset = offset + cookie_len - SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE;
2681 m_sig = m_split(m, sig_offset, M_NOWAIT);
2682 if (m_sig == NULL) {
2683 /* out of memory or ?? */
2684 return (NULL);
2685 }
2686#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
2687 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
2688 sctp_log_mbc(m_sig, SCTP_MBUF_SPLIT);
2689 }
2690#endif
2691
2692 /*
2693 * compute the signature/digest for the cookie
2694 */
2695 ep = &(*inp_p)->sctp_ep;
2696 l_inp = *inp_p;
2697 if (l_stcb) {
2698 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(l_stcb);
2699 }
2700 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(l_inp);
2701 if (l_stcb) {
2702 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(l_stcb);
2703 }
2704 /* which cookie is it? */
2705 if ((cookie->time_entered.tv_sec < (long)ep->time_of_secret_change) &&
2706 (ep->current_secret_number != ep->last_secret_number)) {
2707 /* it's the old cookie */
2708 (void)sctp_hmac_m(SCTP_HMAC,
2709 (uint8_t *)ep->secret_key[(int)ep->last_secret_number],
2710 SCTP_SECRET_SIZE, m, cookie_offset, calc_sig, 0);
2711 } else {
2712 /* it's the current cookie */
2713 (void)sctp_hmac_m(SCTP_HMAC,
2714 (uint8_t *)ep->secret_key[(int)ep->current_secret_number],
2715 SCTP_SECRET_SIZE, m, cookie_offset, calc_sig, 0);
2716 }
2717 /* get the signature */
2718 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(l_inp);
2719 sig = (uint8_t *) sctp_m_getptr(m_sig, 0, SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE, (uint8_t *) & tmp_sig);
2720 if (sig == NULL) {
2721 /* couldn't find signature */
2722 sctp_m_freem(m_sig);
2723 return (NULL);
2724 }
2725 /* compare the received digest with the computed digest */
2726 if (timingsafe_bcmp(calc_sig, sig, SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE) != 0) {
2727 /* try the old cookie? */
2728 if ((cookie->time_entered.tv_sec == (long)ep->time_of_secret_change) &&
2729 (ep->current_secret_number != ep->last_secret_number)) {
2730 /* compute digest with old */
2731 (void)sctp_hmac_m(SCTP_HMAC,
2732 (uint8_t *)ep->secret_key[(int)ep->last_secret_number],
2733 SCTP_SECRET_SIZE, m, cookie_offset, calc_sig, 0);
2734 /* compare */
2735 if (timingsafe_bcmp(calc_sig, sig, SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE) == 0)
2736 cookie_ok = 1;
2737 }
2738 } else {
2739 cookie_ok = 1;
2740 }
2741
2742 /*
2743 * Now before we continue we must reconstruct our mbuf so that
2744 * normal processing of any other chunks will work.
2745 */
2746 {
2747 struct mbuf *m_at;
2748
2749 m_at = m;
2750 while (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at) != NULL) {
2751 m_at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at);
2752 }
2753 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at) = m_sig;
2754 }
2755
2756 if (cookie_ok == 0) {
2757 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "handle_cookie_echo: cookie signature validation failed!\n");
2758 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
2759 "offset = %u, cookie_offset = %u, sig_offset = %u\n",
2760 (uint32_t) offset, cookie_offset, sig_offset);
2761 return (NULL);
2762 }
2763
2764 if (sctp_ticks_to_msecs(cookie->cookie_life) > SCTP_MAX_COOKIE_LIFE) {
2765 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "handle_cookie_echo: Invalid cookie lifetime\n");
2766 return (NULL);
2767 }
2768 time_entered.tv_sec = cookie->time_entered.tv_sec;
2769 time_entered.tv_usec = cookie->time_entered.tv_usec;
2770 if ((time_entered.tv_sec < 0) ||
2771 (time_entered.tv_usec < 0) ||
2772 (time_entered.tv_usec >= 1000000)) {
2773 /* Invalid time stamp. Cookie must have been modified. */
2774 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "handle_cookie_echo: Invalid time stamp\n");
2775 return (NULL);
2776 }
2777 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
2778#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
2779 if (timercmp(&now, &time_entered, <)) {
2780#else
2781 if (timevalcmp(&now, &time_entered, <)) {
2782#endif
2783 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "handle_cookie_echo: cookie generated in the future!\n");
2784 return (NULL);
2785 }
2786 /*
2787 * Check the cookie timestamps to be sure it's not stale.
2788 * cookie_life is in ticks, so we convert to seconds.
2789 */
2790 time_expires.tv_sec = time_entered.tv_sec + sctp_ticks_to_secs(cookie->cookie_life);
2791 time_expires.tv_usec = time_entered.tv_usec;
2792#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
2793 if (timercmp(&now, &time_expires, >))
2794#else
2795 if (timevalcmp(&now, &time_expires, >))
2796#endif
2797 {
2798 /* cookie is stale! */
2799 struct mbuf *op_err;
2800 struct sctp_error_stale_cookie *cause;
2801 struct timeval diff;
2802 uint32_t staleness;
2803
2804 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_error_stale_cookie),
2805 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
2806 if (op_err == NULL) {
2807 /* FOOBAR */
2808 return (NULL);
2809 }
2810 /* Set the len */
2811 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = sizeof(struct sctp_error_stale_cookie);
2812 cause = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_error_stale_cookie *);
2813 cause->cause.code = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_STALE_COOKIE);
2814 cause->cause.length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_error_stale_cookie));
2815#if !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
2816 timersub(&now, &time_expires, &diff);
2817#else
2818 diff = now;
2819 timevalsub(&diff, &time_expires);
2820#endif
2821 if ((uint32_t)diff.tv_sec > UINT32_MAX / 1000000) {
2822 staleness = UINT32_MAX;
2823 } else {
2824 staleness = diff.tv_sec * 1000000;
2825 }
2826 if (UINT32_MAX - staleness >= (uint32_t)diff.tv_usec) {
2827 staleness += diff.tv_usec;
2828 } else {
2829 staleness = UINT32_MAX;
2830 }
2831 cause->stale_time = htonl(staleness);
2832 sctp_send_operr_to(src, dst, sh, cookie->peers_vtag, op_err,
2833#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2834 mflowtype, mflowid, l_inp->fibnum,
2835#endif
2836 vrf_id, port);
2837 return (NULL);
2838 }
2839 /*
2840 * Now we must see with the lookup address if we have an existing
2841 * asoc. This will only happen if we were in the COOKIE-WAIT state
2842 * and a INIT collided with us and somewhere the peer sent the
2843 * cookie on another address besides the single address our assoc
2844 * had for him. In this case we will have one of the tie-tags set at
2845 * least AND the address field in the cookie can be used to look it
2846 * up.
2847 */
2848 to = NULL;
2849 switch (cookie->addr_type) {
2850#ifdef INET6
2851 case SCTP_IPV6_ADDRESS:
2852 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(sin6));
2853 sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
2854#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
2855 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(sin6);
2856#endif
2857 sin6.sin6_port = sh->src_port;
2858 sin6.sin6_scope_id = cookie->scope_id;
2859 memcpy(&sin6.sin6_addr.s6_addr, cookie->address,
2860 sizeof(sin6.sin6_addr.s6_addr));
2861 to = (struct sockaddr *)&sin6;
2862 break;
2863#endif
2864#ifdef INET
2865 case SCTP_IPV4_ADDRESS:
2866 memset(&sin, 0, sizeof(sin));
2867 sin.sin_family = AF_INET;
2868#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
2869 sin.sin_len = sizeof(sin);
2870#endif
2871 sin.sin_port = sh->src_port;
2872 sin.sin_addr.s_addr = cookie->address[0];
2873 to = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
2874 break;
2875#endif
2876#if defined(__Userspace__)
2877 case SCTP_CONN_ADDRESS:
2878 memset(&sconn, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
2879 sconn.sconn_family = AF_CONN;
2880#ifdef HAVE_SCONN_LEN
2881 sconn.sconn_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
2882#endif
2883 sconn.sconn_port = sh->src_port;
2884 memcpy(&sconn.sconn_addr, cookie->address, sizeof(void *));
2885 to = (struct sockaddr *)&sconn;
2886 break;
2887#endif
2888 default:
2889 /* This should not happen */
2890 return (NULL);
2891 }
2892 if (*stcb == NULL) {
2893 /* Yep, lets check */
2894 *stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(inp_p, to, netp, dst, NULL);
2895 if (*stcb == NULL) {
2896 /*
2897 * We should have only got back the same inp. If we
2898 * got back a different ep we have a problem. The
2899 * original findep got back l_inp and now
2900 */
2901 if (l_inp != *inp_p) {
2902 SCTP_PRINTF("Bad problem find_ep got a diff inp then special_locate?\n");
2903 }
2904 } else {
2905 if (*locked_tcb == NULL) {
2906 /* In this case we found the assoc only
2907 * after we locked the create lock. This means
2908 * we are in a colliding case and we must make
2909 * sure that we unlock the tcb if its one of the
2910 * cases where we throw away the incoming packets.
2911 */
2912 *locked_tcb = *stcb;
2913
2914 /* We must also increment the inp ref count
2915 * since the ref_count flags was set when we
2916 * did not find the TCB, now we found it which
2917 * reduces the refcount.. we must raise it back
2918 * out to balance it all :-)
2919 */
2920 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF((*stcb)->sctp_ep);
2921 if ((*stcb)->sctp_ep != l_inp) {
2922 SCTP_PRINTF("Huh? ep:%p diff then l_inp:%p?\n",
2923 (void *)(*stcb)->sctp_ep, (void *)l_inp);
2924 }
2925 }
2926 }
2927 }
2928
2929 cookie_len -= SCTP_SIGNATURE_SIZE;
2930 if (*stcb == NULL) {
2931 /* this is the "normal" case... get a new TCB */
2932 *stcb = sctp_process_cookie_new(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst, sh,
2933 cookie, cookie_len, *inp_p,
2934 netp, to, &notification,
2935 auth_skipped, auth_offset, auth_len,
2936#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2937 mflowtype, mflowid,
2938#endif
2939 vrf_id, port);
2940 } else {
2941 /* this is abnormal... cookie-echo on existing TCB */
2942 had_a_existing_tcb = 1;
2943 *stcb = sctp_process_cookie_existing(m, iphlen, offset,
2944 src, dst, sh,
2945 cookie, cookie_len, *inp_p, *stcb, netp, to,
2946 &notification, auth_skipped, auth_offset, auth_len,
2947#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2948 mflowtype, mflowid,
2949#endif
2950 vrf_id, port);
2951 if (*stcb == NULL) {
2952 *locked_tcb = NULL;
2953 }
2954 }
2955
2956 if (*stcb == NULL) {
2957 /* still no TCB... must be bad cookie-echo */
2958 return (NULL);
2959 }
2960#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
2961 if (*netp != NULL) {
2962 (*netp)->flowtype = mflowtype;
2963 (*netp)->flowid = mflowid;
2964 }
2965#endif
2966 /*
2967 * Ok, we built an association so confirm the address we sent the
2968 * INIT-ACK to.
2969 */
2970 netl = sctp_findnet(*stcb, to);
2971 /*
2972 * This code should in theory NOT run but
2973 */
2974 if (netl == NULL) {
2975 /* TSNH! Huh, why do I need to add this address here? */
2976 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(*stcb, to, NULL, port,
2977 SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE, SCTP_IN_COOKIE_PROC)) {
2978 return (NULL);
2979 }
2980 netl = sctp_findnet(*stcb, to);
2981 }
2982 if (netl) {
2983 if (netl->dest_state & SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED) {
2984 netl->dest_state &= ~SCTP_ADDR_UNCONFIRMED;
2985 (void)sctp_set_primary_addr((*stcb), (struct sockaddr *)NULL,
2986 netl);
2987 send_int_conf = 1;
2988 }
2989 }
2990 sctp_start_net_timers(*stcb);
2991 if ((*inp_p)->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) {
2992 if (!had_a_existing_tcb ||
2993 (((*inp_p)->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) == 0)) {
2994 /*
2995 * If we have a NEW cookie or the connect never
2996 * reached the connected state during collision we
2997 * must do the TCP accept thing.
2998 */
2999 struct socket *so, *oso;
3000 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
3001
3002 if (notification == SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_RESTART) {
3003 /*
3004 * For a restart we will keep the same
3005 * socket, no need to do anything. I THINK!!
3006 */
3007 sctp_ulp_notify(notification, *stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3008 if (send_int_conf) {
3009 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED,
3010 (*stcb), 0, (void *)netl, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3011 }
3012 return (m);
3013 }
3014 oso = (*inp_p)->sctp_socket;
3015 atomic_add_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3016 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK((*stcb));
3017#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3018 CURVNET_SET(oso->so_vnet);
3019#endif
3020#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3021 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(oso, 1);
3022#endif
3023 so = sonewconn(oso, 0
3024#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3025 ,NULL
3026#endif
3027 );
3028#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3029 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(oso, 1);
3030#endif
3031#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3032 CURVNET_RESTORE();
3033#endif
3034 SCTP_TCB_LOCK((*stcb));
3035 atomic_subtract_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3036
3037 if (so == NULL) {
3038 struct mbuf *op_err;
3039#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3040 struct socket *pcb_so;
3041#endif
3042 /* Too many sockets */
3043 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "process_cookie_new: no room for another socket!\n");
3044 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
3045 sctp_abort_association(*inp_p, NULL, m, iphlen,
3046 src, dst, sh, op_err,
3047#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3048 mflowtype, mflowid,
3049#endif
3050 vrf_id, port);
3051#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3052 pcb_so = SCTP_INP_SO(*inp_p);
3053 atomic_add_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3054 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK((*stcb));
3055 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(pcb_so, 1);
3056 SCTP_TCB_LOCK((*stcb));
3057 atomic_subtract_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3058#endif
3059 (void)sctp_free_assoc(*inp_p, *stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
3060 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_23);
3061#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3062 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(pcb_so, 1);
3063#endif
3064 return (NULL);
3065 }
3066 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
3067 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
3068 /*
3069 * We add the unbound flag here so that
3070 * if we get an soabort() before we get the
3071 * move_pcb done, we will properly cleanup.
3072 */
3073 inp->sctp_flags = (SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE |
3074 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED |
3075 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL |
3076 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND |
3077 (SCTP_PCB_COPY_FLAGS & (*inp_p)->sctp_flags) |
3078 SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DONT_WAKE);
3079 inp->sctp_features = (*inp_p)->sctp_features;
3080 inp->sctp_mobility_features = (*inp_p)->sctp_mobility_features;
3081 inp->sctp_socket = so;
3082 inp->sctp_frag_point = (*inp_p)->sctp_frag_point;
3083 inp->max_cwnd = (*inp_p)->max_cwnd;
3084 inp->sctp_cmt_on_off = (*inp_p)->sctp_cmt_on_off;
3085 inp->ecn_supported = (*inp_p)->ecn_supported;
3086 inp->prsctp_supported = (*inp_p)->prsctp_supported;
3087 inp->auth_supported = (*inp_p)->auth_supported;
3088 inp->asconf_supported = (*inp_p)->asconf_supported;
3089 inp->reconfig_supported = (*inp_p)->reconfig_supported;
3090 inp->nrsack_supported = (*inp_p)->nrsack_supported;
3091 inp->pktdrop_supported = (*inp_p)->pktdrop_supported;
3092 inp->partial_delivery_point = (*inp_p)->partial_delivery_point;
3093 inp->sctp_context = (*inp_p)->sctp_context;
3094 inp->local_strreset_support = (*inp_p)->local_strreset_support;
3095 inp->fibnum = (*inp_p)->fibnum;
3096 inp->inp_starting_point_for_iterator = NULL;
3097#if defined(__Userspace__)
3098 inp->ulp_info = (*inp_p)->ulp_info;
3099 inp->recv_callback = (*inp_p)->recv_callback;
3100 inp->send_callback = (*inp_p)->send_callback;
3101 inp->send_sb_threshold = (*inp_p)->send_sb_threshold;
3102#endif
3103 /*
3104 * copy in the authentication parameters from the
3105 * original endpoint
3106 */
3107 if (inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs)
3108 sctp_free_hmaclist(inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs);
3109 inp->sctp_ep.local_hmacs =
3110 sctp_copy_hmaclist((*inp_p)->sctp_ep.local_hmacs);
3111 if (inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks)
3112 sctp_free_chunklist(inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
3113 inp->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks =
3114 sctp_copy_chunklist((*inp_p)->sctp_ep.local_auth_chunks);
3115
3116 /*
3117 * Now we must move it from one hash table to
3118 * another and get the tcb in the right place.
3119 */
3120
3121 /* This is where the one-2-one socket is put into
3122 * the accept state waiting for the accept!
3123 */
3124 if (*stcb) {
3125 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(*stcb, SCTP_STATE_IN_ACCEPT_QUEUE);
3126 }
3127 sctp_move_pcb_and_assoc(*inp_p, inp, *stcb);
3128
3129 atomic_add_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3130 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK((*stcb));
3131
3132#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3133 sctp_pull_off_control_to_new_inp((*inp_p), inp, *stcb,
3134 0);
3135#else
3136 sctp_pull_off_control_to_new_inp((*inp_p), inp, *stcb, M_NOWAIT);
3137#endif
3138 SCTP_TCB_LOCK((*stcb));
3139 atomic_subtract_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3140
3141 /* now we must check to see if we were aborted while
3142 * the move was going on and the lock/unlock happened.
3143 */
3144 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
3145 /* yep it was, we leave the
3146 * assoc attached to the socket since
3147 * the sctp_inpcb_free() call will send
3148 * an abort for us.
3149 */
3150 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3151 return (NULL);
3152 }
3153 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
3154 /* Switch over to the new guy */
3155 *inp_p = inp;
3156 sctp_ulp_notify(notification, *stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3157 if (send_int_conf) {
3158 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED,
3159 (*stcb), 0, (void *)netl, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3160 }
3161
3162 /* Pull it from the incomplete queue and wake the guy */
3163#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3164 atomic_add_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3165 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK((*stcb));
3166 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3167#endif
3168 soisconnected(so);
3169#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3170 SCTP_TCB_LOCK((*stcb));
3171 atomic_subtract_int(&(*stcb)->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3172 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3173#endif
3174 return (m);
3175 }
3176 }
3177 if (notification) {
3178 sctp_ulp_notify(notification, *stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3179 }
3180 if (send_int_conf) {
3181 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED,
3182 (*stcb), 0, (void *)netl, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3183 }
3184 return (m);
3185}
3186
3187static void
3188sctp_handle_cookie_ack(struct sctp_cookie_ack_chunk *cp SCTP_UNUSED,
3189 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
3190{
3191 /* cp must not be used, others call this without a c-ack :-) */
3192 struct sctp_association *asoc;
3193 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
3194
3195 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
3196 "sctp_handle_cookie_ack: handling COOKIE-ACK\n");
3197 if ((stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
3198 return;
3199 }
3200
3201 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
3202 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_THRESHOLD_LOGGING) {
3203 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_THRESHOLD_CLEAR,
3204 asoc->overall_error_count,
3205 0,
3206 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT,
3207 __LINE__);
3208 }
3209 asoc->overall_error_count = 0;
3210 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
3211 /* process according to association state */
3212 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED) {
3213 /* state change only needed when I am in right state */
3214 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "moving to OPEN state\n");
3215 SCTP_SET_STATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_OPEN);
3216 sctp_start_net_timers(stcb);
3217 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) {
3218 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD,
3219 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
3220 }
3221 /* update RTO */
3222 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_activeestab);
3223 SCTP_STAT_INCR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
3224 if (asoc->overall_error_count == 0) {
3225 sctp_calculate_rto(stcb, asoc, net, &asoc->time_entered,
3226 SCTP_RTT_FROM_NON_DATA);
3227 }
3228 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&asoc->time_entered);
3229 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_UP, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3230 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
3231 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
3232#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3233 struct socket *so;
3234
3235#endif
3236 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED;
3237#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3238 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
3239 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3240 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3241 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3242 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3243 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3244#endif
3245 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) == 0) {
3246 soisconnected(stcb->sctp_socket);
3247 }
3248#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3249 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3250#endif
3251 }
3252 /*
3253 * since we did not send a HB make sure we don't double
3254 * things
3255 */
3256 net->hb_responded = 1;
3257
3258 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
3259 /* We don't need to do the asconf thing,
3260 * nor hb or autoclose if the socket is closed.
3261 */
3262 goto closed_socket;
3263 }
3264
3265 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT, stcb->sctp_ep,
3266 stcb, net);
3267
3268 if (stcb->asoc.sctp_autoclose_ticks &&
3269 sctp_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_AUTOCLOSE)) {
3270 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE,
3271 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL);
3272 }
3273 /*
3274 * send ASCONF if parameters are pending and ASCONFs are
3275 * allowed (eg. addresses changed when init/cookie echo were
3276 * in flight)
3277 */
3278 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_DO_ASCONF)) &&
3279 (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 1) &&
3280 (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.asconf_queue))) {
3281#ifdef SCTP_TIMER_BASED_ASCONF
3282 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF,
3283 stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3284 stcb->asoc.primary_destination);
3285#else
3286 sctp_send_asconf(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3287 SCTP_ADDR_NOT_LOCKED);
3288#endif
3289 }
3290 }
3291closed_socket:
3292 /* Toss the cookie if I can */
3293 sctp_toss_old_cookies(stcb, asoc);
3294 /* Restart the timer if we have pending data */
3295 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3296 if (chk->whoTo != NULL) {
3297 break;
3298 }
3299 }
3300 if (chk != NULL) {
3301 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, chk->whoTo);
3302 }
3303}
3304
3305static void
3306sctp_handle_ecn_echo(struct sctp_ecne_chunk *cp,
3307 struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
3308{
3309 struct sctp_nets *net;
3310 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *lchk;
3311 struct sctp_ecne_chunk bkup;
3312 uint8_t override_bit;
3313 uint32_t tsn, window_data_tsn;
3314 int len;
3315 unsigned int pkt_cnt;
3316
3317 len = ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length);
3318 if ((len != sizeof(struct sctp_ecne_chunk)) &&
3319 (len != sizeof(struct old_sctp_ecne_chunk))) {
3320 return;
3321 }
3322 if (len == sizeof(struct old_sctp_ecne_chunk)) {
3323 /* Its the old format */
3324 memcpy(&bkup, cp, sizeof(struct old_sctp_ecne_chunk));
3325 bkup.num_pkts_since_cwr = htonl(1);
3326 cp = &bkup;
3327 }
3328 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvecne);
3329 tsn = ntohl(cp->tsn);
3330 pkt_cnt = ntohl(cp->num_pkts_since_cwr);
3331 lchk = TAILQ_LAST(&stcb->asoc.send_queue, sctpchunk_listhead);
3332 if (lchk == NULL) {
3333 window_data_tsn = stcb->asoc.sending_seq - 1;
3334 } else {
3335 window_data_tsn = lchk->rec.data.tsn;
3336 }
3337
3338 /* Find where it was sent to if possible. */
3339 net = NULL;
3340 TAILQ_FOREACH(lchk, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3341 if (lchk->rec.data.tsn == tsn) {
3342 net = lchk->whoTo;
3343 net->ecn_prev_cwnd = lchk->rec.data.cwnd_at_send;
3344 break;
3345 }
3346 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(lchk->rec.data.tsn, tsn)) {
3347 break;
3348 }
3349 }
3350 if (net == NULL) {
3351 /*
3352 * What to do. A previous send of a
3353 * CWR was possibly lost. See how old it is, we
3354 * may have it marked on the actual net.
3355 */
3356 TAILQ_FOREACH(net, &stcb->asoc.nets, sctp_next) {
3357 if (tsn == net->last_cwr_tsn) {
3358 /* Found him, send it off */
3359 break;
3360 }
3361 }
3362 if (net == NULL) {
3363 /*
3364 * If we reach here, we need to send a special
3365 * CWR that says hey, we did this a long time
3366 * ago and you lost the response.
3367 */
3368 net = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.nets);
3369 if (net == NULL) {
3370 /* TSNH */
3371 return;
3372 }
3373 override_bit = SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE;
3374 } else {
3375 override_bit = 0;
3376 }
3377 } else {
3378 override_bit = 0;
3379 }
3380 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(tsn, net->cwr_window_tsn) &&
3381 ((override_bit&SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE) == 0)) {
3382 /* JRS - Use the congestion control given in the pluggable CC module */
3383 stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_after_ecn_echo(stcb, net, 0, pkt_cnt);
3384 /*
3385 * We reduce once every RTT. So we will only lower cwnd at
3386 * the next sending seq i.e. the window_data_tsn
3387 */
3388 net->cwr_window_tsn = window_data_tsn;
3389 net->ecn_ce_pkt_cnt += pkt_cnt;
3390 net->lost_cnt = pkt_cnt;
3391 net->last_cwr_tsn = tsn;
3392 } else {
3393 override_bit |= SCTP_CWR_IN_SAME_WINDOW;
3394 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(tsn, net->last_cwr_tsn) &&
3395 ((override_bit&SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE) == 0)) {
3396 /*
3397 * Another loss in the same window update how
3398 * many marks/packets lost we have had.
3399 */
3400 int cnt = 1;
3401 if (pkt_cnt > net->lost_cnt) {
3402 /* Should be the case */
3403 cnt = (pkt_cnt - net->lost_cnt);
3404 net->ecn_ce_pkt_cnt += cnt;
3405 }
3406 net->lost_cnt = pkt_cnt;
3407 net->last_cwr_tsn = tsn;
3408 /*
3409 * Most CC functions will ignore this call, since we are in-window
3410 * yet of the initial CE the peer saw.
3411 */
3412 stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_after_ecn_echo(stcb, net, 1, cnt);
3413 }
3414 }
3415 /*
3416 * We always send a CWR this way if our previous one was lost our
3417 * peer will get an update, or if it is not time again to reduce we
3418 * still get the cwr to the peer. Note we set the override when we
3419 * could not find the TSN on the chunk or the destination network.
3420 */
3421 sctp_send_cwr(stcb, net, net->last_cwr_tsn, override_bit);
3422}
3423
3424static void
3425sctp_handle_ecn_cwr(struct sctp_cwr_chunk *cp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
3426{
3427 /*
3428 * Here we get a CWR from the peer. We must look in the outqueue and
3429 * make sure that we have a covered ECNE in the control chunk part.
3430 * If so remove it.
3431 */
3432 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
3433 struct sctp_ecne_chunk *ecne;
3434 int override;
3435 uint32_t cwr_tsn;
3436
3437 cwr_tsn = ntohl(cp->tsn);
3438 override = cp->ch.chunk_flags & SCTP_CWR_REDUCE_OVERRIDE;
3439 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
3440 if (chk->rec.chunk_id.id != SCTP_ECN_ECHO) {
3441 continue;
3442 }
3443 if ((override == 0) && (chk->whoTo != net)) {
3444 /* Must be from the right src unless override is set */
3445 continue;
3446 }
3447 ecne = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_ecne_chunk *);
3448 if (SCTP_TSN_GE(cwr_tsn, ntohl(ecne->tsn))) {
3449 /* this covers this ECNE, we can remove it */
3450 stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq--;
3451 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue, chk,
3452 sctp_next);
3453 stcb->asoc.ctrl_queue_cnt--;
3454 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
3455 chk->data = NULL;
3456 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3457 if (override == 0) {
3458 break;
3459 }
3460 }
3461 }
3462}

3464static void
3465sctp_handle_shutdown_complete(struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk *cp SCTP_UNUSED,
3466 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net)
3467{
3468#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3469 struct socket *so;
3470#endif
3471
3472 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
3473 "sctp_handle_shutdown_complete: handling SHUTDOWN-COMPLETE\n");
3474 if (stcb == NULL)
3475 return;
3476
3477 /* process according to association state */
3478 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) {
3479 /* unexpected SHUTDOWN-COMPLETE... so ignore... */
3480 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
3481 "sctp_handle_shutdown_complete: not in SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT --- ignore\n");
3482 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3483 return;
3484 }
3485 /* notify upper layer protocol */
3486 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
3487 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_DOWN, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3488 }
3489#ifdef INVARIANTS
3490 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.send_queue) ||
3491 !TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue) ||
3492 sctp_is_there_unsent_data(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED)) {
3493 panic("Queues are not empty when handling SHUTDOWN-COMPLETE");
3494 }
3495#endif
3496 /* stop the timer */
3497 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNACK, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, net,
3498 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_24);
3499 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_shutdown);
3500 /* free the TCB */
3501 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2,
3502 "sctp_handle_shutdown_complete: calls free-asoc\n");
3503#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3504 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
3505 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3506 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3507 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3508 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3509 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3510#endif
3511 (void)sctp_free_assoc(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
3512 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_25);
3513#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3514 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3515#endif
3516 return;
3517}
3518
3519static int
3520process_chunk_drop(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_chunk_desc *desc,
3521 struct sctp_nets *net, uint8_t flg)
3522{
3523 switch (desc->chunk_type) {
3524 case SCTP_DATA:
3525 case SCTP_IDATA:
3526 /* find the tsn to resend (possibly) */
3527 {
3528 uint32_t tsn;
3529 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *tp1;
3530
3531 tsn = ntohl(desc->tsn_ifany);
3532 TAILQ_FOREACH(tp1, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3533 if (tp1->rec.data.tsn == tsn) {
3534 /* found it */
3535 break;
3536 }
3537 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(tp1->rec.data.tsn, tsn)) {
3538 /* not found */
3539 tp1 = NULL;
3540 break;
3541 }
3542 }
3543 if (tp1 == NULL) {
3544 /*
3545 * Do it the other way , aka without paying
3546 * attention to queue seq order.
3547 */
3548 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpdnfnd);
3549 TAILQ_FOREACH(tp1, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3550 if (tp1->rec.data.tsn == tsn) {
3551 /* found it */
3552 break;
3553 }
3554 }
3555 }
3556 if (tp1 == NULL) {
3557 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrptsnnf);
3558 }
3559 if ((tp1) && (tp1->sent < SCTP_DATAGRAM_ACKED)) {
3560 if (((flg & SCTP_BADCRC) == 0) &&
3561 ((flg & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) == 0)) {
3562 return (0);
3563 }
3564 if ((stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd == 0) &&
3565 ((flg & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) == 0)) {
3566 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpdiwnp);
3567 return (0);
3568 }
3569 if (stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd == 0 &&
3570 (flg & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX)) {
3571 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpdizrw);
3572 return (0);
3573 }
3574 if ((uint32_t)SCTP_BUF_LEN(tp1->data) <
3575 SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb) + SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY) {
3576 /* Payload not matching. */
3577 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpbadd);
3578 return (-1);
3579 }
3580 if (memcmp(mtod(tp1->data, caddr_t) + SCTP_DATA_CHUNK_OVERHEAD(stcb),
3581 desc->data_bytes, SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY) != 0) {
3582 /* Payload not matching. */
3583 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpbadd);
3584 return (-1);
3585 }
3586 if (tp1->do_rtt) {
3587 /*
3588 * this guy had a RTO calculation
3589 * pending on it, cancel it
3590 */
3591 if (tp1->whoTo->rto_needed == 0) {
3592 tp1->whoTo->rto_needed = 1;
3593 }
3594 tp1->do_rtt = 0;
3595 }
3596 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpmark);
3597 if (tp1->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND)
3598 sctp_ucount_incr(stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
3599 /*
3600 * mark it as if we were doing a FR, since
3601 * we will be getting gap ack reports behind
3602 * the info from the router.
3603 */
3604 tp1->rec.data.doing_fast_retransmit = 1;
3605 /*
3606 * mark the tsn with what sequences can
3607 * cause a new FR.
3608 */
3609 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.send_queue)) {
3610 tp1->rec.data.fast_retran_tsn = stcb->asoc.sending_seq;
3611 } else {
3612 tp1->rec.data.fast_retran_tsn = (TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.send_queue))->rec.data.tsn;
3613 }
3614
3615 /* restart the timer */
3616 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, stcb->sctp_ep,
3617 stcb, tp1->whoTo,
3618 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_26);
3619 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, stcb->sctp_ep,
3620 stcb, tp1->whoTo);
3621
3622 /* fix counts and things */
3623 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_FLIGHT_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
3624 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_FLIGHT_LOG_DOWN_PDRP,
3625 tp1->whoTo->flight_size,
3626 tp1->book_size,
3627 (uint32_t)(uintptr_t)stcb,
3628 tp1->rec.data.tsn);
3629 }
3630 if (tp1->sent < SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
3631 sctp_flight_size_decrease(tp1);
3632 sctp_total_flight_decrease(stcb, tp1);
3633 }
3634 tp1->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND;
3635 } {
3636 /* audit code */
3637 unsigned int audit;
3638
3639 audit = 0;
3640 TAILQ_FOREACH(tp1, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3641 if (tp1->sent == SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND)
3642 audit++;
3643 }
3644 TAILQ_FOREACH(tp1, &stcb->asoc.control_send_queue,
3645 sctp_next) {
3646 if (tp1->sent == SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND)
3647 audit++;
3648 }
3649 if (audit != stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt) {
3650 SCTP_PRINTF("**Local Audit finds cnt:%d asoc cnt:%d\n",
3651 audit, stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
3652#ifndef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
3653 stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt = audit;
3654#endif
3655 }
3656 }
3657 }
3658 break;
3659 case SCTP_ASCONF:
3660 {
3661 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *asconf;
3662
3663 TAILQ_FOREACH(asconf, &stcb->asoc.control_send_queue,
3664 sctp_next) {
3665 if (asconf->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_ASCONF) {
3666 break;
3667 }
3668 }
3669 if (asconf) {
3670 if (asconf->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND)
3671 sctp_ucount_incr(stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
3672 asconf->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND;
3673 asconf->snd_count--;
3674 }
3675 }
3676 break;
3677 case SCTP_INITIATION:
3678 /* resend the INIT */
3679 stcb->asoc.dropped_special_cnt++;
3680 if (stcb->asoc.dropped_special_cnt < SCTP_RETRY_DROPPED_THRESH) {
3681 /*
3682 * If we can get it in, in a few attempts we do
3683 * this, otherwise we let the timer fire.
3684 */
3685 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT, stcb->sctp_ep,
3686 stcb, net,
3687 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_27);
3688 sctp_send_initiate(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3689 }
3690 break;
3691 case SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK:
3692 case SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK:
3693 /* resend the sack */
3694 sctp_send_sack(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3695 break;
3696 case SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST:
3697 /* resend a demand HB */
3698 if ((stcb->asoc.overall_error_count + 3) < stcb->asoc.max_send_times) {
3699 /* Only retransmit if we KNOW we wont destroy the tcb */
3700 sctp_send_hb(stcb, net, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3701 }
3702 break;
3703 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN:
3704 sctp_send_shutdown(stcb, net);
3705 break;
3706 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK:
3707 sctp_send_shutdown_ack(stcb, net);
3708 break;
3709 case SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO:
3710 {
3711 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *cookie;
3712
3713 cookie = NULL;
3714 TAILQ_FOREACH(cookie, &stcb->asoc.control_send_queue,
3715 sctp_next) {
3716 if (cookie->rec.chunk_id.id == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
3717 break;
3718 }
3719 }
3720 if (cookie) {
3721 if (cookie->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND)
3722 sctp_ucount_incr(stcb->asoc.sent_queue_retran_cnt);
3723 cookie->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND;
3724 sctp_stop_all_cookie_timers(stcb);
3725 }
3726 }
3727 break;
3728 case SCTP_COOKIE_ACK:
3729 sctp_send_cookie_ack(stcb);
3730 break;
3731 case SCTP_ASCONF_ACK:
3732 /* resend last asconf ack */
3733 sctp_send_asconf_ack(stcb);
3734 break;
3735 case SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN:
3736 case SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN:
3737 send_forward_tsn(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
3738 break;
3739 /* can't do anything with these */
3740 case SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED:
3741 case SCTP_INITIATION_ACK: /* this should not happen */
3742 case SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK:
3743 case SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION:
3744 case SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR:
3745 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE:
3746 case SCTP_ECN_ECHO:
3747 case SCTP_ECN_CWR:
3748 default:
3749 break;
3750 }
3751 return (0);
3752}
3753
3754void
3755sctp_reset_in_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t number_entries, uint16_t *list)
3756{
3757 uint32_t i;
3758 uint16_t temp;
3759
3760 /*
3761 * We set things to 0xffffffff since this is the last delivered sequence
3762 * and we will be sending in 0 after the reset.
3763 */
3764
3765 if (number_entries) {
3766 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
3767 temp = ntohs(list[i]);
3768 if (temp >= stcb->asoc.streamincnt) {
3769 continue;
3770 }
3771 stcb->asoc.strmin[temp].last_mid_delivered = 0xffffffff;
3772 }
3773 } else {
3774 list = NULL;
3775 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamincnt; i++) {
3776 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].last_mid_delivered = 0xffffffff;
3777 }
3778 }
3779 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_RECV, stcb, number_entries, (void *)list, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3780}
3781
3782static void
3783sctp_reset_out_streams(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t number_entries, uint16_t *list)
3784{
3785 uint32_t i;
3786 uint16_t temp;
3787
3788 if (number_entries > 0) {
3789 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
3790 temp = ntohs(list[i]);
3791 if (temp >= stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
3792 /* no such stream */
3793 continue;
3794 }
3795 stcb->asoc.strmout[temp].next_mid_ordered = 0;
3796 stcb->asoc.strmout[temp].next_mid_unordered = 0;
3797 }
3798 } else {
3799 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
3800 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_ordered = 0;
3801 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].next_mid_unordered = 0;
3802 }
3803 }
3804 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_SEND, stcb, number_entries, (void *)list, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3805}
3806
3807static void
3808sctp_reset_clear_pending(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t number_entries, uint16_t *list)
3809{
3810 uint32_t i;
3811 uint16_t temp;
3812
3813 if (number_entries > 0) {
3814 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
3815 temp = ntohs(list[i]);
3816 if (temp >= stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
3817 /* no such stream */
3818 continue;
3819 }
3820 stcb->asoc.strmout[temp].state = SCTP_STREAM_OPEN;
3821 }
3822 } else {
3823 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
3824 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_OPEN;
3825 }
3826 }
3827}
3828
3829struct sctp_stream_reset_request *
3830sctp_find_stream_reset(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t seq, struct sctp_tmit_chunk **bchk)
3831{
3832 struct sctp_association *asoc;
3833 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
3834 struct sctp_stream_reset_request *r;
3835 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
3836 int len, clen;
3837
3838 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
3839 chk = asoc->str_reset;
3840 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->control_send_queue) ||
3841 (chk == NULL)) {
3842 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding = 0;
3843 return (NULL);
3844 }
3845 if (chk->data == NULL) {
3846 return (NULL);
3847 }
3848 if (bchk != NULL) {
3849 /* he wants a copy of the chk pointer */
3850 *bchk = chk;
3851 }
3852 clen = chk->send_size;
3853 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
3854 r = (struct sctp_stream_reset_request *)(ch + 1);
3855 if (ntohl(r->request_seq) == seq) {
3856 /* found it */
3857 return (r);
3858 }
3859 len = SCTP_SIZE32(ntohs(r->ph.param_length));
3860 if (clen > (len + (int)sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr))) {
3861 /* move to the next one, there can only be a max of two */
3862 r = (struct sctp_stream_reset_request *)((caddr_t)r + len);
3863 if (ntohl(r->request_seq) == seq) {
3864 return (r);
3865 }
3866 }
3867 /* that seq is not here */
3868 return (NULL);
3869}
3870
3871static void
3872sctp_clean_up_stream_reset(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
3873{
3874 struct sctp_association *asoc;
3875 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
3876
3877 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
3878 chk = asoc->str_reset;
3879 if (chk == NULL) {
3880 return;
3881 }
3882 asoc->str_reset = NULL;
3883 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_STRRESET, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3884 NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_28);
3885 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->control_send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
3886 asoc->ctrl_queue_cnt--;
3887 if (chk->data) {
3888 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
3889 chk->data = NULL;
3890 }
3891 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3892}
3893
3894static int
3895sctp_handle_stream_reset_response(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
3896 uint32_t seq, uint32_t action,
3897 struct sctp_stream_reset_response *respin)
3898{
3899 uint16_t type;
3900 int lparam_len;
3901 struct sctp_association *asoc = &stcb->asoc;
3902 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
3903 struct sctp_stream_reset_request *req_param;
3904 struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *req_out_param;
3905 struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *req_in_param;
3906 uint32_t number_entries;
3907
3908 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding == 0) {
3909 /* duplicate */
3910 return (0);
3911 }
3912 if (seq == stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out) {
3913 req_param = sctp_find_stream_reset(stcb, seq, &chk);
3914 if (req_param != NULL) {
3915 stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out++;
3916 type = ntohs(req_param->ph.param_type);
3917 lparam_len = ntohs(req_param->ph.param_length);
3918 if (type == SCTP_STR_RESET_OUT_REQUEST) {
3919 int no_clear = 0;
3920
3921 req_out_param = (struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *)req_param;
3922 number_entries = (lparam_len - sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request)) / sizeof(uint16_t);
3923 asoc->stream_reset_out_is_outstanding = 0;
3924 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding)
3925 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding--;
3926 if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED) {
3927 /* do it */
3928 sctp_reset_out_streams(stcb, number_entries, req_out_param->list_of_streams);
3929 } else if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED) {
3930 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_DENIED_OUT, stcb, number_entries, req_out_param->list_of_streams, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3931 } else if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS) {
3932 /* Set it up so we don't stop retransmitting */
3933 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding++;
3934 stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out--;
3935 asoc->stream_reset_out_is_outstanding = 1;
3936 no_clear = 1;
3937 } else {
3938 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_FAILED_OUT, stcb, number_entries, req_out_param->list_of_streams, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3939 }
3940 if (no_clear == 0) {
3941 sctp_reset_clear_pending(stcb, number_entries, req_out_param->list_of_streams);
3942 }
3943 } else if (type == SCTP_STR_RESET_IN_REQUEST) {
3944 req_in_param = (struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *)req_param;
3945 number_entries = (lparam_len - sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request)) / sizeof(uint16_t);
3946 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding)
3947 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding--;
3948 if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED) {
3949 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_DENIED_IN, stcb,
3950 number_entries, req_in_param->list_of_streams, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3951 } else if (action != SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED) {
3952 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_FAILED_IN, stcb,
3953 number_entries, req_in_param->list_of_streams, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3954 }
3955 } else if (type == SCTP_STR_RESET_ADD_OUT_STREAMS) {
3956 /* Ok we now may have more streams */
3957 int num_stream;
3958
3959 num_stream = stcb->asoc.strm_pending_add_size;
3960 if (num_stream > (stcb->asoc.strm_realoutsize - stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt)) {
3961 /* TSNH */
3962 num_stream = stcb->asoc.strm_realoutsize - stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt;
3963 }
3964 stcb->asoc.strm_pending_add_size = 0;
3965 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding)
3966 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding--;
3967 if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED) {
3968 /* Put the new streams into effect */
3969 int i;
3970 for (i = asoc->streamoutcnt; i < (asoc->streamoutcnt + num_stream); i++) {
3971 asoc->strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_OPEN;
3972 }
3973 asoc->streamoutcnt += num_stream;
3974 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt, 0);
3975 } else if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED) {
3976 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt,
3977 SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_DENIED);
3978 } else {
3979 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt,
3980 SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_FAILED);
3981 }
3982 } else if (type == SCTP_STR_RESET_ADD_IN_STREAMS) {
3983 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding)
3984 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding--;
3985 if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED) {
3986 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt,
3987 SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_DENIED);
3988 } else if (action != SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED) {
3989 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt,
3990 SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_FAILED);
3991 }
3992 } else if (type == SCTP_STR_RESET_TSN_REQUEST) {
3993 /**
3994 * a) Adopt the new in tsn.
3995 * b) reset the map
3996 * c) Adopt the new out-tsn
3997 */
3998 struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn *resp;
3999 struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk fwdtsn;
4000 int abort_flag = 0;
4001 if (respin == NULL) {
4002 /* huh ? */
4003 return (0);
4004 }
4005 if (ntohs(respin->ph.param_length) < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn)) {
4006 return (0);
4007 }
4008 if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED) {
4009 resp = (struct sctp_stream_reset_response_tsn *)respin;
4010 asoc->stream_reset_outstanding--;
4011 fwdtsn.ch.chunk_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk));
4012 fwdtsn.ch.chunk_type = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
4013 fwdtsn.new_cumulative_tsn = htonl(ntohl(resp->senders_next_tsn) - 1);
4014 sctp_handle_forward_tsn(stcb, &fwdtsn, &abort_flag, NULL, 0);
4015 if (abort_flag) {
4016 return (1);
4017 }
4018 stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map = (ntohl(resp->senders_next_tsn) - 1);
4019 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MAP_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
4020 sctp_log_map(0, 7, asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map, SCTP_MAP_SLIDE_RESULT);
4021 }
4022
4023 stcb->asoc.tsn_last_delivered = stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn = stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map;
4024 stcb->asoc.mapping_array_base_tsn = ntohl(resp->senders_next_tsn);
4025 memset(stcb->asoc.mapping_array, 0, stcb->asoc.mapping_array_size);
4026
4027 stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_nr_map = stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map;
4028 memset(stcb->asoc.nr_mapping_array, 0, stcb->asoc.mapping_array_size);
4029
4030 stcb->asoc.sending_seq = ntohl(resp->receivers_next_tsn);
4031 stcb->asoc.last_acked_seq = stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn;
4032
4033 sctp_reset_out_streams(stcb, 0, (uint16_t *) NULL);
4034 sctp_reset_in_stream(stcb, 0, (uint16_t *) NULL);
4035 sctp_notify_stream_reset_tsn(stcb, stcb->asoc.sending_seq, (stcb->asoc.mapping_array_base_tsn + 1), 0);
4036 } else if (action == SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED) {
4037 sctp_notify_stream_reset_tsn(stcb, stcb->asoc.sending_seq, (stcb->asoc.mapping_array_base_tsn + 1),
4038 SCTP_ASSOC_RESET_DENIED);
4039 } else {
4040 sctp_notify_stream_reset_tsn(stcb, stcb->asoc.sending_seq, (stcb->asoc.mapping_array_base_tsn + 1),
4041 SCTP_ASSOC_RESET_FAILED);
4042 }
4043 }
4044 /* get rid of the request and get the request flags */
4045 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding == 0) {
4046 sctp_clean_up_stream_reset(stcb);
4047 }
4048 }
4049 }
4050 if (asoc->stream_reset_outstanding == 0) {
4051 sctp_send_stream_reset_out_if_possible(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4052 }
4053 return (0);
4054}
4055
4056static void
4057sctp_handle_str_reset_request_in(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4058 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
4059 struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *req, int trunc)
4060{
4061 uint32_t seq;
4062 int len, i;
4063 int number_entries;
4064 uint16_t temp;
4065
4066 /*
4067 * peer wants me to send a str-reset to him for my outgoing seq's if
4068 * seq_in is right.
4069 */
4070 struct sctp_association *asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4071
4072 seq = ntohl(req->request_seq);
4073 if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in == seq) {
4074 asoc->last_reset_action[1] = asoc->last_reset_action[0];
4075 if (!(asoc->local_strreset_support & SCTP_ENABLE_RESET_STREAM_REQ)) {
4076 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4077 } else if (trunc) {
4078 /* Can't do it, since they exceeded our buffer size */
4079 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4080 } else if (stcb->asoc.stream_reset_out_is_outstanding == 0) {
4081 len = ntohs(req->ph.param_length);
4082 number_entries = ((len - sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request)) / sizeof(uint16_t));
4083 if (number_entries) {
4084 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
4085 temp = ntohs(req->list_of_streams[i]);
4086 if (temp >= stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt) {
4087 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4088 goto bad_boy;
4089 }
4090 req->list_of_streams[i] = temp;
4091 }
4092 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
4093 if (stcb->asoc.strmout[req->list_of_streams[i]].state == SCTP_STREAM_OPEN) {
4094 stcb->asoc.strmout[req->list_of_streams[i]].state = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING;
4095 }
4096 }
4097 } else {
4098 /* Its all */
4099 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
4100 if (stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state == SCTP_STREAM_OPEN)
4101 stcb->asoc.strmout[i].state = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_PENDING;
4102 }
4103 }
4104 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED;
4105 } else {
4106 /* Can't do it, since we have sent one out */
4107 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_IN_PROGRESS;
4108 }
4109 bad_boy:
4110 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4111 asoc->str_reset_seq_in++;
4112 } else if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 1 == seq) {
4113 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4114 } else if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 2 == seq) {
4115 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[1]);
4116 } else {
4117 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_BAD_SEQNO);
4118 }
4119 sctp_send_stream_reset_out_if_possible(stcb, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4120}
4121
4122static int
4123sctp_handle_str_reset_request_tsn(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4124 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
4125 struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request *req)
4126{
4127 /* reset all in and out and update the tsn */
4128 /*
4129 * A) reset my str-seq's on in and out. B) Select a receive next,
4130 * and set cum-ack to it. Also process this selected number as a
4131 * fwd-tsn as well. C) set in the response my next sending seq.
4132 */
4133 struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk fwdtsn;
4134 struct sctp_association *asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4135 int abort_flag = 0;
4136 uint32_t seq;
4137
4138 seq = ntohl(req->request_seq);
4139 if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in == seq) {
4140 asoc->last_reset_action[1] = stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[0];
4141 if (!(asoc->local_strreset_support & SCTP_ENABLE_CHANGE_ASSOC_REQ)) {
4142 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4143 } else {
4144 fwdtsn.ch.chunk_length = htons(sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk));
4145 fwdtsn.ch.chunk_type = SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN;
4146 fwdtsn.ch.chunk_flags = 0;
4147 fwdtsn.new_cumulative_tsn = htonl(stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map + 1);
4148 sctp_handle_forward_tsn(stcb, &fwdtsn, &abort_flag, NULL, 0);
4149 if (abort_flag) {
4150 return (1);
4151 }
4152 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map += SCTP_STREAM_RESET_TSN_DELTA;
4153 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MAP_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
4154 sctp_log_map(0, 10, asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map, SCTP_MAP_SLIDE_RESULT);
4155 }
4156 asoc->tsn_last_delivered = asoc->cumulative_tsn = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map;
4157 asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map + 1;
4158 memset(asoc->mapping_array, 0, asoc->mapping_array_size);
4159 asoc->highest_tsn_inside_nr_map = asoc->highest_tsn_inside_map;
4160 memset(asoc->nr_mapping_array, 0, asoc->mapping_array_size);
4161 atomic_add_int(&asoc->sending_seq, 1);
4162 /* save off historical data for retrans */
4163 asoc->last_sending_seq[1] = asoc->last_sending_seq[0];
4164 asoc->last_sending_seq[0] = asoc->sending_seq;
4165 asoc->last_base_tsnsent[1] = asoc->last_base_tsnsent[0];
4166 asoc->last_base_tsnsent[0] = asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn;
4167 sctp_reset_out_streams(stcb, 0, (uint16_t *) NULL);
4168 sctp_reset_in_stream(stcb, 0, (uint16_t *) NULL);
4169 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED;
4170 sctp_notify_stream_reset_tsn(stcb, asoc->sending_seq, (asoc->mapping_array_base_tsn + 1), 0);
4171 }
4172 sctp_add_stream_reset_result_tsn(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0],
4173 asoc->last_sending_seq[0], asoc->last_base_tsnsent[0]);
4174 asoc->str_reset_seq_in++;
4175 } else if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 1 == seq) {
4176 sctp_add_stream_reset_result_tsn(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0],
4177 asoc->last_sending_seq[0], asoc->last_base_tsnsent[0]);
4178 } else if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 2 == seq) {
4179 sctp_add_stream_reset_result_tsn(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[1],
4180 asoc->last_sending_seq[1], asoc->last_base_tsnsent[1]);
4181 } else {
4182 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_BAD_SEQNO);
4183 }
4184 return (0);
4185}
4186
4187static void
4188sctp_handle_str_reset_request_out(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4189 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
4190 struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *req, int trunc)
4191{
4192 uint32_t seq, tsn;
4193 int number_entries, len;
4194 struct sctp_association *asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4195
4196 seq = ntohl(req->request_seq);
4197
4198 /* now if its not a duplicate we process it */
4199 if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in == seq) {
4200 len = ntohs(req->ph.param_length);
4201 number_entries = ((len - sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request)) / sizeof(uint16_t));
4202 /*
4203 * the sender is resetting, handle the list issue.. we must
4204 * a) verify if we can do the reset, if so no problem b) If
4205 * we can't do the reset we must copy the request. c) queue
4206 * it, and setup the data in processor to trigger it off
4207 * when needed and dequeue all the queued data.
4208 */
4209 tsn = ntohl(req->send_reset_at_tsn);
4210
4211 /* move the reset action back one */
4212 asoc->last_reset_action[1] = asoc->last_reset_action[0];
4213 if (!(asoc->local_strreset_support & SCTP_ENABLE_RESET_STREAM_REQ)) {
4214 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4215 } else if (trunc) {
4216 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4217 } else if (SCTP_TSN_GE(asoc->cumulative_tsn, tsn)) {
4218 /* we can do it now */
4219 sctp_reset_in_stream(stcb, number_entries, req->list_of_streams);
4220 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED;
4221 } else {
4222 /*
4223 * we must queue it up and thus wait for the TSN's
4224 * to arrive that are at or before tsn
4225 */
4226 struct sctp_stream_reset_list *liste;
4227 int siz;
4228
4229 siz = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_list) + (number_entries * sizeof(uint16_t));
4230 SCTP_MALLOC(liste, struct sctp_stream_reset_list *,
4231 siz, SCTP_M_STRESET);
4232 if (liste == NULL) {
4233 /* gak out of memory */
4234 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4235 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4236 return;
4237 }
4238 liste->seq = seq;
4239 liste->tsn = tsn;
4240 liste->number_entries = number_entries;
4241 memcpy(&liste->list_of_streams, req->list_of_streams, number_entries * sizeof(uint16_t));
4242 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->resetHead, liste, next_resp);
4243 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS;
4244 }
4245 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4246 asoc->str_reset_seq_in++;
4247 } else if ((asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 1) == seq) {
4248 /*
4249 * one seq back, just echo back last action since my
4250 * response was lost.
4251 */
4252 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4253 } else if ((asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 2) == seq) {
4254 /*
4255 * two seq back, just echo back last action since my
4256 * response was lost.
4257 */
4258 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[1]);
4259 } else {
4260 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_BAD_SEQNO);
4261 }
4262}
4263
4264static void
4265sctp_handle_str_reset_add_strm(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk,
4266 struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *str_add)
4267{
4268 /*
4269 * Peer is requesting to add more streams.
4270 * If its within our max-streams we will
4271 * allow it.
4272 */
4273 uint32_t num_stream, i;
4274 uint32_t seq;
4275 struct sctp_association *asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4276 struct sctp_queued_to_read *ctl, *nctl;
4277
4278 /* Get the number. */
4279 seq = ntohl(str_add->request_seq);
4280 num_stream = ntohs(str_add->number_of_streams);
4281 /* Now what would be the new total? */
4282 if (asoc->str_reset_seq_in == seq) {
4283 num_stream += stcb->asoc.streamincnt;
4284 stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[1] = stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[0];
4285 if (!(asoc->local_strreset_support & SCTP_ENABLE_CHANGE_ASSOC_REQ)) {
4286 asoc->last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4287 } else if ((num_stream > stcb->asoc.max_inbound_streams) ||
4288 (num_stream > 0xffff)) {
4289 /* We must reject it they ask for to many */
4290 denied:
4291 stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;
4292 } else {
4293 /* Ok, we can do that :-) */
4294 struct sctp_stream_in *oldstrm;
4295
4296 /* save off the old */
4297 oldstrm = stcb->asoc.strmin;
4298 SCTP_MALLOC(stcb->asoc.strmin, struct sctp_stream_in *,
4299 (num_stream * sizeof(struct sctp_stream_in)),
4300 SCTP_M_STRMI);
4301 if (stcb->asoc.strmin == NULL) {
4302 stcb->asoc.strmin = oldstrm;
4303 goto denied;
4304 }
4305 /* copy off the old data */
4306 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamincnt; i++) {
4307 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].inqueue);
4308 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].uno_inqueue);
4309 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].sid = i;
4310 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].last_mid_delivered = oldstrm[i].last_mid_delivered;
4311 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].delivery_started = oldstrm[i].delivery_started;
4312 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].pd_api_started = oldstrm[i].pd_api_started;
4313 /* now anything on those queues? */
4314 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(ctl, &oldstrm[i].inqueue, next_instrm, nctl) {
4315 TAILQ_REMOVE(&oldstrm[i].inqueue, ctl, next_instrm);
4316 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].inqueue, ctl, next_instrm);
4317 }
4318 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(ctl, &oldstrm[i].uno_inqueue, next_instrm, nctl) {
4319 TAILQ_REMOVE(&oldstrm[i].uno_inqueue, ctl, next_instrm);
4320 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].uno_inqueue, ctl, next_instrm);
4321 }
4322 }
4323 /* Init the new streams */
4324 for (i = stcb->asoc.streamincnt; i < num_stream; i++) {
4325 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].inqueue);
4326 TAILQ_INIT(&stcb->asoc.strmin[i].uno_inqueue);
4327 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].sid = i;
4328 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].last_mid_delivered = 0xffffffff;
4329 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].pd_api_started = 0;
4330 stcb->asoc.strmin[i].delivery_started = 0;
4331 }
4332 SCTP_FREE(oldstrm, SCTP_M_STRMI);
4333 /* update the size */
4334 stcb->asoc.streamincnt = num_stream;
4335 stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED;
4336 sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(stcb, stcb->asoc.streamincnt, stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt, 0);
4337 }
4338 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4339 asoc->str_reset_seq_in++;
4340 } else if ((asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 1) == seq) {
4341 /*
4342 * one seq back, just echo back last action since my
4343 * response was lost.
4344 */
4345 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4346 } else if ((asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 2) == seq) {
4347 /*
4348 * two seq back, just echo back last action since my
4349 * response was lost.
4350 */
4351 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[1]);
4352 } else {
4353 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_BAD_SEQNO);
4354 }
4355}

4360{
4361 /*
4362 * Peer is requesting to add more streams.

4365 */

4369
4370 /* Get the number. */

4392 stcb->asoc.last_reset_action[0] = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_DENIED;

4400 * response was lost.
4401 */
4402 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[0]);
4403 } else if ((asoc->str_reset_seq_in - 2) == seq) {
4404 /*
4405 * two seq back, just echo back last action since my
4406 * response was lost.
4407 */
4408 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, asoc->last_reset_action[1]);
4409 } else {
4410 sctp_add_stream_reset_result(chk, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_ERR_BAD_SEQNO);
4411 }
