4414#ifdef __GNUC__
4415__attribute__ ((noinline))
4416#endif
4417static int
4418sctp_handle_stream_reset(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct mbuf *m, int offset,
4419 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch_req)
4420{
4421 uint16_t remaining_length, param_len, ptype;
4422 struct sctp_paramhdr pstore;
4423 uint8_t cstore[SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE];
4424 uint32_t seq = 0;
4425 int num_req = 0;
4426 int trunc = 0;
4427 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
4428 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
4429 struct sctp_paramhdr *ph;
4430 int ret_code = 0;
4431 int num_param = 0;
4432
4433 /* now it may be a reset or a reset-response */
4434 remaining_length = ntohs(ch_req->chunk_length) - sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
4435
4436 /* setup for adding the response */
4437 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
4438 if (chk == NULL) {
4439 return (ret_code);
4440 }
4441 chk->copy_by_ref = 0;
4442 chk->rec.chunk_id.id = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
4443 chk->rec.chunk_id.can_take_data = 0;
4444 chk->flags = 0;
4445 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4446 chk->no_fr_allowed = 0;
4447 chk->book_size = chk->send_size = sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
4448 chk->book_size_scale = 0;
4449 chk->data = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4450 if (chk->data == NULL) {
4451 strres_nochunk:
4452 if (chk->data) {
4453 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
4454 chk->data = NULL;
4455 }
4456 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4457 return (ret_code);
4458 }
4459 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(chk->data, SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD);
4460
4461 /* setup chunk parameters */
4462 chk->sent = SCTP_DATAGRAM_UNSENT;
4463 chk->snd_count = 0;
4464 chk->whoTo = NULL;
4465
4466 ch = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
4467 ch->chunk_type = SCTP_STREAM_RESET;
4468 ch->chunk_flags = 0;
4469 ch->chunk_length = htons(chk->send_size);
4470 SCTP_BUF_LEN(chk->data) = SCTP_SIZE32(chk->send_size);
4471 offset += sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
4472 while (remaining_length >= sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr)) {
4473 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset, sizeof(pstore), (uint8_t *)&pstore);
4474 if (ph == NULL) {
4475 /* TSNH */
4476 break;
4477 }
4478 param_len = ntohs(ph->param_length);
4479 if ((param_len > remaining_length) ||
4480 (param_len < (sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + sizeof(uint32_t)))) {
4481 /* bad parameter length */
4482 break;
4483 }
4484 ph = (struct sctp_paramhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset, min(param_len, sizeof(cstore)),
4485 (uint8_t *)&cstore);
4486 if (ph == NULL) {
4487 /* TSNH */
4488 break;
4489 }
4490 ptype = ntohs(ph->param_type);
4491 num_param++;
4492 if (param_len > sizeof(cstore)) {
4493 trunc = 1;
4494 } else {
4495 trunc = 0;
4496 }
4497 if (num_param > SCTP_MAX_RESET_PARAMS) {
4498 /* hit the max of parameters already sorry.. */
4499 break;
4500 }
4501 if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_OUT_REQUEST) {
4502 struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *req_out;
4503
4504 if (param_len < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request)) {
4505 break;
4506 }
4507 req_out = (struct sctp_stream_reset_out_request *)ph;
4508 num_req++;
4509 if (stcb->asoc.stream_reset_outstanding) {
4510 seq = ntohl(req_out->response_seq);
4511 if (seq == stcb->asoc.str_reset_seq_out) {
4512 /* implicit ack */
4513 (void)sctp_handle_stream_reset_response(stcb, seq, SCTP_STREAM_RESET_RESULT_PERFORMED, NULL);
4514 }
4515 }
4516 sctp_handle_str_reset_request_out(stcb, chk, req_out, trunc);
4517 } else if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_ADD_OUT_STREAMS) {
4518 struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *str_add;
4519
4520 if (param_len < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm)) {
4521 break;
4522 }
4523 str_add = (struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *)ph;
4524 num_req++;
4525 sctp_handle_str_reset_add_strm(stcb, chk, str_add);
4526 } else if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_ADD_IN_STREAMS) {
4527 struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *str_add;
4528
4529 if (param_len < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm)) {
4530 break;
4531 }
4532 str_add = (struct sctp_stream_reset_add_strm *)ph;
4533 num_req++;
4534 sctp_handle_str_reset_add_out_strm(stcb, chk, str_add);
4535 } else if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_IN_REQUEST) {
4536 struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *req_in;
4537
4538 num_req++;
4539 req_in = (struct sctp_stream_reset_in_request *)ph;
4540 sctp_handle_str_reset_request_in(stcb, chk, req_in, trunc);
4541 } else if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_TSN_REQUEST) {
4542 struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request *req_tsn;
4543
4544 num_req++;
4545 req_tsn = (struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_request *)ph;
4546 if (sctp_handle_str_reset_request_tsn(stcb, chk, req_tsn)) {
4547 ret_code = 1;
4548 goto strres_nochunk;
4549 }
4550 /* no more */
4551 break;
4552 } else if (ptype == SCTP_STR_RESET_RESPONSE) {
4553 struct sctp_stream_reset_response *resp;
4554 uint32_t result;
4555
4556 if (param_len < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_response)) {
4557 break;
4558 }
4559 resp = (struct sctp_stream_reset_response *)ph;
4560 seq = ntohl(resp->response_seq);
4561 result = ntohl(resp->result);
4562 if (sctp_handle_stream_reset_response(stcb, seq, result, resp)) {
4563 ret_code = 1;
4564 goto strres_nochunk;
4565 }
4566 } else {
4567 break;
4568 }
4569 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(param_len);
4570 if (remaining_length >= SCTP_SIZE32(param_len)) {
4571 remaining_length -= SCTP_SIZE32(param_len);
4572 } else {
4573 remaining_length = 0;
4574 }
4575 }
4576 if (num_req == 0) {
4577 /* we have no response free the stuff */
4578 goto strres_nochunk;
4579 }
4580 /* ok we have a chunk to link in */
4581 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue,
4582 chk,
4583 sctp_next);
4584 stcb->asoc.ctrl_queue_cnt++;
4585 return (ret_code);
4586}
4587
4588/*
4589 * Handle a router or endpoints report of a packet loss, there are two ways
4590 * to handle this, either we get the whole packet and must disect it
4591 * ourselves (possibly with truncation and or corruption) or it is a summary
4592 * from a middle box that did the disectting for us.
4593 */
4594static void
4595sctp_handle_packet_dropped(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk *cp,
4596 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net, uint32_t limit)
4597{
4598 struct sctp_chunk_desc desc;
4599 struct sctp_chunkhdr *chk_hdr;
4600 struct sctp_data_chunk *data_chunk;
4601 struct sctp_idata_chunk *idata_chunk;
4602 uint32_t bottle_bw, on_queue;
4603 uint32_t offset, chk_len;
4604 uint16_t pktdrp_len;
4605 uint8_t pktdrp_flags;
4606
4607 KASSERT(sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk) <= limit,
4608 ("PKTDROP chunk too small"));
4609 pktdrp_flags = cp->ch.chunk_flags;
4610 pktdrp_len = ntohs(cp->ch.chunk_length);
4611 KASSERT(limit <= pktdrp_len, ("Inconsistent limit"));
4612 if (pktdrp_flags & SCTP_PACKET_TRUNCATED) {
4613 if (ntohs(cp->trunc_len) <= pktdrp_len - sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk)) {
4614 /* The peer plays games with us. */
4615 return;
4616 }
4617 }
4618 limit -= sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk);
4619 offset = 0;
4620 if (offset == limit) {
4621 if (pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) {
4622 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpbwrpt);
4623 }
4624 } else if (offset + sizeof(struct sctphdr) > limit) {
4625 /* Only a partial SCTP common header. */
4626 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpcrupt);
4627 offset = limit;
4628 } else {
4629 /* XXX: Check embedded SCTP common header. */
4630 offset += sizeof(struct sctphdr);
4631 }
4632 /* Now parse through the chunks themselves. */
4633 while (offset < limit) {
4634 if (offset + sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) > limit) {
4635 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpcrupt);
4636 break;
4637 }
4638 chk_hdr = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)(cp->data + offset);
4639 desc.chunk_type = chk_hdr->chunk_type;
4640 /* get amount we need to move */
4641 chk_len = (uint32_t)ntohs(chk_hdr->chunk_length);
4642 if (chk_len < sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr)) {
4643 /* Someone is lying... */
4644 break;
4645 }
4646 if (desc.chunk_type == SCTP_DATA) {
4647 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported) {
4648 /* Some is playing games with us. */
4649 break;
4650 }
4651 if (chk_len <= sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk)) {
4652 /* Some is playing games with us. */
4653 break;
4654 }
4655 if (chk_len < sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk) + SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY) {
4656 /* Not enough data bytes available in the chunk. */
4657 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpnedat);
4658 goto next_chunk;
4659 }
4660 if (offset + sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk) + SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY > limit) {
4661 /* Not enough data in buffer. */
4662 break;
4663 }
4664 data_chunk = (struct sctp_data_chunk *)(cp->data + offset);
4665 memcpy(desc.data_bytes, data_chunk + 1, SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY);
4666 desc.tsn_ifany = data_chunk->dp.tsn;
4667 if (pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) {
4668 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpmbda);
4669 }
4670 } else if (desc.chunk_type == SCTP_IDATA) {
4671 if (!stcb->asoc.idata_supported) {
4672 /* Some is playing games with us. */
4673 break;
4674 }
4675 if (chk_len <= sizeof(struct sctp_idata_chunk)) {
4676 /* Some is playing games with us. */
4677 break;
4678 }
4679 if (chk_len < sizeof(struct sctp_idata_chunk) + SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY) {
4680 /* Not enough data bytes available in the chunk. */
4681 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpnedat);
4682 goto next_chunk;
4683 }
4684 if (offset + sizeof(struct sctp_idata_chunk) + SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY > limit) {
4685 /* Not enough data in buffer. */
4686 break;
4687 }
4688 idata_chunk = (struct sctp_idata_chunk *)(cp->data + offset);
4689 memcpy(desc.data_bytes, idata_chunk + 1, SCTP_NUM_DB_TO_VERIFY);
4690 desc.tsn_ifany = idata_chunk->dp.tsn;
4691 if (pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) {
4692 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpmbda);
4693 }
4694 } else {
4695 if (pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) {
4696 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpmbct);
4697 }
4698 }
4699 if (process_chunk_drop(stcb, &desc, net, pktdrp_flags)) {
4700 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrppdbrk);
4701 break;
4702 }
4703next_chunk:
4704 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(chk_len);
4705 }
4706 /* Now update any rwnd --- possibly */
4707 if ((pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) == 0) {
4708 /* From a peer, we get a rwnd report */
4709 uint32_t a_rwnd;
4710
4711 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpfehos);
4712
4713 bottle_bw = ntohl(cp->bottle_bw);
4714 on_queue = ntohl(cp->current_onq);
4715 if (bottle_bw && on_queue) {
4716 /* a rwnd report is in here */
4717 if (bottle_bw > on_queue)
4718 a_rwnd = bottle_bw - on_queue;
4719 else
4720 a_rwnd = 0;
4721
4722 if (a_rwnd == 0)
4723 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd = 0;
4724 else {
4725 if (a_rwnd > stcb->asoc.total_flight) {
4726 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd =
4727 a_rwnd - stcb->asoc.total_flight;
4728 } else {
4729 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd = 0;
4730 }
4731 if (stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd <
4732 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_ep.sctp_sws_sender) {
4733 /* SWS sender side engages */
4734 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd = 0;
4735 }
4736 }
4737 }
4738 } else {
4739 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_pdrpfmbox);
4740 }
4741
4742 /* now middle boxes in sat networks get a cwnd bump */
4743 if ((pktdrp_flags & SCTP_FROM_MIDDLE_BOX) &&
4744 (stcb->asoc.sat_t3_loss_recovery == 0) &&
4745 (stcb->asoc.sat_network)) {
4746 /*
4747 * This is debatable but for sat networks it makes sense
4748 * Note if a T3 timer has went off, we will prohibit any
4749 * changes to cwnd until we exit the t3 loss recovery.
4750 */
4751 stcb->asoc.cc_functions.sctp_cwnd_update_after_packet_dropped(stcb,
4752 net, cp, &bottle_bw, &on_queue);
4753 }
4754}
4755
4756/*
4757 * handles all control chunks in a packet inputs: - m: mbuf chain, assumed to
4758 * still contain IP/SCTP header - stcb: is the tcb found for this packet -
4759 * offset: offset into the mbuf chain to first chunkhdr - length: is the
4760 * length of the complete packet outputs: - length: modified to remaining
4761 * length after control processing - netp: modified to new sctp_nets after
4762 * cookie-echo processing - return NULL to discard the packet (ie. no asoc,
4763 * bad packet,...) otherwise return the tcb for this packet
4764 */
4765#ifdef __GNUC__
4766__attribute__ ((noinline))
4767#endif
4768static struct sctp_tcb *
4769sctp_process_control(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int *offset, int length,
4770 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
4771 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch, struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
4772 struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets **netp, int *fwd_tsn_seen,
4773#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4774 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
4775#endif
4776 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
4777{
4778 struct sctp_association *asoc;
4779 struct mbuf *op_err;
4780 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
4781 uint32_t vtag_in;
4782 int num_chunks = 0; /* number of control chunks processed */
4783 uint32_t chk_length, contiguous;
4784 int ret;
4785 int abort_no_unlock = 0;
4786 int ecne_seen = 0;
4787 int abort_flag;
4788 /*
4789 * How big should this be, and should it be alloc'd? Lets try the
4790 * d-mtu-ceiling for now (2k) and that should hopefully work ...
4791 * until we get into jumbo grams and such..
4792 */
4793 uint8_t chunk_buf[SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE];
4794 int got_auth = 0;
4795 uint32_t auth_offset = 0, auth_len = 0;
4796 int auth_skipped = 0;
4797 int asconf_cnt = 0;
4798#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4799 struct socket *so;
4800#endif
4801
4802 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "sctp_process_control: iphlen=%u, offset=%u, length=%u stcb:%p\n",
4803 iphlen, *offset, length, (void *)stcb);
4804
4805 if (stcb) {
4806 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
4807 }
4808 /* validate chunk header length... */
4809 if (ntohs(ch->chunk_length) < sizeof(*ch)) {
4810 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Invalid header length %d\n",
4811 ntohs(ch->chunk_length));
4812 *offset = length;
4813 return (stcb);
4814 }
4815 /*
4816 * validate the verification tag
4817 */
4818 vtag_in = ntohl(sh->v_tag);
4819
4820 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_INITIATION) {
4821 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Its an INIT of len:%d vtag:%x\n",
4822 ntohs(ch->chunk_length), vtag_in);
4823 if (vtag_in != 0) {
4824 /* protocol error- silently discard... */
4825 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_badvtag);
4826 if (stcb != NULL) {
4827 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4828 }
4829 return (NULL);
4830 }
4831 } else if (ch->chunk_type != SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
4832 /*
4833 * If there is no stcb, skip the AUTH chunk and process
4834 * later after a stcb is found (to validate the lookup was
4835 * valid.
4836 */
4837 if ((ch->chunk_type == SCTP_AUTHENTICATION) &&
4838 (stcb == NULL) &&
4839 (inp->auth_supported == 1)) {
4840 /* save this chunk for later processing */
4841 auth_skipped = 1;
4842 auth_offset = *offset;
4843 auth_len = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
4844
4845 /* (temporarily) move past this chunk */
4846 *offset += SCTP_SIZE32(auth_len);
4847 if (*offset >= length) {
4848 /* no more data left in the mbuf chain */
4849 *offset = length;
4850 return (NULL);
4851 }
4852 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, *offset,
4853 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), chunk_buf);
4854 }
4855 if (ch == NULL) {
4856 /* Help */
4857 *offset = length;
4858 return (stcb);
4859 }
4860 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO) {
4861 goto process_control_chunks;
4862 }
4863 /*
4864 * first check if it's an ASCONF with an unknown src addr we
4865 * need to look inside to find the association
4866 */
4867 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_ASCONF && stcb == NULL) {
4868 struct sctp_chunkhdr *asconf_ch = ch;
4869 uint32_t asconf_offset = 0, asconf_len = 0;
4870
4871 /* inp's refcount may be reduced */
4872 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
4873
4874 asconf_offset = *offset;
4875 do {
4876 asconf_len = ntohs(asconf_ch->chunk_length);
4877 if (asconf_len < sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_paramhdr))
4878 break;
4879 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_asconf(m,
4880 *offset,
4881 dst,
4882 sh, &inp, netp, vrf_id);
4883 if (stcb != NULL)
4884 break;
4885 asconf_offset += SCTP_SIZE32(asconf_len);
4886 asconf_ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, asconf_offset,
4887 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), chunk_buf);
4888 } while (asconf_ch != NULL && asconf_ch->chunk_type == SCTP_ASCONF);
4889 if (stcb == NULL) {
4890 /*
4891 * reduce inp's refcount if not reduced in
4892 * sctp_findassociation_ep_asconf().
4893 */
4894 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
4895 }
4896
4897 /* now go back and verify any auth chunk to be sure */
4898 if (auth_skipped && (stcb != NULL)) {
4899 struct sctp_auth_chunk *auth;
4900
4901 if (auth_len <= SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE) {
4902 auth = (struct sctp_auth_chunk *)sctp_m_getptr(m, auth_offset, auth_len, chunk_buf);
4903 got_auth = 1;
4904 auth_skipped = 0;
4905 } else {
4906 auth = NULL;
4907 }
4908 if ((auth == NULL) || sctp_handle_auth(stcb, auth, m,
4909 auth_offset)) {
4910 /* auth HMAC failed so dump it */
4911 *offset = length;
4912 return (stcb);
4913 } else {
4914 /* remaining chunks are HMAC checked */
4915 stcb->asoc.authenticated = 1;
4916 }
4917 }
4918 }
4919 if (stcb == NULL) {
4920 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "OOTB, %s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
4921 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
4922 msg);
4923 /* no association, so it's out of the blue... */
4924 sctp_handle_ootb(m, iphlen, *offset, src, dst, sh, inp, op_err,
4925#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4926 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
4927#endif
4928 vrf_id, port);
4929 *offset = length;
4930 return (NULL);
4931 }
4932 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4933 /* ABORT and SHUTDOWN can use either v_tag... */
4934 if ((ch->chunk_type == SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION) ||
4935 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE) ||
4936 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED)) {
4937 /* Take the T-bit always into account. */
4938 if ((((ch->chunk_flags & SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB) == 0) &&
4939 (vtag_in == asoc->my_vtag)) ||
4940 (((ch->chunk_flags & SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB) == SCTP_HAD_NO_TCB) &&
4941 (asoc->peer_vtag != htonl(0)) &&
4942 (vtag_in == asoc->peer_vtag))) {
4943 /* this is valid */
4944 } else {
4945 /* drop this packet... */
4946 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_badvtag);
4947 if (stcb != NULL) {
4948 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4949 }
4950 return (NULL);
4951 }
4952 } else {
4953 /* for all other chunks, vtag must match */
4954 if (vtag_in != asoc->my_vtag) {
4955 /* invalid vtag... */
4956 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3,
4957 "invalid vtag: %xh, expect %xh\n",
4958 vtag_in, asoc->my_vtag);
4959 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_badvtag);
4960 if (stcb != NULL) {
4961 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4962 }
4963 *offset = length;
4964 return (NULL);
4965 }
4966 }
4967 } /* end if !SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO */
4968 /*
4969 * process all control chunks...
4970 */
4971 if (((ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
4972 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK) ||
4973 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST)) &&
4974 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
4975 /* implied cookie-ack.. we must have lost the ack */
4976 sctp_handle_cookie_ack((struct sctp_cookie_ack_chunk *)ch, stcb,
4977 *netp);
4978 }
4979
4980 process_control_chunks:
4981 while (IS_SCTP_CONTROL(ch)) {
4982 /* validate chunk length */
4983 chk_length = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
4984 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT2, "sctp_process_control: processing a chunk type=%u, len=%u\n",
4985 ch->chunk_type, chk_length);
4986 SCTP_LTRACE_CHK(inp, stcb, ch->chunk_type, chk_length);
4987 if (chk_length < sizeof(*ch) ||
4988 (*offset + (int)chk_length) > length) {
4989 *offset = length;
4990 return (stcb);
4991 }
4992 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_incontrolchunks);
4993 /*
4994 * INIT and INIT-ACK only gets the init ack "header" portion
4995 * only because we don't have to process the peer's COOKIE.
4996 * All others get a complete chunk.
4997 */
4998 switch (ch->chunk_type) {
4999 case SCTP_INITIATION:
5000 contiguous = sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk);
5001 break;
5002 case SCTP_INITIATION_ACK:
5003 contiguous = sizeof(struct sctp_init_ack_chunk);
5004 break;
5005 default:
5006 contiguous = min(chk_length, sizeof(chunk_buf));
5007 break;
5008 }
5009 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, *offset,
5010 contiguous,
5011 chunk_buf);
5012 if (ch == NULL) {
5013 *offset = length;
5014 return (stcb);
5015 }
5016
5017 num_chunks++;
5018 /* Save off the last place we got a control from */
5019 if (stcb != NULL) {
5020 if (((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) || (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_ASCONF)) {
5021 /*
5022 * allow last_control to be NULL if
5023 * ASCONF... ASCONF processing will find the
5024 * right net later
5025 */
5026 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL))
5027 stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from = *netp;
5028 }
5029 }
5030#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
5031 sctp_audit_log(0xB0, ch->chunk_type);
5032#endif
5033
5034 /* check to see if this chunk required auth, but isn't */
5035 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
5036 sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(ch->chunk_type, stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks) &&
5037 !stcb->asoc.authenticated) {
5038 /* "silently" ignore */
5039 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvauthmissing);
5040 goto next_chunk;
5041 }
5042 switch (ch->chunk_type) {
5043 case SCTP_INITIATION:
5044 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_INIT\n");
5045 /* The INIT chunk must be the only chunk. */
5046 if ((num_chunks > 1) ||
5047 (length - *offset > (int)SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length))) {
5048 /*
5049 * RFC 4960bis requires stopping the
5050 * processing of the packet.
5051 */
5052 *offset = length;
5053 return (stcb);
5054 }
5055 /* Honor our resource limit. */
5056 if (chk_length > SCTP_LARGEST_INIT_ACCEPTED) {
5057 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
5058 sctp_abort_association(inp, stcb, m, iphlen,
5059 src, dst, sh, op_err,
5060#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5061 mflowtype, mflowid,
5062#endif
5063 vrf_id, port);
5064 *offset = length;
5065 return (NULL);
5066 }
5067 sctp_handle_init(m, iphlen, *offset, src, dst, sh,
5068 (struct sctp_init_chunk *)ch, inp,
5069 stcb, *netp, &abort_no_unlock,
5070#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5071 mflowtype, mflowid,
5072#endif
5073 vrf_id, port);
5074 *offset = length;
5075 if ((!abort_no_unlock) && (stcb != NULL)) {
5076 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5077 }
5078 return (NULL);
5079 break;
5080 case SCTP_PAD_CHUNK:
5081 break;
5082 case SCTP_INITIATION_ACK:
5083 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_INIT_ACK\n");
5084 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5085 /* We are not interested anymore */
5086 if ((stcb != NULL) && (stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size)) {
5087 ;
5088 } else {
5089 *offset = length;
5090 if (stcb != NULL) {
5091#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5092 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
5093 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5094 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5095 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
5096 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5097 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5098#endif
5099 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
5100 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_29);
5101#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5102 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5103#endif
5104 }
5105 return (NULL);
5106 }
5107 }
5108 /* The INIT-ACK chunk must be the only chunk. */
5109 if ((num_chunks > 1) ||
5110 (length - *offset > (int)SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length))) {
5111 *offset = length;
5112 return (stcb);
5113 }
5114 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5115 ret = sctp_handle_init_ack(m, iphlen, *offset,
5116 src, dst, sh,
5117 (struct sctp_init_ack_chunk *)ch,
5118 stcb, *netp,
5119 &abort_no_unlock,
5120#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5121 mflowtype, mflowid,
5122#endif
5123 vrf_id);
5124 } else {
5125 ret = -1;
5126 }
5127 *offset = length;
5128 if (abort_no_unlock) {
5129 return (NULL);
5130 }
5131 /*
5132 * Special case, I must call the output routine to
5133 * get the cookie echoed
5134 */
5135 if ((stcb != NULL) && (ret == 0)) {
5136 sctp_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_CONTROL_PROC, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
5137 }
5138 return (stcb);
5139 break;
5140 case SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK:
5141 case SCTP_NR_SELECTIVE_ACK:
5142 {
5143 int abort_now = 0;
5144 uint32_t a_rwnd, cum_ack;
5145 uint16_t num_seg, num_nr_seg, num_dup;
5146 uint8_t flags;
5147 int offset_seg, offset_dup;
5148
5149 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s\n",
5150 ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK ? "SCTP_SACK" : "SCTP_NR_SACK");
5151 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvsacks);
5152 if (stcb == NULL) {
5153 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INDATA1, "No stcb when processing %s chunk\n",
5154 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ? "SCTP_SACK" : "SCTP_NR_SACK");
5155 break;
5156 }
5157 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
5158 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk)) {
5159 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INDATA1, "Bad size on SACK chunk, too small\n");
5160 break;
5161 }
5162 } else {
5163 if (stcb->asoc.nrsack_supported == 0) {
5164 goto unknown_chunk;
5165 }
5166 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk)) {
5167 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INDATA1, "Bad size on NR_SACK chunk, too small\n");
5168 break;
5169 }
5170 }
5171 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) {
5172 /*-
5173 * If we have sent a shutdown-ack, we will pay no
5174 * attention to a sack sent in to us since
5175 * we don't care anymore.
5176 */
5177 break;
5178 }
5179 flags = ch->chunk_flags;
5180 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) {
5181 struct sctp_sack_chunk *sack;
5182
5183 sack = (struct sctp_sack_chunk *)ch;
5184 cum_ack = ntohl(sack->sack.cum_tsn_ack);
5185 num_seg = ntohs(sack->sack.num_gap_ack_blks);
5186 num_nr_seg = 0;
5187 num_dup = ntohs(sack->sack.num_dup_tsns);
5188 a_rwnd = ntohl(sack->sack.a_rwnd);
5189 if (sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk) +
5190 num_seg * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block) +
5191 num_dup * sizeof(uint32_t) != chk_length) {
5192 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INDATA1, "Bad size of SACK chunk\n");
5193 break;
5194 }
5195 offset_seg = *offset + sizeof(struct sctp_sack_chunk);
5196 offset_dup = offset_seg + num_seg * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block);
5197 } else {
5198 struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk *nr_sack;
5199
5200 nr_sack = (struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk *)ch;
5201 cum_ack = ntohl(nr_sack->nr_sack.cum_tsn_ack);
5202 num_seg = ntohs(nr_sack->nr_sack.num_gap_ack_blks);
5203 num_nr_seg = ntohs(nr_sack->nr_sack.num_nr_gap_ack_blks);
5204 num_dup = ntohs(nr_sack->nr_sack.num_dup_tsns);
5205 a_rwnd = ntohl(nr_sack->nr_sack.a_rwnd);
5206 if (sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk) +
5207 (num_seg + num_nr_seg) * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block) +
5208 num_dup * sizeof(uint32_t) != chk_length) {
5209 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INDATA1, "Bad size of NR_SACK chunk\n");
5210 break;
5211 }
5212 offset_seg = *offset + sizeof(struct sctp_nr_sack_chunk);
5213 offset_dup = offset_seg + (num_seg + num_nr_seg) * sizeof(struct sctp_gap_ack_block);
5214 }
5215 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s process cum_ack:%x num_seg:%d a_rwnd:%d\n",
5216 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SELECTIVE_ACK) ? "SCTP_SACK" : "SCTP_NR_SACK",
5217 cum_ack, num_seg, a_rwnd);
5218 stcb->asoc.seen_a_sack_this_pkt = 1;
5219 if ((stcb->asoc.pr_sctp_cnt == 0) &&
5220 (num_seg == 0) && (num_nr_seg == 0) &&
5221 SCTP_TSN_GE(cum_ack, stcb->asoc.last_acked_seq) &&
5222 (stcb->asoc.saw_sack_with_frags == 0) &&
5223 (stcb->asoc.saw_sack_with_nr_frags == 0) &&
5224 (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue))) {
5225 /*
5226 * We have a SIMPLE sack having no
5227 * prior segments and data on sent
5228 * queue to be acked. Use the
5229 * faster path sack processing. We
5230 * also allow window update sacks
5231 * with no missing segments to go
5232 * this way too.
5233 */
5234 sctp_express_handle_sack(stcb, cum_ack, a_rwnd,
5235 &abort_now, ecne_seen);
5236 } else {
5237 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5238 sctp_handle_sack(m, offset_seg, offset_dup, stcb,
5239 num_seg, num_nr_seg, num_dup, &abort_now, flags,
5240 cum_ack, a_rwnd, ecne_seen);
5241 }
5242 }
5243 if (abort_now) {
5244 /* ABORT signal from sack processing */
5245 *offset = length;
5246 return (NULL);
5247 }
5248 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.send_queue) &&
5249 TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue) &&
5250 (stcb->asoc.stream_queue_cnt == 0)) {
5251 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENDER_DRY, stcb, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
5252 }
5253 break;
5254 }
5255 case SCTP_HEARTBEAT_REQUEST:
5256 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_HEARTBEAT\n");
5257 if ((stcb != NULL) && (netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5258 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvheartbeat);
5259 sctp_send_heartbeat_ack(stcb, m, *offset,
5260 chk_length, *netp);
5261 }
5262 break;
5263 case SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK:
5264 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_HEARTBEAT_ACK\n");
5265 if ((stcb == NULL) || (chk_length != sizeof(struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk))) {
5266 /* Its not ours */
5267 break;
5268 }
5269 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvheartbeatack);
5270 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5271 sctp_handle_heartbeat_ack((struct sctp_heartbeat_chunk *)ch,
5272 stcb, *netp);
5273 }
5274 break;
5275 case SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION:
5276 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_ABORT, stcb %p\n",
5277 (void *)stcb);
5278 *offset = length;
5279 if ((stcb != NULL) && (netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5280 if (sctp_handle_abort((struct sctp_abort_chunk *)ch, stcb, *netp)) {
5281 return (NULL);
5282 } else {
5283 return (stcb);
5284 }
5285 } else {
5286 return (NULL);
5287 }
5288 break;
5289 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN:
5290 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_SHUTDOWN, stcb %p\n",
5291 (void *)stcb);
5292 if ((stcb == NULL) || (chk_length != sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_chunk))) {
5293 break;
5294 }
5295 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5296 abort_flag = 0;
5297 sctp_handle_shutdown((struct sctp_shutdown_chunk *)ch,
5298 stcb, *netp, &abort_flag);
5299 if (abort_flag) {
5300 *offset = length;
5301 return (NULL);
5302 }
5303 }
5304 break;
5305 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK:
5306 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK, stcb %p\n", (void *)stcb);
5307 if ((chk_length == sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk)) &&
5308 (stcb != NULL) && (netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5309 sctp_handle_shutdown_ack((struct sctp_shutdown_ack_chunk *)ch, stcb, *netp);
5310 *offset = length;
5311 return (NULL);
5312 }
5313 break;
5314 case SCTP_OPERATION_ERROR:
5315 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_OP_ERR\n");
5316 if ((stcb != NULL) && (netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL) &&
5317 sctp_handle_error(ch, stcb, *netp, contiguous) < 0) {
5318 *offset = length;
5319 return (NULL);
5320 }
5321 break;
5322 case SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO:
5323 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3,
5324 "SCTP_COOKIE_ECHO, stcb %p\n", (void *)stcb);
5325 if ((stcb != NULL) && (stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size > 0)) {
5326 ;
5327 } else {
5328 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5329 /* We are not interested anymore */
5330 abend:
5331 if (stcb != NULL) {
5332 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5333 }
5334 *offset = length;
5335 return (NULL);
5336 }
5337 }
5338 /*-
5339 * First are we accepting? We do this again here
5340 * since it is possible that a previous endpoint WAS
5341 * listening responded to a INIT-ACK and then
5342 * closed. We opened and bound.. and are now no
5343 * longer listening.
5344 *
5345 * XXXGL: notes on checking listen queue length.
5346 * 1) SCTP_IS_LISTENING() doesn't necessarily mean
5347 * SOLISTENING(), because a listening "UDP type"
5348 * socket isn't listening in terms of the socket
5349 * layer. It is a normal data flow socket, that
5350 * can fork off new connections. Thus, we should
5351 * look into sol_qlen only in case we are !UDP.
5352 * 2) Checking sol_qlen in general requires locking
5353 * the socket, and this code lacks that.
5354 */
5355 if ((stcb == NULL) &&
5356 (!SCTP_IS_LISTENING(inp) ||
5357 (!(inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UDPTYPE) &&
5358#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5359 inp->sctp_socket->sol_qlen >= inp->sctp_socket->sol_qlimit))) {
5360#else
5361 inp->sctp_socket->so_qlen >= inp->sctp_socket->so_qlimit))) {
5362#endif
5363 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
5364 (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_abort_if_one_2_one_hits_limit))) {
5365 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_OUT_OF_RESC, "");
5366 sctp_abort_association(inp, stcb, m, iphlen,
5367 src, dst, sh, op_err,
5368#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5369 mflowtype, mflowid,
5370#endif
5371 vrf_id, port);
5372 }
5373 *offset = length;
5374 return (NULL);
5375 } else {
5376 struct mbuf *ret_buf;
5377 struct sctp_inpcb *linp;
5378 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
5379
5380 if (stcb) {
5381 linp = NULL;
5382 } else {
5383 linp = inp;
5384 }
5385
5386 if (linp != NULL) {
5387 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_LOCK(linp);
5388 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
5389 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
5390 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(linp);
5391 goto abend;
5392 }
5393 }
5394
5395 if (netp != NULL) {
5396 struct sctp_tcb *locked_stcb;
5397
5398 locked_stcb = stcb;
5399 ret_buf =
5400 sctp_handle_cookie_echo(m, iphlen,
5401 *offset,
5402 src, dst,
5403 sh,
5404 (struct sctp_cookie_echo_chunk *)ch,
5405 &inp, &stcb, netp,
5406 auth_skipped,
5407 auth_offset,
5408 auth_len,
5409 &locked_stcb,
5410#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5411 mflowtype,
5412 mflowid,
5413#endif
5414 vrf_id,
5415 port);
5416 if ((locked_stcb != NULL) && (locked_stcb != stcb)) {
5417 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(locked_stcb);
5418 }
5419 if (stcb != NULL) {
5420 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
5421 }
5422 } else {
5423 ret_buf = NULL;
5424 }
5425 if (linp != NULL) {
5426 SCTP_ASOC_CREATE_UNLOCK(linp);
5427 }
5428 if (ret_buf == NULL) {
5429 if (stcb != NULL) {
5430 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5431 }
5432 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3,
5433 "GAK, null buffer\n");
5434 *offset = length;
5435 return (NULL);
5436 }
5437 /* if AUTH skipped, see if it verified... */
5438 if (auth_skipped) {
5439 got_auth = 1;
5440 auth_skipped = 0;
5441 }
5442 /* Restart the timer if we have pending data */
5443 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &stcb->asoc.sent_queue, sctp_next) {
5444 if (chk->whoTo != NULL) {
5445 break;
5446 }
5447 }
5448 if (chk != NULL) {
5449 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, chk->whoTo);
5450 }
5451 }
5452 break;
5453 case SCTP_COOKIE_ACK:
5454 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_COOKIE_ACK, stcb %p\n", (void *)stcb);
5455 if ((stcb == NULL) || chk_length != sizeof(struct sctp_cookie_ack_chunk)) {
5456 break;
5457 }
5458 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5459 /* We are not interested anymore */
5460 if ((stcb) && (stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size)) {
5461 ;
5462 } else if (stcb) {
5463#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5464 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
5465 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5466 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5467 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
5468 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5469 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5470#endif
5471 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
5472 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_30);
5473#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5474 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5475#endif
5476 *offset = length;
5477 return (NULL);
5478 }
5479 }
5480 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5481 sctp_handle_cookie_ack((struct sctp_cookie_ack_chunk *)ch, stcb, *netp);
5482 }
5483 break;
5484 case SCTP_ECN_ECHO:
5485 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_ECN_ECHO\n");
5486 if (stcb == NULL) {
5487 break;
5488 }
5489 if (stcb->asoc.ecn_supported == 0) {
5490 goto unknown_chunk;
5491 }
5492 if (chk_length != sizeof(struct sctp_ecne_chunk)) {
5493 break;
5494 }
5495 sctp_handle_ecn_echo((struct sctp_ecne_chunk *)ch, stcb);
5496 ecne_seen = 1;
5497 break;
5498 case SCTP_ECN_CWR:
5499 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_ECN_CWR\n");
5500 if (stcb == NULL) {
5501 break;
5502 }
5503 if (stcb->asoc.ecn_supported == 0) {
5504 goto unknown_chunk;
5505 }
5506 if (chk_length != sizeof(struct sctp_cwr_chunk)) {
5507 break;
5508 }
5509 sctp_handle_ecn_cwr((struct sctp_cwr_chunk *)ch, stcb, *netp);
5510 break;
5511 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE:
5512 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE, stcb %p\n", (void *)stcb);
5513 /* must be first and only chunk */
5514 if ((num_chunks > 1) ||
5515 (length - *offset > (int)SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length))) {
5516 *offset = length;
5517 return (stcb);
5518 }
5519 if ((chk_length == sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk)) &&
5520 (stcb != NULL) && (netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5521 sctp_handle_shutdown_complete((struct sctp_shutdown_complete_chunk *)ch,
5522 stcb, *netp);
5523 *offset = length;
5524 return (NULL);
5525 }
5526 break;
5527 case SCTP_ASCONF:
5528 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_ASCONF\n");
5529 if (stcb != NULL) {
5530 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 0) {
5531 goto unknown_chunk;
5532 }
5533 sctp_handle_asconf(m, *offset, src,
5534 (struct sctp_asconf_chunk *)ch, stcb, asconf_cnt == 0);
5535 asconf_cnt++;
5536 }
5537 break;
5538 case SCTP_ASCONF_ACK:
5539 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_ASCONF_ACK\n");
5540 if (stcb == NULL) {
5541 break;
5542 }
5543 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 0) {
5544 goto unknown_chunk;
5545 }
5546 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_asconf_ack_chunk)) {
5547 break;
5548 }
5549 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5550 /* He's alive so give him credit */
5551 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_THRESHOLD_LOGGING) {
5552 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_THRESHOLD_CLEAR,
5553 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count,
5554 0,
5555 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT,
5556 __LINE__);
5557 }
5558 stcb->asoc.overall_error_count = 0;
5559 sctp_handle_asconf_ack(m, *offset,
5560 (struct sctp_asconf_ack_chunk *)ch, stcb, *netp, &abort_no_unlock);
5561 if (abort_no_unlock)
5562 return (NULL);
5563 }
5564 break;
5565 case SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN:
5566 case SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN:
5567 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "%s\n",
5568 ch->chunk_type == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN ? "FORWARD_TSN" : "I_FORWARD_TSN");
5569 if (stcb == NULL) {
5570 break;
5571 }
5572 if (stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported == 0) {
5573 goto unknown_chunk;
5574 }
5575 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk)) {
5576 break;
5577 }
5578 if (((stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 1) && (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN)) ||
5579 ((stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) && (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_IFORWARD_CUM_TSN))) {
5580 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_FORWARD_CUM_TSN) {
5581 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "%s", "FORWARD-TSN chunk received when I-FORWARD-TSN was negotiated");
5582 } else {
5583 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "%s", "I-FORWARD-TSN chunk received when FORWARD-TSN was negotiated");
5584 }
5585 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_CAUSE_PROTOCOL_VIOLATION, msg);
5586 sctp_abort_an_association(inp, stcb, op_err, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
5587 *offset = length;
5588 return (NULL);
5589 }
5590 *fwd_tsn_seen = 1;
5591 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5592 /* We are not interested anymore */
5593#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5594 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
5595 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5596 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5597 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
5598 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5599 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5600#endif
5601 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
5602 SCTP_FROM_SCTP_INPUT + SCTP_LOC_31);
5603#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5604 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5605#endif
5606 *offset = length;
5607 return (NULL);
5608 }
5609 /*
5610 * For sending a SACK this looks like DATA
5611 * chunks.
5612 */
5613 stcb->asoc.last_data_chunk_from = stcb->asoc.last_control_chunk_from;
5614 abort_flag = 0;
5615 sctp_handle_forward_tsn(stcb,
5616 (struct sctp_forward_tsn_chunk *)ch, &abort_flag, m, *offset);
5617 if (abort_flag) {
5618 *offset = length;
5619 return (NULL);
5620 }
5621 break;
5622 case SCTP_STREAM_RESET:
5623 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_STREAM_RESET\n");
5624 if (stcb == NULL) {
5625 break;
5626 }
5627 if (stcb->asoc.reconfig_supported == 0) {
5628 goto unknown_chunk;
5629 }
5630 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_tsn_req)) {
5631 break;
5632 }
5633 if (sctp_handle_stream_reset(stcb, m, *offset, ch)) {
5634 /* stop processing */
5635 *offset = length;
5636 return (NULL);
5637 }
5638 break;
5639 case SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED:
5640 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED\n");
5641 if (stcb == NULL) {
5642 break;
5643 }
5644 if (stcb->asoc.pktdrop_supported == 0) {
5645 goto unknown_chunk;
5646 }
5647 if (chk_length < sizeof(struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk)) {
5648 break;
5649 }
5650 if ((netp != NULL) && (*netp != NULL)) {
5651 sctp_handle_packet_dropped((struct sctp_pktdrop_chunk *)ch,
5652 stcb, *netp,
5653 min(chk_length, contiguous));
5654 }
5655 break;
5656 case SCTP_AUTHENTICATION:
5657 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "SCTP_AUTHENTICATION\n");
5658 if (stcb == NULL) {
5659 /* save the first AUTH for later processing */
5660 if (auth_skipped == 0) {
5661 auth_offset = *offset;
5662 auth_len = chk_length;
5663 auth_skipped = 1;
5664 }
5665 /* skip this chunk (temporarily) */
5666 break;
5667 }
5668 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) {
5669 goto unknown_chunk;
5670 }
5671 if ((chk_length < (sizeof(struct sctp_auth_chunk))) ||
5672 (chk_length > (sizeof(struct sctp_auth_chunk) +
5673 SCTP_AUTH_DIGEST_LEN_MAX))) {
5674 /* Its not ours */
5675 *offset = length;
5676 return (stcb);
5677 }
5678 if (got_auth == 1) {
5679 /* skip this chunk... it's already auth'd */
5680 break;
5681 }
5682 got_auth = 1;
5683 if (sctp_handle_auth(stcb, (struct sctp_auth_chunk *)ch, m, *offset)) {
5684 /* auth HMAC failed so dump the packet */
5685 *offset = length;
5686 return (stcb);
5687 } else {
5688 /* remaining chunks are HMAC checked */
5689 stcb->asoc.authenticated = 1;
5690 }
5691 break;
5692
5693 default:
5694 unknown_chunk:
5695 /* it's an unknown chunk! */
5696 if ((ch->chunk_type & 0x40) &&
5697 (stcb != NULL) &&
5698 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_EMPTY) &&
5699 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_INUSE) &&
5700 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) != SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT)) {
5701 struct sctp_gen_error_cause *cause;
5702 int len;
5703
5704 op_err = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause),
5705 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5706 if (op_err != NULL) {
5707 len = min(SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length), (uint32_t)(length - *offset));
5708 cause = mtod(op_err, struct sctp_gen_error_cause *);
5709 cause->code = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_UNRECOG_CHUNK);
5710 cause->length = htons((uint16_t)(len + sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause)));
5711 SCTP_BUF_LEN(op_err) = sizeof(struct sctp_gen_error_cause);
5712 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err) = SCTP_M_COPYM(m, *offset, len, M_NOWAIT);
5713 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err) != NULL) {
5714#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
5715 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5716 sctp_log_mbc(SCTP_BUF_NEXT(op_err), SCTP_MBUF_ICOPY);
5717 }
5718#endif
5719 sctp_queue_op_err(stcb, op_err);
5720 } else {
5721 sctp_m_freem(op_err);
5722 }
5723 }
5724 }
5725 if ((ch->chunk_type & 0x80) == 0) {
5726 /* discard this packet */
5727 *offset = length;
5728 return (stcb);
5729 } /* else skip this bad chunk and continue... */
5730 break;
5731 } /* switch (ch->chunk_type) */
5732
5733 next_chunk:
5734 /* get the next chunk */
5735 *offset += SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length);
5736 if (*offset >= length) {
5737 /* no more data left in the mbuf chain */
5738 break;
5739 }
5740 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, *offset,
5741 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr), chunk_buf);
5742 if (ch == NULL) {
5743 *offset = length;
5744 return (stcb);
5745 }
5746 } /* while */
5747
5748 if ((asconf_cnt > 0) && (stcb != NULL)) {
5749 sctp_send_asconf_ack(stcb);
5750 }
5751 return (stcb);
5752}
5753
5754/*
5755 * common input chunk processing (v4 and v6)
5756 */
5757void
5758sctp_common_input_processing(struct mbuf **mm, int iphlen, int offset, int length,
5759 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
5760 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch,
5761 uint8_t compute_crc,
5762 uint8_t ecn_bits,
5763#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5764 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
5765#endif
5766 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
5767{
5768 uint32_t high_tsn;
5769 int fwd_tsn_seen = 0, data_processed = 0;
5770 struct mbuf *m = *mm, *op_err;
5771 char msg[SCTP_DIAG_INFO_LEN];
5772 int un_sent;
5773 int cnt_ctrl_ready = 0;
5774 struct sctp_inpcb *inp = NULL, *inp_decr = NULL;
5775 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
5776 struct sctp_nets *net = NULL;
5777#if defined(__Userspace__)
5778 struct socket *upcall_socket = NULL;
5779#endif
5780
5781 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvdatagrams);
5782#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
5783 sctp_audit_log(0xE0, 1);
5784 sctp_auditing(0, inp, stcb, net);
5785#endif
5786 if (compute_crc != 0) {
5787 uint32_t check, calc_check;
5788
5789 check = sh->checksum;
5790 sh->checksum = 0;
5791 calc_check = sctp_calculate_cksum(m, iphlen);
5792 sh->checksum = check;
5793 if (calc_check != check) {
5794 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Bad CSUM on SCTP packet calc_check:%x check:%x m:%p mlen:%d iphlen:%d\n",
5795 calc_check, check, (void *)m, length, iphlen);
5796 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr(m, offset, src, dst,
5797 sh, ch, &inp, &net, vrf_id);
5798#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
5799 if ((ch->chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) &&
5800 (net != NULL) && (net->port != port)) {
5801 if (net->port == 0) {
5802 /* UDP encapsulation turned on. */
5803 net->mtu -= sizeof(struct udphdr);
5804 if (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > net->mtu) {
5805 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
5806 }
5807 } else if (port == 0) {
5808 /* UDP encapsulation turned off. */
5809 net->mtu += sizeof(struct udphdr);
5810 /* XXX Update smallest_mtu */
5811 }
5812 net->port = port;
5813 }
5814#endif
5815#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5816 if (net != NULL) {
5817 net->flowtype = mflowtype;
5818 net->flowid = mflowid;
5819 }
5820 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
5821#endif
5822 if ((inp != NULL) && (stcb != NULL)) {
5823 sctp_send_packet_dropped(stcb, net, m, length, iphlen, 1);
5824 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_INPUT_ERROR, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
5825 } else if ((inp != NULL) && (stcb == NULL)) {
5826 inp_decr = inp;
5827 }
5828 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_badsum);
5829 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_checksumerrors);
5830 goto out;
5831 }
5832 }
5833 /* Destination port of 0 is illegal, based on RFC4960. */
5834 if (sh->dest_port == 0) {
5835 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_hdrops);
5836 goto out;
5837 }
5838 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr(m, offset, src, dst,
5839 sh, ch, &inp, &net, vrf_id);
5840#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
5841 if ((ch->chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) &&
5842 (net != NULL) && (net->port != port)) {
5843 if (net->port == 0) {
5844 /* UDP encapsulation turned on. */
5845 net->mtu -= sizeof(struct udphdr);
5846 if (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > net->mtu) {
5847 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
5848 }
5849 } else if (port == 0) {
5850 /* UDP encapsulation turned off. */
5851 net->mtu += sizeof(struct udphdr);
5852 /* XXX Update smallest_mtu */
5853 }
5854 net->port = port;
5855 }
5856#endif
5857#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5858 if (net != NULL) {
5859 net->flowtype = mflowtype;
5860 net->flowid = mflowid;
5861 }
5862#endif
5863 if (inp == NULL) {
5864#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5865 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
5866#endif
5867 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_noport);
5868#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5869 if (badport_bandlim(BANDLIM_SCTP_OOTB) < 0) {
5870 goto out;
5871 }
5872#endif
5873 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK) {
5874 sctp_send_shutdown_complete2(src, dst, sh,
5875#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5876 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
5877#endif
5878 vrf_id, port);
5879 goto out;
5880 }
5881 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE) {
5882 goto out;
5883 }
5884 if (ch->chunk_type != SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION) {
5885 if ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_blackhole) == 0) ||
5886 ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_blackhole) == 1) &&
5887 (ch->chunk_type != SCTP_INIT))) {
5888 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
5889 "Out of the blue");
5890 sctp_send_abort(m, iphlen, src, dst,
5891 sh, 0, op_err,
5892#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5893 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
5894#endif
5895 vrf_id, port);
5896 }
5897 }
5898 goto out;
5899 } else if (stcb == NULL) {
5900 inp_decr = inp;
5901 }
5902 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "Ok, Common input processing called, m:%p iphlen:%d offset:%d length:%d stcb:%p\n",
5903 (void *)m, iphlen, offset, length, (void *)stcb);
5904 if (stcb) {
5905 /* always clear this before beginning a packet */
5906 stcb->asoc.authenticated = 0;
5907 stcb->asoc.seen_a_sack_this_pkt = 0;
5908 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1, "stcb:%p state:%x\n",
5909 (void *)stcb, stcb->asoc.state);
5910
5911 if ((stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED) ||
5912 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED)) {
5913 /*-
5914 * If we hit here, we had a ref count
5915 * up when the assoc was aborted and the
5916 * timer is clearing out the assoc, we should
5917 * NOT respond to any packet.. its OOTB.
5918 */
5919 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5920 stcb = NULL;
5921#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5922 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
5923#endif
5924 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "OOTB, %s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5925 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
5926 msg);
5927 sctp_handle_ootb(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst, sh, inp, op_err,
5928#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5929 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
5930#endif
5931 vrf_id, port);
5932 goto out;
5933 }
5934 }
5935#if defined(__Userspace__)
5936 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
5937 !(stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) &&
5938 (stcb->sctp_socket != NULL)) {
5939 if (stcb->sctp_socket->so_head != NULL) {
5940 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket->so_head;
5941 } else {
5942 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket;
5943 }
5944 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
5945 soref(upcall_socket);
5946 SOCK_UNLOCK(upcall_socket);
5947 }
5948#endif
5949 if (IS_SCTP_CONTROL(ch)) {
5950 /* process the control portion of the SCTP packet */
5951 /* sa_ignore NO_NULL_CHK */
5952 stcb = sctp_process_control(m, iphlen, &offset, length,
5953 src, dst, sh, ch,
5954 inp, stcb, &net, &fwd_tsn_seen,
5955#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5956 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
5957#endif
5958 vrf_id, port);
5959 if (stcb) {
5960 /* This covers us if the cookie-echo was there
5961 * and it changes our INP.
5962 */
5963 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
5964#if defined(INET) || defined(INET6)
5965 if ((ch->chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) &&
5966 (net != NULL) && (net->port != port)) {
5967 if (net->port == 0) {
5968 /* UDP encapsulation turned on. */
5969 net->mtu -= sizeof(struct udphdr);
5970 if (stcb->asoc.smallest_mtu > net->mtu) {
5971 sctp_pathmtu_adjustment(stcb, net->mtu);
5972 }
5973 } else if (port == 0) {
5974 /* UDP encapsulation turned off. */
5975 net->mtu += sizeof(struct udphdr);
5976 /* XXX Update smallest_mtu */
5977 }
5978 net->port = port;
5979 }
5980#endif
5981 }
5982 } else {
5983 /*
5984 * no control chunks, so pre-process DATA chunks (these
5985 * checks are taken care of by control processing)
5986 */
5987
5988 /*
5989 * if DATA only packet, and auth is required, then punt...
5990 * can't have authenticated without any AUTH (control)
5991 * chunks
5992 */
5993 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
5994 sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks)) {
5995 /* "silently" ignore */
5996#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5997 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
5998#endif
5999 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvauthmissing);
6000 goto out;
6001 }
6002 if (stcb == NULL) {
6003 /* out of the blue DATA chunk */
6004#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6005 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, NULL, m, NULL, sh);
6006#endif
6007 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "OOTB, %s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6008 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
6009 msg);
6010 sctp_handle_ootb(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst, sh, inp, op_err,
6011#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6012 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
6013#endif
6014 vrf_id, port);
6015 goto out;
6016 }
6017 if (stcb->asoc.my_vtag != ntohl(sh->v_tag)) {
6018 /* v_tag mismatch! */
6019#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6020 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
6021#endif
6022 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_badvtag);
6023 goto out;
6024 }
6025 }
6026
6027#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6028 SCTP_PROBE5(receive, NULL, stcb, m, stcb, sh);
6029#endif
6030 if (stcb == NULL) {
6031 /*
6032 * no valid TCB for this packet, or we found it's a bad
6033 * packet while processing control, or we're done with this
6034 * packet (done or skip rest of data), so we drop it...
6035 */
6036 goto out;
6037 }
6038#if defined(__Userspace__)
6039 if ((upcall_socket == NULL) &&
6040 !(stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) &&
6041 (stcb->sctp_socket != NULL)) {
6042 if (stcb->sctp_socket->so_head != NULL) {
6043 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket->so_head;
6044 } else {
6045 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket;
6046 }
6047 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
6048 soref(upcall_socket);
6049 SOCK_UNLOCK(upcall_socket);
6050 }
6051#endif
6052
6053 /*
6054 * DATA chunk processing
6055 */
6056 /* plow through the data chunks while length > offset */
6057
6058 /*
6059 * Rest should be DATA only. Check authentication state if AUTH for
6060 * DATA is required.
6061 */
6062 if ((length > offset) &&
6063 (stcb != NULL) &&
6064 sctp_auth_is_required_chunk(SCTP_DATA, stcb->asoc.local_auth_chunks) &&
6065 !stcb->asoc.authenticated) {
6066 /* "silently" ignore */
6067 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvauthmissing);
6068 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_AUTH1,
6069 "Data chunk requires AUTH, skipped\n");
6070 goto trigger_send;
6071 }
6072 if (length > offset) {
6073 int retval;
6074
6075 /*
6076 * First check to make sure our state is correct. We would
6077 * not get here unless we really did have a tag, so we don't
6078 * abort if this happens, just dump the chunk silently.
6079 */
6080 switch (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb)) {
6081 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED:
6082 /*
6083 * we consider data with valid tags in this state
6084 * shows us the cookie-ack was lost. Imply it was
6085 * there.
6086 */
6087 sctp_handle_cookie_ack((struct sctp_cookie_ack_chunk *)ch, stcb, net);
6088 break;
6089 case SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT:
6090 /*
6091 * We consider OOTB any data sent during asoc setup.
6092 */
6093 SCTP_SNPRINTF(msg, sizeof(msg), "OOTB, %s:%d at %s", __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6094 op_err = sctp_generate_cause(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_diag_info_code),
6095 msg);
6096 sctp_handle_ootb(m, iphlen, offset, src, dst, sh, inp, op_err,
6097#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6098 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
6099#endif
6100 vrf_id, port);
6101 goto out;
6102 /*sa_ignore NOTREACHED*/
6103 break;
6104 case SCTP_STATE_EMPTY: /* should not happen */
6105 case SCTP_STATE_INUSE: /* should not happen */
6106 case SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED: /* This is a peer error */
6107 case SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT:
6108 default:
6109 goto out;
6110 /*sa_ignore NOTREACHED*/
6111 break;
6112 case SCTP_STATE_OPEN:
6113 case SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT:
6114 break;
6115 }
6116 /* plow through the data chunks while length > offset */
6117 retval = sctp_process_data(mm, iphlen, &offset, length,
6118 inp, stcb, net, &high_tsn);
6119 if (retval == 2) {
6120 /*
6121 * The association aborted, NO UNLOCK needed since
6122 * the association is destroyed.
6123 */
6124 stcb = NULL;
6125 goto out;
6126 }
6127 if (retval == 0) {
6128 data_processed = 1;
6129 }
6130 /*
6131 * Anything important needs to have been m_copy'ed in
6132 * process_data
6133 */
6134 }
6135
6136 /* take care of ecn */
6137 if ((data_processed == 1) &&
6138 (stcb->asoc.ecn_supported == 1) &&
6139 ((ecn_bits & SCTP_CE_BITS) == SCTP_CE_BITS)) {
6140 /* Yep, we need to add a ECNE */
6141 sctp_send_ecn_echo(stcb, net, high_tsn);
6142 }
6143
6144 if ((data_processed == 0) && (fwd_tsn_seen)) {
6145 int was_a_gap;
6146 uint32_t highest_tsn;
6147
6148 if (SCTP_TSN_GT(stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_nr_map, stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map)) {
6149 highest_tsn = stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_nr_map;
6150 } else {
6151 highest_tsn = stcb->asoc.highest_tsn_inside_map;
6152 }
6153 was_a_gap = SCTP_TSN_GT(highest_tsn, stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn);
6154 stcb->asoc.send_sack = 1;
6155 sctp_sack_check(stcb, was_a_gap);
6156 } else if (fwd_tsn_seen) {
6157 stcb->asoc.send_sack = 1;
6158 }
6159 /* trigger send of any chunks in queue... */
6160trigger_send:
6161#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
6162 sctp_audit_log(0xE0, 2);
6163 sctp_auditing(1, inp, stcb, net);
6164#endif
6165 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
6166 "Check for chunk output prw:%d tqe:%d tf=%d\n",
6167 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd,
6168 TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue),
6169 stcb->asoc.total_flight);
6170 un_sent = (stcb->asoc.total_output_queue_size - stcb->asoc.total_flight);
6171 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.control_send_queue)) {
6172 cnt_ctrl_ready = stcb->asoc.ctrl_queue_cnt - stcb->asoc.ecn_echo_cnt_onq;
6173 }
6174 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&stcb->asoc.asconf_send_queue) ||
6175 cnt_ctrl_ready ||
6176 stcb->asoc.trigger_reset ||
6177 ((un_sent > 0) &&
6178 (stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd > 0 || stcb->asoc.total_flight == 0))) {
6179 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "Calling chunk OUTPUT\n");
6180 sctp_chunk_output(inp, stcb, SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_CONTROL_PROC, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
6181 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT3, "chunk OUTPUT returns\n");
6182 }
6183#ifdef SCTP_AUDITING_ENABLED
6184 sctp_audit_log(0xE0, 3);
6185 sctp_auditing(2, inp, stcb, net);
6186#endif
6187 out:
6188 if (stcb != NULL) {
6189 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6190 }
6191#if defined(__Userspace__)
6192 if (upcall_socket != NULL) {
6193 if (upcall_socket->so_upcall != NULL) {
6194 if (soreadable(upcall_socket) ||
6195 sowriteable(upcall_socket) ||
6196 upcall_socket->so_error) {
6197 (*upcall_socket->so_upcall)(upcall_socket, upcall_socket->so_upcallarg, M_NOWAIT);
6198 }
6199 }
6200 ACCEPT_LOCK();
6201 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
6202 sorele(upcall_socket);
6203 }
6204#endif
6205 if (inp_decr != NULL) {
6206 /* reduce ref-count */
6207 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp_decr);
6208 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp_decr);
6209 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp_decr);
6210 }
6211 return;
6212}
6213
6214#ifdef INET
6215#if !defined(__Userspace__)
6216void
6217sctp_input_with_port(struct mbuf *i_pak, int off, uint16_t port)
6218{
6219 struct mbuf *m;
6220 int iphlen;
6221 uint32_t vrf_id = 0;
6222 uint8_t ecn_bits;
6223 struct sockaddr_in src, dst;
6224 struct ip *ip;
6225 struct sctphdr *sh;
6226 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
6227 int length, offset;
6228 uint8_t compute_crc;
6229#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6230 uint32_t mflowid;
6231 uint8_t mflowtype;
6232 uint16_t fibnum;
6233#endif
6234#if defined(__Userspace__)
6235 uint16_t port = 0;
6236#endif
6237
6238 iphlen = off;
6239 if (SCTP_GET_PKT_VRFID(i_pak, vrf_id)) {
6240 SCTP_RELEASE_PKT(i_pak);
6241 return;
6242 }
6243 m = SCTP_HEADER_TO_CHAIN(i_pak);
6244#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
6245 /* Log in any input mbufs */
6246 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6247 sctp_log_mbc(m, SCTP_MBUF_INPUT);
6248 }
6249#endif
6250#ifdef SCTP_PACKET_LOGGING
6251 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_LAST_PACKET_TRACING) {
6252 sctp_packet_log(m);
6253 }
6254#endif
6255#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6256 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_CRCOFFLOAD,
6257 "sctp_input(): Packet of length %d received on %s with csum_flags 0x%b.\n",
6258 m->m_pkthdr.len,
6259 if_name(m->m_pkthdr.rcvif),
6260 (int)m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags, CSUM_BITS);
6261#endif
6262#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6263 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_CRCOFFLOAD,
6264 "sctp_input(): Packet of length %d received on %s%d with csum_flags 0x%x.\n",
6265 m->m_pkthdr.len,
6266 m->m_pkthdr.rcvif->if_name,
6267 m->m_pkthdr.rcvif->if_unit,
6268 m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags);
6269#endif
6270#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6271 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_CRCOFFLOAD,
6272 "sctp_input(): Packet of length %d received on %s with csum_flags 0x%x.\n",
6273 m->m_pkthdr.len,
6274 m->m_pkthdr.rcvif->if_xname,
6275 m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags);
6276#endif
6277#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6278 mflowid = m->m_pkthdr.flowid;
6279 mflowtype = M_HASHTYPE_GET(m);
6280 fibnum = M_GETFIB(m);
6281#endif
6282 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvpackets);
6283 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER64(sctps_inpackets);
6284 /* Get IP, SCTP, and first chunk header together in the first mbuf. */
6285 offset = iphlen + sizeof(struct sctphdr) + sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
6286 if (SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) < offset) {
6287 if ((m = m_pullup(m, offset)) == NULL) {
6288 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_hdrops);
6289 return;
6290 }
6291 }
6292 ip = mtod(m, struct ip *);
6293 sh = (struct sctphdr *)((caddr_t)ip + iphlen);
6294 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)((caddr_t)sh + sizeof(struct sctphdr));
6295 offset -= sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr);
6296 memset(&src, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
6297 src.sin_family = AF_INET;
6298#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
6299 src.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
6300#endif
6301 src.sin_port = sh->src_port;
6302 src.sin_addr = ip->ip_src;
6303 memset(&dst, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
6304 dst.sin_family = AF_INET;
6305#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
6306 dst.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
6307#endif
6308 dst.sin_port = sh->dest_port;
6309 dst.sin_addr = ip->ip_dst;
6310#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6311 NTOHS(ip->ip_len);
6312#endif
6313#if defined(__linux__) || (defined(_WIN32) && defined(__Userspace__))
6314 ip->ip_len = ntohs(ip->ip_len);
6315#endif
6316#if defined(__Userspace__)
6317#if defined(__linux__) || defined(_WIN32)
6318 length = ip->ip_len;
6319#else
6320 length = ip->ip_len + iphlen;
6321#endif
6322#elif defined(__FreeBSD__)
6323 length = ntohs(ip->ip_len);
6324#elif defined(__APPLE__)
6325 length = ip->ip_len + iphlen;
6326#else
6327 length = ip->ip_len;
6328#endif
6329 /* Validate mbuf chain length with IP payload length. */
6330 if (SCTP_HEADER_LEN(m) != length) {
6331 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_INPUT1,
6332 "sctp_input() length:%d reported length:%d\n", length, SCTP_HEADER_LEN(m));
6333 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_hdrops);
6334 goto out;
6335 }
6336 /* SCTP does not allow broadcasts or multicasts */
6337 if (IN_MULTICAST(ntohl(dst.sin_addr.s_addr))) {
6338 goto out;
6339 }
6340 if (SCTP_IS_IT_BROADCAST(dst.sin_addr, m)) {
6341 goto out;
6342 }
6343 ecn_bits = ip->ip_tos;
6344#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6345 if (m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags & CSUM_SCTP_VALID) {
6346 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvhwcrc);
6347 compute_crc = 0;
6348 } else {
6349#else
6350 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_no_csum_on_loopback) &&
6351 ((src.sin_addr.s_addr == dst.sin_addr.s_addr) ||
6352 (SCTP_IS_IT_LOOPBACK(m)))) {
6353 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvhwcrc);
6354 compute_crc = 0;
6355 } else {
6356#endif
6357 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_recvswcrc);
6358 compute_crc = 1;
6359 }
6360 sctp_common_input_processing(&m, iphlen, offset, length,
6361 (struct sockaddr *)&src,
6362 (struct sockaddr *)&dst,
6363 sh, ch,
6364 compute_crc,
6365 ecn_bits,
6366#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6367 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
6368#endif
6369 vrf_id, port);
6370 out:
6371 if (m) {
6372 sctp_m_freem(m);
6373 }
6374 return;
6375}
